(1, 'AC1', 'Client Acceptance or Continuance', 'Active'),
(2, 'AC2', 'Provision of Non-Audit Services', 'Active'),
(3, 'AC3', 'Permanent File Checklist', 'Active'),
(4, 'AC4', 'Preliminary Planning Procedures - Client Involvement', 'Active'),
(5, 'AC5', 'Preliminary Analytical Procedures', 'Active'),
(6, 'AC6', 'Narrative Inherent Risk and Control Environment', 'Active'),
(7, 'AC7', 'Narrative Inherent Risk Assessment', 'Active'),
(8, 'AC8', 'Assessment of Materiality', 'Active'),
(9, 'AC9', 'Assignment Plan', 'Active'),
(10, 'AC10', 'Sample Size table', 'Active'),
(11, 'AC11', 'Team Discussions and Briefing', 'Active'),
(12, 'GPBR', 'Guide Potential Business Risks and Possible Accounting Controls', 'Active'),
(13, 'GRA', 'Guide Risk Assessment - Specific Areas', 'Active');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c2` (`acID`, `c2tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `desc`, `controleffect`, `implemented`, `assessed`, `yesno`, `comment`, `corptax`, `statutory`, `accountancy`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(2020, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Obtain a lead schedule of intangible non-current assets and goodwill, showing the movement for each class of asset during the period. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2021, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Agree totals shown on the lead schedule to the trial balance<b>(E)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2022, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(V)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2023, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Review intangible non-current assets and goodwill for reasonableness and consistency. <b>(C & E)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2024, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2025, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2026, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b>(P)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2027, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Ensure that intangible assets acquired in a business combination are recognised separately from goodwill where they are identifiable and their fair value is reliably measurable. <b>(V, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2028, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Vouch a sample of additions to supporting documentation and ensure the expenditure has been appropriately capitalised. <b>(E, R & O)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2029, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Vouch a sample of disposals to sales invoices and receipts, and ensure that the profit / loss on disposal has been correctly calculated. <b>(C, V)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2030, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>For a sample of intangible non-current assets obtain evidence that these assets still exist by agreeing to contract, patent or other supporting documentation. Ensure that they are still generating cash flows or cash savings.  <b>(E)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2031, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Ensure that goodwill is not internally generated. Also, with the exception of development expenditure that meets the recognition criteria, ensure that internally generated intangible non-current assets have not been capitalised. <b>(E)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2032, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Where development expenditure, when it is deemed to be probable that it will lead to an economic return, has been capitalised (research expenditure must always be expensed unless purchased or acquired as part of a business combination) agree capitalised expenditure costs (including finance costs where the option to capitalise these costs has also been taken) to backing documentation.  Produce a working paper to justify why the recognition criteria for capitalisation has been met. <b>(V)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2033, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Recalculate the amortisation and assess the reasonableness of rates used.  Ensure that for intangibles other than goodwill, ensure that the useful economic lives, residual values and amortisation methods adopted are reviewed by the directors annually. <b>(V)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2034, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Consider whether there is any indication that intangible non-current assets or goodwill are impaired.<b> (E, V)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2035, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Ensure that any impairment loss previously recognised against goodwill is not reversed in a subsequent period. <b>(V)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2036, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Ensure that intangible non-current assets are not revalued. <b>(V)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2037, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Ensure negative goodwill has been expensed through profit or loss when it arises.<b>(P)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2038, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Review board minutes during the period, and intangible non-current asset additions after the year end.  For those items where there was a contractual agreement in place at the year end to acquire the asset, ensure that correct disclosure has been made of capital commitments. <b>(P)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2039, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>Where the entity has recognised research and development costs as an expense, ensure the total value of these costs been quantified and disclosed.<b>(P)</b> </p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2040, 14, '2.1 B2', '2.1 B2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:22:33'),
(2041, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Obtain a lead schedule of property, plant and equipment, and investment properties, showing the movement for each class during the period. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2042, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Obtain an asset register, which lists all the assets held by the entity and their values. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2043, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Agree totals shown on the lead schedule to the trial balance and register of property, plant and equipment. <b> (E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2044, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2045, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Review property, plant and equipment for reasonableness and consistency. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2046, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2047, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2048, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b>(D)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2049, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Vouch a sample of additions to supporting documentation.<b> (E, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2050, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that the cost of self-constructed items of PPE includes, if appropriate, attributable borrowing costs. <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2051, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>If payment for additions is deferred beyond normal credit terms or if a finance lease is entered into, ensure that ‘cost’ represents the present value of all future payments.<b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2052, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Where the entity has a de minimis limit below which property, plant and equipment are not capitalised, review the entity’s policy and consider whether it is reasonable. In particular, consider whether over time it could lead to property, plant and equipment being materially understated. <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2053, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Review repairs, renewals and sundries to identify any items which should have been capitalised. <b>(V, C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2054, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Vouch a sample of disposals to contracts, sales invoices and cash receipts, and ensure that the profit / loss on disposal has been correctly calculated.<b>(E, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2055, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Check physical existence of a sample of assets. <b>(E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2056, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Check a sample of assets to documents of title.<b> (R & O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2057, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that management have reviewed the useful economic life and residual value for material items of property, plant and equipment at the end of every reporting period. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2058, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Recalculate a sample of depreciation calculations and assess the reasonableness of the rates used. <v>(V)</v><br>\r\n<i>NB: No depreciation should be provided on freehold land or investment properties.</i></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2059, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Consider whether there is any indication that items of property, plant and equipment are impaired.<b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2060, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Review register of property, plant and equipment with a member of management to ensure that obsolete and scrapped assets are identified and appropriately treated. <b>(E, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2061, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Confirm with the client whether there are any assets financed by capital grants. Where identified, complete the Fixed Assets Top Up Programme in respect of such assets.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2062, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Review finance and operating leases and ensure they have been correctly classified. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2063, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Consider the need to complete the Fixed Assets Top Up Programme in respect of leased assets</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2064, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Where applicable, for assets held under hire purchase contracts and finance leases, ensure that correct disclosure has been made of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Net book value as at the period end; and</li>\r\n    <li>Depreciation charge in the period.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Obtain copies of significant contracts / leases for the permanent file. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2065, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Review board minutes during the period, and additions of property, plant and equipment after the year end.  For those items where there was a contractual agreement in place at the year end to acquire the asset, ensure that correct disclosure has been made of capital commitments.<b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2066, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that where assets are going to be disposed of that they have been treated in accordance with IFRS 5 and they are valued at the lower of carrying value and fair value less costs to sell, ensuring that once a decision has been made to dispose of an asset, that systematic depreciation ceases. <b>(P, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2067, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that assets that meet the definition of investment properties are appropriately classified as such (including properties in the course of construction which are intended to be used as investment properties). <b>(V, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2068, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that all items of property, plant and equipment are held at either:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Fair value;</li>\r\n    <li>Deemed cost (effectively a ‘frozen valuation’ which either represents the asset’s fair value at transition to IFRS or the last value prior to transition in accordance with the entity’s previous accounting regime); or</li>\r\n    <li>Historic cost. <b>(V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2069, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>For assets held at fair value consider the reasonableness of the valuation (Where an external valuer has been used, complete the relevant tests on the N Audit Programme to document consideration of the use of an expert).  Ensure that a copy of the valuation is on the permanent file. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2070, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that all investment properties are held at either:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Fair Value (excluding those properties where a reliable estimate of Fair Value cannot be obtained); or</li>\r\n    <li>Cost (NB: The Fair Value still needs to be disclosed). <b>(V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2071, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that where the fair value model has been adopted that all investment properties held under operating leases have been capitalised and fair valued.<b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2072, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that the cost of self-constructed investment properties include, if appropriate, attributable borrowing costs.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2073, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that gains and losses on revaluation have been correctly accounted for. </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2074, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>Ensure that gains and losses on revaluation have been correctly accounted for. </p>\r\n<p><i>All changes in fair value of investment properties are recognised in profit or loss (and not other comprehensive income) and will be included in the profit and loss reserve.  However, these gains are not realised and hence are generally not available for distribution until the property is disposed of.</i></p>\r\n<p><i>Revaluation gains on other items of property, plant and equipment should be included in other comprehensive income and result in a revaluation reserve unless they represent a reversal of a loss previously recognised through profit or loss.</i></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2075, 15, '2.2.1 C2', '2.2.1 C2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:33:24'),
(2098, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>The “right of use” model of IFRS 16 does not have to be applied to leases that are short term  <i>(i.e. a lease with a term of 12 months or less from the commencement date). </i></p>\r\n<p>Confirm that any leases for which this exemption has been claimed meet the qualifying criteria.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2099, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>The “right of use” model of IFRS 16 does not have to be applied to leases for which the underlying asset is of low value <i>(refer to IFRS 16 B3 -B8 for guidance).</i></p>\r\n<p>Confirm that any leases for which this exemption has been claimed meet the qualifying criteria.</p>\r\n<p><i>NB: the “low value” criteria is an absolute criteria, based on the underlying asset having a value, when new, of US$5,000 or less. Materiality <b> <u> does not</u> </b> come into the equation..</i></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2100, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Ensure that the assessment of the lease term has taken into account each of the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The non-cancellable period of the lease;</li>\r\n    <li>Periods covered by an option to extend the lease if the lessee is reasonably certain to exercise that option; and</li>\r\n    <li>Periods covered by an option to terminate the lease if the lessee is reasonably certain not to exercise that option.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>See IFRS 16.B37 - 40 for guidance.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2101, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Ensure that if the lease term has been revised, this has only happened as a result of a change in the non-cancellable period of the lease.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2102, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>On initial measurement, the right of use asset shall be measured at cost. </p>\r\n<p>Ensure that this has been calculated appropriately.</p>\r\n<i>See IFRS 16.24 for guidance.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2103, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Generally, the right of use asset will be measured subsequently at cost less depreciation and impairment.  Complete the appropriate tests on the tangible fixed assets programme.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2104, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>On initial measurement, the lease liability is measured at the present value of the lease payments that are not paid at that time. </p>\r\n<p>Ensure that this has been calculated appropriately.</p>\r\n<i>See IFRS 16.27 for guidance.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2105, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>The discount rate to be used when calculating the present value of the lease payments is either:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The interest rate implicit in the lease, if this rate can be easily determined; or</li>\r\n    <li>The lessee’s incremental borrowing rate.  </li>\r\n    <li>Periods covered by an option to terminate the lease if the lessee is reasonably certain not to exercise that option.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Obtain appropriate evidence to support the discount rate used. </p>\r\n<i>See IFRS 16.26 for detail. </i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2106, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Where there are changes to the lease payments (for example, as a result of a change in the expected lease term, or a change in the assessment of an option to purchase the underlying asset), ensure that the lease liability is remeasured and a corresponding adjustment to the right of use asset is made.</p>\r\n<i>See IFRS 16.40 to 43 for guidance.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2107, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>If there is a lease modification, ensure this is treated as a separate lease only if both qualifying criteria in paragraph 44a have been met.</p>\r\n<p>If the criteria are not met, ensure that the modification has been accounted for correctly.</p>\r\n<i>Refer to IFRS 16.44 to 46 for guidance. </i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2108, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>IFRS 16 is applied using one of the following two methods</p>\r\n<p>(a)	The “retrospective” method: apply the Standard retrospectively to each prior reporting period presented in accordance with IAS 8 <i>Accounting Policies, Changes in Accounting Estimates and Errors, </i> subject to the expedients in paragraph IFRS 16.C3; or</p>\r\n<p>(b)	The “cumulative effect” method: retrospectively with the cumulative effect of initially applying IFRS 16 recognised as an adjustment to the opening balance of retained earnings (or other component of equity, as appropriate) of the annual reporting period that includes the date of initial application. </p>\r\n<i>The date of initial application is the start of the reporting period in which an entity first applies this Standard (i.e. 1 January 2019 for a 31 December 2019 year-end);</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2109, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Ensure that the transition to IFRS 16 has been appropriately dealt with in accordance with Appendix C of IFRS 16.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2110, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Appendix C of IFRS 16 provides a number of practical expedients to lessees who apply the Standard using the cumulative effect method. </p>\r\n<p>Ensure that any practical expedients taken advantage of have been appropriately applied.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2111, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Obtain a reconciliation that shows the impact of first-time adoption of IFRS 16. This should include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Narrative explanation of how the first-time adoption has been treated (i.e. full retrospective application or the “cumulative effect” approach);</li>\r\n    <li>Narrative explanation of the changes made on first time adoption; </li>\r\n    <li><b><u>If the retrospective method has been used:</u> </b> <br>For the preceding period, an analysis of each line item in the financial statements affected by the change, showing:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The figure as originally stated under IAS 17;</li>\r\n            <li>Any reclassification adjustments made;</li>\r\n            <li>Any remeasurement changes from applying the IFRS 16 requirements;</li>\r\n            <li>The restated figure under IFRS 16.</li>\r\n            <li>This should also include a reconciliation of retained earnings.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li><b><u>If the cumulative effect method has been used: </u></b><br>For the current period, an analysis of the difference between: \r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>operating lease commitments disclosed at the prior period end, discounted using the incremental borrowing rate; and</li>\r\n            <li>the lease liability recognised on initial application.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>A reconciliation of opening retained earnings should be also be obtained. </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2112, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2113, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Review capital grants received and ensure they have not been netted off the price of the tangible fixed asset acquired.  </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2114, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Ensure that capital grants received are correctly categorised as government grants and non-government grants.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2115, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Where grants are non-governmental in nature they must be recognised in the profit or loss section of the Statement of Comprehensive Income as soon as the conditions imposed by the grant are satisfied.  Ensure this has occurred.</p>\r\n<i>NB: Recognition in income could be as the asset is constructed, when the asset is purchased or over a specific period of time where there are conditions relating to the usage of the asset.</i>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2116, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Where grants are governmental they can either be recognised as above or the grant can be credited to deferred income and recognised systematically over the useful economic life of the asset acquired. Ascertain the method used by the client and ensure they have applied this in practice. </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2117, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Check whether assets are still being used for the purposes for which the grant was given and consider whether claw-back provisions apply.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2118, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>Consider whether capital grants applied for but not received should be treated as accrued income.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2119, 16, '2.2.2 C2-1', '2.2.2 C2-1', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:49:17'),
(2120, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Obtain a schedule of investments, split between investments in group undertakings and other investments.  <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2121, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Agree totals shown on the lead schedule to the trial balance and register of investments. <b>(E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2122, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2123, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Review investments for reasonableness and consistency. Consider whether any debt instrument included within investments would be more appropriately classified as debtors. <b>(C, E &P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2124, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2125, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2126, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate.<b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2127, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>If available, consider obtaining the Type 2 Report from the investment manager(s) or custodian(s).  Review the report(s) and based on the assurance obtained on the effectiveness and reliability of the controls in place, consider the extent to which tests 9 to 12 need to be completed.  Ensure that the relevant tests on the N section Audit Programme have been completed to document consideration of the use of a service organisation. <b>(E, R&O, C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2128, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Agree shareholdings to share certificates or other suitable documentation. <b>(E, R & O)</b></p>\r\n<i>This test is required for subsidiaries, joint ventures and associates, as well as other investments.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2129, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Check a sample of purchases to supporting documentation.<b>(E, R & O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2130, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Check a sample of disposals to contract notes and bank receipts, and ensure that the profit / loss has been correctly calculated. <b>(C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2131, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>For listed investments which must be carried at fair value, vouch period end values to published data using ‘bid’ prices. <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2132, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Check whether items denoted in a foreign currency have been translated at the correct rate. <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2133, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Ensure the audit file justifies the classification of investments as: subsidiaries, associates, joint ventures and other investments. <b>(D, V).</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2134, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>For investments in subsidiaries, associates and joint venture ensure that the entity has valued them at either:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Cost; or</li>\r\n    <li>Fair value through profit or loss; or</li>\r\n    <li>Fair value through other comprehensive income. <b>(V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2135, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>For unlisted investments (other than subsidiaries, associates or joint ventures) ensure they are accounted for at fair value through profit or loss unless their fair value cannot be reliably measured.<b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2136, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>For listed investments confirm that all dividends and interest receivable have been accounted for and that ‘dirty pricing’ has not occurred. <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2137, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Where investments are not carried at fair value, consider whether there is any indication that investments are impaired. (This could involve a review recent financial statements or budgets, or where there is significant concern, obtaining an expert valuation.) <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2138, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Where those charged with governance conclude that non-listed investments (other than subsidiaries, associates or joint ventures) cannot be reliably measured on a fair value basis obtain confirmation of this in the letter of representation.  Consider the reasonableness of the arguments put forward to rebut the presumption that most investments can fair valued. (Ideally those charged with governance should produce a ‘paper’ to support the accounting treatment adopted). <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2139, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Where non-listed investments have been fair valued, obtain details of the valuation prepared either by those charged with governance or an expert. <b> (V)</b></p>\r\n<p>NB: Details of the valuation model used and key assumptions must be disclosed in the financial statements.  <b>(D)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2140, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Where an expert’s valuation has been obtained to support the value of an investment held at fair value or as part of an impairment review, undertake the appropriate audit tests on the N audit programme.<b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2141, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Where valuations are based on a directors’ valuation, review the appropriateness of the valuation model used and the assumptions made.<b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2142, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Consider investment performance post period end to confirm no substantial fall in valuation. <b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2143, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>Ascertain whether investments have been placed as collateral or security by inspecting reports from the investment custodian, loan agreements, minutes etc. <b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2144, 17, '2.3 D2', '2.3 D2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 20:56:02'),
(2145, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Obtain a schedule of inventories. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2146, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Agree the totals on the lead schedule to the trial balance and final inventory lists. <b>(E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2147, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2148, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Review inventories for reasonableness and consistency. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2149, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2150, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2151, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2152, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>If inventory is a material figure, before the inventory count, undertake appropriate audit planning procedures and review the client’s inventory count procedures (Inventory Appendix 1).  <b>(E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2153, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>If inventory is a material figure, attend the inventory count and complete the attendance at inventory count tests (Inventory Appendix 2). <b>(E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2154, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>If the inventory valuation has been prepared by a professional inventory counter, complete the tests relating to service organisations. <b>(E, C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2155, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Verify final inventory sheets with the rough sheets produced at the count, checking that no unauthorised alterations have been made. <b>(C & E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2156, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Review inventory sheets and aged inventory printouts for potentially obsolete items and discuss with management.  <b>(E, R & O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2157, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Verify the value of a sample of inventory items to purchase invoices or costing records.<b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2158, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Where inventory is valued by reference to costing records, test the accuracy of the costing records by reviewing the appropriateness of the allocation of material costs, labour costs and overhead absorption rates. <v> (V)</v></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2159, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Ensure that ‘traded’ inventories are valued at the lower of cost and net realisable value by reviewing post period-end sales invoices for a sample of inventory items. <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2160, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Many entities provide their clients and potential clients promotional and advertising material without charge.  This might include:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Brochures and catalogues;</li>\r\n    <li>Samples;</li>\r\n    <li>Information sheets;</li>\r\n    <li>Logo merchandising, pens, mouse mats etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Ensure that these items are expensed unless they are deemed to have a net realisable value (in which case, should be valued in accordance with 15 above).  <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2161, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Test the cut-off for inventory by checking that goods received and goods dispatched around the period-end are included in the correct period.<b> (C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2162, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Consider whether any amounts should be treated as “amounts recoverable under contracts” and if necessary ensure that the supplementary Construction Contracts programme has been completed.  <b> (E, V, P, CL)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2163, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Consider whether third parties hold any inventory and ensure it is included in the client’s inventory figure. <b>(C, R & O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2164, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>If third parties hold inventory (and the amount processed by the third party during the period has been material), complete the tests relating to service organisations. <b>(E, C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2165, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Where the entity has written down specific items of inventory or has a general inventory write down policy, review its appropriateness. <b>(C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2166, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Ensure that the value of write downs of inventories during the period and write backs of provisions from previous periods are all quantified. These must be disclosed in the financial statements. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2167, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>Ensure that inventory subject to reservation of title (Romalpa Clause) is identified and an appropriate security note is included in the financial statements. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2168, 18, '2.4.1 E2', '2.4.1 E2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:01:43'),
(2169, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'aicpppa', '<p>Ensure that the Regulation of Auditor’s Checklist has been completed.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:14:51'),
(2170, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'aicpppa', '<p>If available, use “rolled forward” interim financial statements to calculate materiality and performance materiality.  Otherwise assess these based on final figure for prior period.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:14:51'),
(2171, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'aicpppa', '<p>Assess inherent risk for inventories, and using an estimated inventory valuation, calculate a sample size for test counts.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:14:51'),
(2172, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'aicpppa', '<p>Identify whether any specialist knowledge is required, either by the auditor, or by the use of an expert (if the use of an expert is required, perform appropriate tests on N2).</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:14:51'),
(2173, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'aicpppa', '<p>Obtain inventory count instructions for all locations whether or not they are to be visited.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:14:51'),
(2174, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'aicpppa', '<p>Consider whether there are any areas of concern (inventories where there have been significant changes, inventory over which controls are weak, inventories in remote locations etc.)</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:14:51'),
(2175, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'aicpppa', '<p>Identify all locations where inventory is held, and note the actual/expected value of inventory held at each location. Decide which locations are to be visited and justify this decision. Allocate staff as appropriate.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:14:51'),
(2176, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'aicpppa', '<p>For locations that are not going to be visited, note what alternative procedures will be performed.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:14:51'),
(2177, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'aicpppa', '<p>Ensure that audit staff will be in attendance throughout the inventory count and brief staff on detailed timings, precise location, inventory count instructions etc.</p>\r\n', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 21:14:51'),
(2493, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p><b>1.	OVERALL CONTROLS</b></p>\r\n<p>•	Briefing of staff and issuing of instructions beforehand?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2494, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Allocation of duties to staff?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c2` (`acID`, `c2tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `desc`, `controleffect`, `implemented`, `assessed`, `yesno`, `comment`, `corptax`, `statutory`, `accountancy`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(2495, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The supervision of the inventory count by a person not generally responsible for the custody of inventories?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2496, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Overall control by management?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2497, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p><b>2.	ORGANISATION</b></p>\r\n<p>•	The division of inventories into properly segregated areas?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2498, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The inclusion of the organisation’s inventories at outside locations, depots etc., or in the hands of third parties?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2499, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The inclusion of the organisation’s inventories at outside locations, depots etc., or in the hands of third parties?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2500, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The exclusion from listing of inventories belonging to third parties (e.g. goods sold but not delivered, goods held for repair, goods on sale or return where the risks and rewards are deemed still to rest with the third party)?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2501, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The prohibition of all internal inventory movements during the inventory count or the recording of all such movements?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2502, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The classification, identification and listing of surplus (slow moving or excess) obsolete or damaged inventory?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2503, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The inclusion in purchases of inventories received prior to the inventory count?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2504, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The correct treatment of goods in transit?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2505, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The segregation of goods arriving during the inventory count?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2506, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The inclusion of non-standard items, e.g. scrap inventories, by-products, spare parts for property, plant and equipment (which are minor in nature), stand-by equipment (which are minor in nature) and promotional material including catalogues etc.?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2507, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The inspection of W.I.P. and recording of degree of completion, quantity and condition?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2508, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The separate identification and listing of any goods that are subject to reservation of title (Romalpa Clause)?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2509, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p><b>3.	ACCOUNTING AND MEASURING</b></p><p> •	The checking of counting and weighing devices immediately prior to the inventory count to ensure they are correctly calibrated?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2510, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Controls to ensure that all items are counted and that no items are counted twice?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2511, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Counting of inventories by one person and listing by another?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2512, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Estimation of inventory quantities not easily capable of measurement?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2513, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Boxed items are opened on a sample basis and counted?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2514, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Identification of inventories which have been counted (e.g. by permanent marking on bins, floor areas etc.)?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2515, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	At least one of the counters being independent of those responsible for keeping inventory and issuing initial inventory count records?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2516, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Controls to ensure all items counted will be entered on inventory sheets?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2517, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Resolution of all differences?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2518, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p><b>4.	INVENTORY SHEETS</b></p><p>•	The pre-numbering of inventory sheets or cards?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2519, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The obtaining of signatures for all inventory sheets / cards issued or returned?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2520, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Checks to ensure that all inventory sheets / cards issued are returned to the controller even when unused?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2521, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>The initialling of inventory sheets by counters and listers?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2522, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	The recording of descriptions (i.e. locations, condition and state of completion) and quantity units on the inventory sheets / cards to ensure their identification for pricing purposes, and that they can be agreed to inventory records?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2523, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Recording of all details in ink?</p>', '', 'reff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2524, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Retention of inventory sheets / cards for subsequent reference?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2525, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p><b>5.	INVENTORY COUNT TO BE PERFORMED BY INDEPENDENT INVENTORY COUNTER</b></p>\r\n<p>•	Liaise with the client / independent inventory counter prior to attendance to ensure the smooth running at the attendance? <br> <b>NB:</b> Where an independent inventory counter is used, they are a service organisation, and if inventory held at the location exceeds performance materiality, ISA 501 requires the auditor to attend the inventory count.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2526, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p>•	Prepare a Valuation Request Letter (Proforma Documents / Appendix 3) to send to the independent inventory counter.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2527, 19, '2.4.2 E2-1', 'rcicp', '<p><b>6.	CYCLICAL INVENTORY CHECKS</b></p><p>•	Verification of each inventory item once every 12 months?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-09 22:25:08'),
(2528, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Inspect area and ensure inventory to be counted is clearly identified.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2529, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Check that inventory count instructions are being followed, and count is carefully carried out.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2530, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Count physical inventory and compare test counts to client’s count records to ensure the accuracy of the inventory count.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2531, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Select items from client’s count records and count physical inventory they represent, concentrating on material items (DO NOT MARK client’s copies).</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2532, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Ensure all differences are resolved and consider recounts if differences have arisen.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2533, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Inspect inventory count control record to determine whether all pre-numbered inventory sheets have been accounted for including unused and spoilt sheets.  Enquire into alterations / unusual items.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2534, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>If inventory sheets / cards are numerically controlled, note numbers used.  In other cases, initial all inventory sheets.  Consider whether there are any opportunities for insertion of non-existent inventory.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2535, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Scan or copy a sample or preferably all inventory sheets used.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2536, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p><b>Valuation</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure inventories which appear to be excessive, long-standing, obsolete or damaged are noted.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2537, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p><b>Cut-Off</b></p>\r\n<p>Note the last number used and the next number unused of the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Goods inwards notes;</li>\r\n    <li>Goods outwards notes;</li>\r\n    <li>Goods returned notes;</li>\r\n    <li>Purchase invoices;</li>\r\n    <li>Sales invoices;</li>\r\n    <li>Credit notes; and</li>\r\n    <li>Purchase orders.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2538, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Ascertain how goods received / dispatched during the inventory count are dealt with.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2539, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Check that the last entries in goods received records before the inventory count commenced have been included in inventory.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2540, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Check that last dispatches prior to the inventory count have been excluded from inventory and included in sales.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2541, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Check that goods received / dispatched during the inventory count have been dealt with properly.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2542, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Check that goods moving between areas are properly controlled.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2543, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>Check inventory in transit, especially intra-group inventory, has been properly identified.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2544, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p><b>Ownership</b></p>\r\n<p>Check that inventory that does not belong to the client has been properly identified and not included in the count.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2545, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '\r\n<p>Summarise the adequacy and effectiveness of the client’s inventory count procedures by preparing a report in respect of each location visited, which should include the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>What is your opinion of the capability of the individuals responsible for organising inventory-taking?</li>\r\n    <li>Were assistants properly organised and briefed?</li>\r\n    <li>Were instructions adequate? (If instructions were verbal, attach a brief summary of inventory count procedures)</li>\r\n    <li>Was inventory arranged so as to make inventory identification and counting efficient and straightforward?</li>\r\n    <li>Were inventory counters generally familiar with the inventory that they were counting?</li>\r\n    <li>What precautions were taken to prevent misdescription of the quantity units (e.g. 1 box of 10 machines recorded as 10 boxes, or imperial measurements being recorded as metric?)</li>\r\n    <li>Describe the methods used to identify and quantify obsolete, surplus and damaged inventories?</li>\r\n    <li>What is your opinion on the general reliability of the inventory count?</li>\r\n    <li>What changes would you recommend for improving future inventory counts at this location?  Have these been included in the management letter worksheet if appropriate?</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(2546, 20, '2.4.3 E2-2', '2.4.3 E2-2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 10:55:56'),
(3125, 21, '2.4.4 E2-3', '2.4.4 E2-3', '<p>Check client maintains adequate inventory records that are kept up to date. (i.e. zero profit or loss is recognised on the contract).</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:13:19'),
(3126, 21, '2.4.4 E2-3', '2.4.4 E2-3', '<p>Check inventory records are supported by purchase invoices, production records and labour analysis for transfers in and sales invoices / goods outward notes for transfers out.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:13:19'),
(3127, 21, '2.4.4 E2-3', '2.4.4 E2-3', '<p>Review sequence of pre-numbered dispatch and receipts documents.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:13:19'),
(3128, 21, '2.4.4 E2-3', '2.4.4 E2-3', '<p>Consider reviewing physical inventories at a post period-end date and reconciling back.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:13:19'),
(3129, 21, '2.4.4 E2-3', '2.4.4 E2-3', '<p>Check whether inventories are counted once a year, and consider attending interim inventory count.  Review records of the inventory count to see if necessary adjustments have been put through.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:13:19'),
(3130, 21, '2.4.4 E2-3', '2.4.4 E2-3', '<p>Verify reconciling and adjusting entries between physical and book inventories at the inventory count date.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:13:19'),
(3131, 21, '2.4.4 E2-3', '2.4.4 E2-3', '<p>Check book inventories have been updated for purchases and sales prior to the period end, and omit subsequent movements.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:13:19'),
(3132, 21, '2.4.4 E2-3', '2.4.4 E2-3', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:13:19'),
(3159, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Obtain a schedule that shows the following:</p><ul><li>Amounts recoverable on contracts;</li>\r\n    <li>Provisions for onerous contracts;</li>\r\n    <li>Payments on account;</li>\r\n    <li>Cost of material purchases for use in a later stage of the contract;</li>\r\n    <li>Cost of material purchases for use in a later stage of the contract;</li>\r\n    <li>Rectification provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>Retentions (with details of expected dates of release);.</li>\r\n</ul><p>Agree these items to the trial balance. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3160, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p><b>Contracts Recognised on the Percentage Completion Method</b></p>\r\n<p>Document which method the client uses to estimate the stage of completion of the contract.  The most common ways are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Total costs incurred as a percentage of anticipated total costs;</li>\r\n    <li>Surveys undertaken by the client, the counterparty or an independent surveyor;</li>\r\n    <li>Completion of a physical proportion of the contract work or the completion of a proportion of the service contact. <b>(V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3161, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Where revenue is recognised using the total cost to complete method, undertake a retrospective review of previous contracts to determine how accurate the entity’s budgetary function has historically been.  Review whether costs have accrued in line with expectations after the end of the reporting period.<b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3162, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Where revenue recognition is based on surveys consider the reliability of surveys undertaken.  If the surveyor is independent complete the tests on N2. </p>\r\n<p>Where the surveyor is internal or a counterparty consider how reliable they are including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Whether both the client and the counter party have conducted surveys which are independent of each other;</li>\r\n    <li>The qualifications of the surveyor;</li>\r\n    <li>Site visits by the audit team or an expert employed by the auditor;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether subsequent valuations bring into question the validity of historic valuations;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether customers question or challenge interim valuations, or whether they only ever challenge the final valuation;</li>\r\n    <li>Correspondence / complaints from customers;</li>\r\n    <li>Invoices not raised promptly after a valuation has been undertaken, or delays in settlement of those invoices. <b>(V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3163, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Where revenue recognition is based on the physical completion of a specific number of bespoke units ensure these items are either physically inspected at the stock-take or are agreed to dispatch notes close to the period end. <b>(V)</b></p>\r\n<i>As these items are made to order, physical delivery at the reporting date is not necessary to trigger revenue recognition. Unless installation is a significant part of the contact the key issue is whether production has been completed by that date.</i>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3164, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Where income recognition is based on the completion of a proportion of a service contract confirm the validity of the state of completion by:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Physical inspection (where possible);</li>\r\n    <li>Internal progress reports or progress reports sent to the client;</li>\r\n    <li>Timesheets to determine whether the cost incurred to date are reasonable based on the level of service that has allegedly been provided and any budgets that exist;</li>\r\n    <li>Where necessary, consider the need for and expert to be involved. <b>(V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3165, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p><b>Cost Allocated to Contracts</b></p>\r\n<i>The key consideration is whether costs are completely and accurately allocated to contracts, or whether there is a risk that onerous contracts will not be identified due to them being ‘disguised’.</i>\r\n<p>The tests here are in addition to the standard testing on cost of stock on E2.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3166, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Note any commission payments and consider whether they could represent a potential bribe.  <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3167, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Confirm validity of transfers between contracts. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3168, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Discuss with the client problematic contracts including, those that:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>have been subject to frequent variations1;</li>\r\n    <li>are behind schedule;</li>\r\n    <li>have been subject to complaints;</li>\r\n    <li>are outside the normal scope of the services undertaken by the client. <b>(V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>1 Consider whether variations should be accounted for as an alteration to the existing contract or whether the variation should be considered to be a separate ‘new’ contract in its own right.</i>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3169, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Where not already undertaken, review internal reports where the client assesses whether actual costs are in line with budgeted costs and undertake a review of post period end costs to ensure they are in line with expectations.   <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3170, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>From the above contract review ensure that adequate provision is made for contracts where there are foreseeable losses including penalty provisions. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3171, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Enquire into any abandoned projects to ensure that a provision is made for all unavoidable future costs.  <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3172, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Undertake a retrospective review of onerous contract provisions to ensure that with the benefit of hindsight they proved to be reliable / reasonable.  <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3173, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Review files of signed contracts or accepted bespoke orders and ensure that these contracts have been correctly accounted for. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3174, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Review client team meeting minutes and workflow documents such as planning sheets to spot potentially unidentified contracts. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3175, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Ensure that where transactions tests have been undertaken on purchase orders or the allocation of wage records that any purchase order or element of wages that have not been allocated to a contract, represent valid administration expenditure. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3176, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Ensure that sales invoices have been raised in accordance with contractual terms.  <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3177, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Ensure retentions are accounted for as part of the total revenue receivable on the contract unless they are effectively a discount to the contract value as the client never actively pursues or recovers them. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3178, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Ensure that where revenue recognised is different to the total value of invoice raised that an appropriate balance as mounts recoverable on contracts is recognised. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3179, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Ensure that for completed contracts that consideration is given to the need to provide for a rectification provision.  Assess the reasonableness of the rectification provision, and also undertake a retrospective review of previous provisions made. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3180, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Where debit and credit balances exist for the same contract consider whether these should be shown gross or net. <b>(C)</b></p>\r\n<i>FRS 102 gives little specific guidance on netting off balances on ‘long-term contracts’.  However, it would be inappropriate to show a stock balance where there is an onerous contract provision for the same contract.  Conversely, due to their different legal natures it would appear inappropriate to net amounts recoverable on contracts against payments on account.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3181, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Consider whether the time value of money is material enough to require retentions to be discounted. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3182, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p><b>Contracts where their outcome cannot be reliably assessed</b></p>\r\n<p>Where the outcome of a contract cannot be reliably assessed ensure that costs incurred are recognised in the period in which they are incurred and revenue is recognised to match costs (i.e. zero profit or loss is recognised on the contract).<b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3183, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Based on historic experience with the client and the client’s expertise at budgeting contracts, assess whether their assumption that the outcome of the contract cannot be reliably assessed is reasonable.  <b>(V)</b></p>\r\n<i>The risk of aggressive earnings or tax management should be carefully considered</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3184, 22, '2.4.5 E2-4', '2.4.5 E2-4', '<p>Consider whether any such contracts may be become onerous. If so, establish whether an appropriate provision been made. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:18:26'),
(3185, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Obtain schedules of receivables and prepayments. <b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3186, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Agree totals shown on the lead schedule to backing schedules and the trial balance. <b>(E & C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3187, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(P, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3188, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Review receivables for reasonableness and consistency.<b> (C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3189, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3190, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3191, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3192, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p><b>Trade Receivables</b></p>\r\n<p>Obtain an aged receivables’ listing and reconcile it to the trade receivables figure shown on the lead schedule. <b> (C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3193, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Consider carrying out a receivables’ circularisation on a sample of trade receivables to confirm the existence of receivables.  If a receivables’ circularisation is not undertaken, note why and state what alternative procedures are going to be undertaken. <b> (V, R & O, E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3194, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Review after-date cash for a sample of trade receivables to confirm they are recoverable.  Make enquiries regarding the recoverability of any balances still outstanding.  <b>(V, C, E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3195, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>For any outstanding trade receivable balances above performance materiality (either individually or in aggregate) at the date of the audit report, make further enquiries regarding the validity of these receivables.  Ensure that any amounts which are deemed to be irrecoverable receivables have an appropriate provision against them.<b>(V, C, E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3196, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Review all significant credit notes issued post period end to ensure they do not relate to pre period end sales. <b>(V, C, E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3197, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Ensure that any trade receivables due to be received in foreign currency have been correctly translated at the period end rate and there is an adequate accounting policy note.  <b>(P, C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3198, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Review credit balances included on the receivables’ ledger. Consider whether they represent unrecorded sales and if they are a bona fide credit balances consider reclassifying as creditors. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3199, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Test cut-off by examining sales invoices and credit notes issued around the period end and ensure recorded in the correct period by reference to underlying documents. <b>(C, V) </b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3200, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Review amounts recoverable on contracts and accrued income to ensure that cut-off has been correctly undertaken. Obtain evidence that these amounts are recoverable.  <b>(C, V) </b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3201, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Check supporting documentation for material ‘other receivables’ and consider their recoverability. (For related party balances this should include obtaining written confirmation of the balance.)    <b>(V & E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3202, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Review loans to subsidiaries and entities in which the client has a participating interest to determine whether it would be more appropriate to classify these balances as investments. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3203, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Ensure that correct cut-off procedures have been applied to loans to subsidiaries and entities in which the client has a participating interest. Specific consideration should be given to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Management charges;</li>\r\n    <li>Accrued interest;</li>\r\n    <li>Dividends still to be received. <b>(C)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3204, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Where loans receivable are denominated in a foreign currency determine by reviewing the loan documentation whether the client or the counterparty bears the risk or rewards of movements in the exchange rate.<b> (P & V)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3205, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Review all receivable balances and ensure that amounts recoverable after more than one year from the reporting date have been identified.  Also, where balances are shown as non-current, ensure that the counterparty has the legal right to avoid payment for at least 12 months.  <b> (P)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3206, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Where loans are supported by formal loan agreements review these agreements to ensure that none of the clauses trigger the loan being accounted for on a fair value basis. If any loans do need to be accounted for at fair value, complete test 28 below.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3207, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Where balances are due after more than one year, and did not carry a commercial rate of interest at inception consider whether the time value of money is material, and if so, ensure that they are accounted for on an amortised cost basis, and that an appropriate discount rate has been applied . <b>(V)</b></p>\r\n<p>Subject to materiality the following balances should be considered:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Retentions;</li>\r\n    <li>Staff loans;</li>\r\n    <li>Related party loans;</li>\r\n    <li>Rent deposits.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3208, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p><b>Audit tests ~ Prepayments</b></p>\r\n<p>24.	If prepayments are above performance materiality (either individually or in aggregate), recalculate a sample from source documentation.<b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3209, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p><b>Audit tests ~ Financial Instruments</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure that IFRS 9 has been applied to all types of financial instruments except those set out in paragraph 2.1 of IFRS 9</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3210, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Review the classification of the entity’s financial assets, which should be based on the entity’s business model and the contractual cash flows of the financial asset (known as the “SPPI” test).</p>\r\n<p>Ensure that the classification is appropriate.</p>\r\n<p><i>See IFRS 9.4.1 for detail. </i></p>\r\n<p><i>A financial asset will be classified as subsequently measured at either amortised cost, FVOCI or FVTPL depending on the entity’s business model and the contractual cash flows of the asset</i></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3211, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Despite the considerations above, an entity can choose to designate, on initial recognition, a financial asset at FVTPL if doing so mitigates an “accounting mismatch”. </p>\r\n<p>If this is the case, ensure such an asset has been treated appropriately from initial recognition..</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3212, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>For any financial asset held at fair value, carry out the following procedures (as appropriate):</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Ascertain how management has determined the fair value (e.g. calculated by management; counter-party valuation received;  independent third party valuation received);</li>\r\n    <li>Assess and test the bases and assumptions used to calculate/support the fair value;</li>\r\n    <li>If management have engaged a third party valuer, undertake the appropriate audit tests on the N audit programme to determine the reliability of the evidence obtained;</li>\r\n    <li>Consider the need to appoint an auditor’s expert (as per ISA 620). If this is considered necessary, complete the relevant test on the N audit programme;</li>\r\n    <li>Develop your own range of estimates of the fair value and compare against those used by management for reasonableness;</li>\r\n    <li>Consider whether any events subsequent to the reporting period end up to the date of the audit report provide any audit evidence.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB 1: Reliance CANNOT be placed a valuation provided by the counter-party to the financial instrument. This is due to the fact that any such valuation is not independent, and in most cases, does not provide detail of the assumptions, data or models used to support the valuation. </p>\r\n<p>NB 2: Auditors are prohibited by the IESBA Code of Ethics from providing valuation services to audit clients where the valuation involves subjectivity and the effect is material to the financial statements.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3213, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Despite the considerations above, an entity can choose to designate, on initial recognition, a financial asset at FVTPL if doing so mitigates an “accounting mismatch”. </p>\r\n<p>If this is the case, ensure such an asset has been treated appropriately from initial recognition.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3214, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>For loss allowances on assets held at FVOCI, ensure that the loss allowance has been recognised in OCI rather than reducing the carrying amount of the asset. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3215, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Ensure that a loss allowance for expected credit losses has been recognised on:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Financial assets held at amortised cost;</li>\r\n    <li>Financial assets held at FVOCI;</li>\r\n    <li>Contract assets;</li>\r\n    <li>Lease receivables, and </li>\r\n    <li>Certain loan commitments and financial guarantee contracts (see IFRS 9.5.5.1)  <b>(V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3216, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Review the guidance in IFRS 9 on measuring the loss allowance and ensure the entity has followed this. <b>(V)</b></p>\r\n<i>Note that there is a simplified approach for typical trade receivable balances (and certain other assets), where the loss allowance is measured at the amount equal to lifetime expected credit losses. See IFRS 9.5.5.15 for detail</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3217, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p><b>Derecognition</b></p>\r\n<p>Financial assets are derecognised when, and only when:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The contractual rights to the cash flows from the financial asset expire; or</li>\r\n    <li>The entity transfers the financial asset as set out in paragraphs 3.2.4 and 3.2.5 and the transfer qualifies for derecognition in accordance with paragraph 3.2.6.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Where financial assets have been transferred, review the requirements of IFRS 9.3.2.3 to 9.3.2.23 and ensure these have been complied with.  <b>(R&O, CO)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3218, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p><b>Scrutiny Tests</b></p>\r\n<p>Scrutinise the sales ledger and sales day book for unusual items.  <b>(CL, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3219, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>Scrutinise the nominal ledger and cash book for any large or unusual items of income. <b>(CL, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3220, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p><b>For periods commencing on or after 1 January 2019:</b></p>\r\n<p>Review loans and other debt instruments held at FVTPL for any early repayment features with negative compensation (that is, the difference between the prepayment amount and unpaid amounts of principal and interest). If the negative compensation amount is “reasonable compensation for early termination of the contract”, and the loan is held to collect, the loan can now be carried at amortised cost rather than at FVTPL.</p>\r\n<p>Where such financial assets were previously carried at FVTPL, ensure that the transition requirements per IFRS 9.7.2.29 to 34 are complied with.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3221, 23, '2.5 F2', '2.5 F2', '<p>37.	List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:27:14'),
(3222, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Update the permanent file to include new or varied bank mandates, bank accounts and signatories. </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3223, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Obtain a schedule of all bank and cash balances. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3224, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Agree totals shown on the lead schedule to the trial balance. <b>(E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3225, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(D, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3226, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Review cash and bank balances for reasonableness and consistency. <b>(C & E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3227, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3228, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3229, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3230, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Ensure that outstanding cheques and lodgements shown on bank reconciliations have cleared shortly after the period-end. <b>(V, E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3231, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Where bank accounts have both credit and debit balances relating to the same financial institution, consider and justify whether these figures should be ‘netted off’ or shown gross. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3232, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Obtain a bank letter from each bank with which the client has had a relationship during the period.  Agree the account balances and ensure all other matters arising are dealt with. <b>(P, R & O, E, C, V)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c2` (`acID`, `c2tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `desc`, `controleffect`, `implemented`, `assessed`, `yesno`, `comment`, `corptax`, `statutory`, `accountancy`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(3233, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Review the cash book and the bank statements around the period-end to ensure that any transfers etc. have been properly reflected in the financial statements. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3234, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Review the cash book and bank statements for the period for any unusual receipts or payments. <b>(E, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3235, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Ensure that any foreign currency balances at the period end have been correctly translated at the period end rate, and ensure there is an adequate accounting policy note. <b>(V, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3236, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Count petty cash balances and agree to the control account. <b>(V, C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3237, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>Obtain written confirmation of material petty cash floats held. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3238, 24, '2.6 H2', '2.6 H2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:31:17'),
(3239, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Obtain schedules of payables and accruals. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3240, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Agree totals shown on the lead schedule to backing schedules and the trial balance. <b>(E & C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3241, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Ensure payables are properly split between amounts due in less than one year and amounts due in more than one year.    Ensure that where balances are shown as non-current that the entity has the legal right to avoid payment for at least 12 months from the reporting date.  <b>(R & O, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3242, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3243, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Review payables for reasonableness and consistency and ensure that related party balances have been identified. <b>(P, C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3244, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3245, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3246, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3247, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Inspect board minutes, loan agreements and other evidence to ascertain whether all debentures and other loans (including bank loans) have been recorded. <b>(V, R&O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3248, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Obtain counter party confirmation of all debenture and loan account balances (including bank loans).  Agree the account balances and ensure all other matters arising are dealt with. <b>(P, R & O, E, C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3249, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Obtain details of loan covenants and consider as to whether they have been complied with. <b>(P)</b></p>\r\n<i>Where a loan covenant has been breached and not rectified by the reporting date and the financial institution has not agreed by the reporting date to ‘overlook’ the breach, the entire loan must be disclosed as repayable within one year. </i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3250, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Review loan agreements (particularly bank loans) to ensure that none of the clauses within the loan agreement trigger the loan being accounted for on a fair value basis. If any loans are to be accounted for at fair value, complete test 39 below. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3251, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Discuss with those charged with governance whether, in relation to any loan agreements, they have entered into any interest rate swaps, cap or collar arrangements through a ‘side agreement’ or via a separate contract. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3252, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Where such interest rate swaps or loans that need to be accounted for at fair value are identified, ensure the client has obtained an appropriate fair value from the counterparty and complete test 39 below. If hedge accounting is being applied, complete the tests on S2/4.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3253, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Where payable balances are due after more than one year, and did not carry a commercial rate of interest at inception, consider whether the time value of money is material, and if so, ensure they are accounted for on an amortised cost basis and that an appropriate discount rate has been applied.  <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3254, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Where loans are due after more than one year and the interest is not spread evenly over the period of the loan (for example, irregular payments throughout the loan term or a balloon payment on completion), ensure that the effective interest rate is calculated and the loan carried at amortised cost. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3255, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Ensure that cut-off has been correctly applied on loans from subsidiaries and entities in which the client has a participating interest. Specific consideration should be given to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Management charges;</li>\r\n    <li>Accrued interest;</li>\r\n    <li>Dividends still to be paid.  <b>(C)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3256, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Where loans payable are denominated in a foreign currency determine by reviewing the loan documentation whether the client or the counterparty bears the risk or rewards of movements in the exchange rate. <b>(P & V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3257, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Obtain an aged payables’ listing and reconcile it to the trade payables figure shown on the lead schedule. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3258, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Select a sample of trade payable balances and agree / reconcile them to suppliers’ statements, direct confirmation or purchase invoices.  Where the balance is reconciled to supplier statements, follow up any reconciling items and ensure all necessary provisions are included in the financial statements. <b>(V, R&O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3259, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Ensure that any payables due to be paid in foreign currency have been correctly translated at the period end rate, and ensure there is an adequate accounting policy note. <b>(V & P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3260, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Ensure cut-off has been properly dealt with.  Examine goods received notes either side of the period-end date and ensure recorded in the correct accounting period.<b> (C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3261, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Select a sample of after-date purchase invoices, cash book payments, expense claims and transactions on company credit card statements and confirm they represent post period items or are correctly recorded as payables. <b> (C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3262, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Review debit balances included on the payables’ ledger, consider whether they represent unrecorded purchases and if they are bona fide debit balances consider reclassifying as debtors.  <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3263, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Check supporting documentation for material ‘other payables’, these should include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Corporation tax;</li>\r\n    <li>Payroll deductions;</li>\r\n    <li>Any other material payable balances.<b> (V, E)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3264, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>If any finance lease individually is ‘significant’ ensure it is identified as such and suitable disclosure is included in the financial statements. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3265, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Obtain written confirmation of the value of any loans included in ‘other payables’, including any amounts due to related parties. <b>(V, R & O, E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3266, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Ensure all secured payables, including trade payables where goods are under reservation of title (Romalpa Clause), have been identified, and that appropriate disclosure has been made regarding the security. <b>(P, R&O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3267, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Ensure all payables falling partly or wholly due after more than five years have been identified, and that information relating to additional disclosure can be provided. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3268, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>If accruals are above performance materiality (either individually or in aggregate), then recalculate a sample from source documentation.<b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3269, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Review deferred income and ensure that cut-off procedures have been adequately undertaken. <b> (C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3270, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Ensure that any dividends shown in payables are final dividends and were approved prior to the reporting date. <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3271, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Ensure that any bonus shown in payables represents either a contractual or constructive obligation at the reporting date.<b> (R&O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3272, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Scrutinise the purchase ledger and purchases day book for unusual items. <b>(CL, A, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3273, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Scrutinise the nominal ledger and cash book for any large or unusual items of expenditure. <b>(CL, A, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3274, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p><b>Financial Instruments</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure that IFRS 9 has been applied to all types of financial instruments except those set out in paragraph 2.1 of IFRS 9.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3275, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>Most financial liabilities will be classified as subsequently measured at amortised cost. However, there are exceptions, as set out in IFRS 9.4.2.1.</p>\r\n<p>Review the entity’s financial liabilities and ensure these are appropriately classified.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3276, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>The entity can designate, on initial recognition, a financial liability at FVTPL if:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>doing so mitigates an “accounting mismatch”;</li>\r\n    <li>a group of financial assets and/or liabilities is managed and performance evaluated on a FV basis; or</li>\r\n    <li>it is a certain type of hybrid contract per 4.3.5 of IFRS 9.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If this is the case, ensure such a liability has been treated appropriately from initial recognition</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3277, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>For any financial liability recognised at fair value, carry out the following procedures (as appropriate):</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Ascertain how management has determined the fair value (e.g. calculated by management; counter-party valuation received; independent third party valuation received);</li>\r\n    <li>Assess and test the bases and assumptions used to calculate/support the fair value;</li>\r\n    <li>If management have engaged a third party valuer, undertake the appropriate audit tests on the N audit programme to determine the reliability of the evidence obtained;</li>\r\n    <li>Consider the need to appoint an auditor’s expert (as per ISA 620). If this is considered necessary, complete the relevant test on the N audit programme;</li>\r\n    <li>Develop your own range of estimates of the fair value and compare against those used by management for reasonableness;</li>\r\n    <li>Consider whether any events subsequent to the reporting period end up to the date of the audit report provide any audit evidence</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB 1: Reliance CANNOT be placed a valuation provided by the counter-party to the financial instrument. This is due to the fact that any such valuation is not independent, and in most cases, does not provide detail of the assumptions, data or models used to support the valuation. </p>\r\n<p>NB 2: Auditors are prohibited by the IESBA Code of Ethics from providing valuation services to audit clients where the valuation involves subjectivity and the effect is material to the financial statements.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3278, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>If the entity has contracts with embedded derivatives, ensure these have been treated in accordance with IFRS 9.4.3.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3279, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p><b>For periods commencing on or after 1 January 2019:</b></p>\r\n<p>Review loans and other debt instruments held at FVTPL for any early repayment features with negative compensation (that is, the difference between the prepayment amount and unpaid amounts of principal and interest). If the negative compensation amount is “reasonable compensation for early termination of the contract”, and the loan is held to collect, the loan can now be carried at amortised cost rather than at FVTPL. </p>\r\n<p>Where such financial assets were previously carried at FVTPL, ensure that the transition requirements per IFRS 9.7.2.29 to 34 are complied with.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3280, 25, '2.7 I2', '2.7 I2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:39:05'),
(3281, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Obtain a taxation lead schedule.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3282, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Agree the constituents of the tax charge / credit shown on the lead schedule to the trial balance.   <b>(E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3283, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s financial statements. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3284, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3285, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3286, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Ensure that where a separate tax review is going to be performed, matters from other sections of the audit working papers (for example, relating to employment or sales taxes / duties) which require special consideration from a taxation perspective have been specifically drawn to the attention of the individual performing the tax review.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3287, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3288, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Ensure that the appropriate taxation authority has acknowledged receipt and has processed the previous period’s tax return.<b> (R&O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3289, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Ensure that payments have been made on the due date (where necessary, these are the “payment on account” dates), and that interest has been provided in respect of all late payments. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3290, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Review correspondence with the appropriate taxation authority to confirm that all matters are correctly treated in the financial statements. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3291, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Obtain a copy of the current corporation tax computation. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3292, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Agree figures in the current tax computations to supporting evidence throughout the audit file. <b>(A, C, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3293, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Check the current tax computation, considering the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Items treated differently for tax and financial reporting purposes;</li>\r\n    <li>Items disallowable for tax purposes;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether allowances have been claimed on eligible assets and have been calculated correctly;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether charges on income have been correctly treated;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether all reliefs claimed are valid;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether all chargeable gains have been brought into the computation;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether available chargeable losses have been utilised;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether non-trading income has been treated correctly;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether tax charge has been calculated using correct rate has been claimed;</li>\r\n    <li>Validity of any set-offs and deductions (income tax, group relief claims etc.). <b>(V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3294, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Obtain a tax reconciliation between the expected tax charge (pre-tax profit per the financial statements multiplied by the normal tax rate) and the actual tax charge, and ensure that all reconciling items have been correctly identified. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3295, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Check how reliable previous tax provisions were and consider whether this impacts on the reliably of the current period’s estimate.  Ensure that if any unused provision from prior periods is carried forward this is for a valid reason. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3296, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Obtain a copy of the deferred tax computation. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3297, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Consider whether all circumstances leading to timing differences have been considered, for example:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Revaluations and fair value adjustments;</li>\r\n    <li>Capital allowances ‘v’ depreciation;</li>\r\n    <li>Interest and royalties paid and received;</li>\r\n    <li>General provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>Pension contribution ‘v’ pension costs;</li>\r\n    <li>Share-based payments;</li>\r\n    <li>Losses carried forward; and</li>\r\n    <li>Other timing differences.<b> (C, V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3298, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Ensure that deferred tax assets are only recognised to the extent that they are more likely than not to be recovered.  Also, ensure that where deferred tax assets are not recognised this is consistent with other information in the audit file, especially consideration of the going concern status of the entity. <b>(R&O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3299, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Confirm deferred tax has been calculated using rates that have been substantively enacted at the reporting date that are expected to apply to the reversal of the timing difference. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3300, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>Ensure that the taxation charge or credit whether it is current or deferred is recognised in the same prime statement as the underlying gain or loss. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3301, 26, '2.8 J2', '2.8 J2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 12:59:31'),
(3302, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Obtain a schedule of transactions with directors and related parties (including key management*). <b>(P)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3303, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Ensure the schedule of related parties included on the permanent file has been reviewed and updated and includes those identified in prior period audits, by previous auditors and those identified during this period’s audit. <b>(C)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3304, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Agree amounts shown on the lead schedule to the trial balance, sales ledger or purchase ledger if applicable. <b>(E)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3305, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Agree comparative figures and disclosures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements, if applicable.<b> (V)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3306, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Review transactions and balances with directors and other related parties for reasonableness and consistency. <b>(C,E)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3307, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3308, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Obtain confirmation that all transactions with directors and related parties are correctly disclosed via the letter of representation.  Ensure additional key findings from this section are included on the points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention. <b>(D, C, V, R &O)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3309, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b>(D)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3310, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Review client procedures for identifying related parties and related party transactions. <b>(C)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3311, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p><b>Directors’ loans and transactions</b></p>\r\n<p>Agree directors’ loan account balances to confirmation certificates. <b>(C, V)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3312, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Consider whether balances due from directors are recoverable. <b>(V)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3313, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Obtain details of all guarantees by client on behalf of directors and consider the maximum possible liability. <b>(P, R&O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3314, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Confirm that all transactions have been properly authorised and comply with the company’s constitution. <b>(R & O)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3315, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Ensure appropriate provision has been made for any tax falling due on the directors’ overdrawn loan accounts. <b>(C)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3316, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Where interim dividends have been paid to clear an overdrawn directors’ loan account, ensure a creditor has not been created rendering the dividend partially invalid. <b>(R&O)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3317, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p><b>Related party transactions</b> </p>\r\n<p>Discuss with the management and directors whether material related party transactions have occurred. <b>(C,P)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3318, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Ensure that salaries paid to related parties (other than directors and key management) are identified. <b>(P)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3319, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>From reviewing the audit file summarise the work that has been undertaken in the other section of the file which helps to confirm the completeness of related party transactions. <b> (P, C, V)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3320, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Scrutinise the following for evidence of undisclosed related party transactions (this should include liaison with other departments within the audit firm):</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>third party and counter party confirmations received during the audit;</li>\r\n    <li>analytical procedures;</li>\r\n    <li>invoices / correspondence with legal and other professional advisers;</li>\r\n    <li>tax returns and correspondence with the appropriate taxation authority;</li>\r\n    <li>statutory records;</li>\r\n    <li>information supplied to regulators; </li>\r\n    <li>correspondence with the pension scheme; and</li>\r\n    <li>shareholder and board minutes. <b>(C, E, V)</b> </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3321, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Scrutinise the following for evidence of undisclosed related party transactions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>investments in entities which have not been identified as being related parties (and are not listed investments);</li>\r\n    <li>loans to entities which have not been identified as being related parties;</li>\r\n    <li>guarantees provided, which are on behalf of entities or individuals which have not been identified as being related parties;</li>\r\n    <li>the provision of services which are not part of the normal course of business, or are not on “commercial terms”. <b>(C, E, V)</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3322, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>If tests 19 – 20 identify undisclosed related party transactions, undertake additional procedures as necessary to reduce the risk that there may be further undisclosed related party transactions to an acceptable level. <b> (P)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3323, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>If significant transactions are identified which are outside the entity’s normal course of business:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>inspect the underlying contracts or agreements;</li>\r\n    <li>obtain audit evidence that the transaction has been appropriately authorised and approved. <b>(R&O, C, V, O)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3324, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>If management has made an assertion in the financial statements which indicates that a related party transaction was conducted on an “arm’s length basis”, obtain evidence to confirm that this assertion is correct. <b> (R&O, C, V, P)</b> </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3325, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Where related party transactions are not an “arm’s length” basis, consider whether any transfer pricing issues arise and ensure that adequate consideration is given in the J section of the file.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3326, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>Where related party transactions have been aggregated for disclosure purposes, consider the appropriateness of the aggregation and whether any transaction included in the aggregation should be disclosed separately.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3327, 27, '2.9 K2', '2.9 K2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary:</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:09:56'),
(3328, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Obtain a schedule of provisions, contingent assets, contingent liabilities and financial commitments showing the movement for each provision in the period.  <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3329, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Regarding provisions agree the total shown on the lead schedule to the trial balance. <b>(E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3330, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Regarding provisions agree comparative figures and regarding contingencies comparative disclosures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3331, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Review provisions, contingent assets, contingent liabilities and financial commitments for reasonableness and consistency.<b> (C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3332, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3333, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Discuss with management to ensure all appropriate provisions have been included in the financial statements and that appropriate disclosure has been made of contingent liabilities and contingent assets.  Confirm findings in the letter of representation.  Ensure additional key findings from this section are included on the points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3334, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3335, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Confirm that provisions have only been recognised when:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>an entity has a present obligation as a result of a past event; and</li>\r\n    <li>it is probable that a transfer of economic benefits is required to settle the obligation; and</li>\r\n    <li>a reliable estimate can be made of the amount of the obligation. <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3336, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Confirm that contingent liabilities have been disclosed when:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>an entity has a present obligation as a result of a past event; and</li>\r\n    <li>it is probable that a transfer of economic benefits is required to settle the obligation, however a reliable estimate cannot be made of the amount of the obligation; or</li>\r\n    <li>it is only possible (but not remote) that a transfer of economic benefits is required.<b> (P)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3337, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Confirm that a contingent asset has been disclosed when an inflow as a result of a past event of economic benefit is probable. <b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3338, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Check provisions to supporting documentation ensuring that provisions represents the present value (if the time value of money is material) of the best estimate of the liability. (Specific consideration should be given to the discounting rate applied). <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3339, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Verify expenditure charged against provisions to supporting documentation to confirm that the expenditure is for the purpose for which the provision was originally established. <b>(R&O, A,P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3340, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Where provisions have not been utilised and have been released to the profit or loss section of the Statement of Comprehensive Income, ascertain the reasons why and consider whether this draws into question the reliability of any other provisions.<b> (E, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3341, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Ascertain whether all necessary provisions have been made and contingencies disclosed by considering, for example:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>litigation and claims ;</li>\r\n    <li>deferred tax (see the J Section);</li>\r\n    <li>dilapidations;</li>\r\n    <li>product warranty provisions</li>\r\n    <li>rectification provisions (see the E Section);</li>\r\n    <li>onerous contracts; and</li>\r\n    <li>pension commitments.  <b>(C, P)</b></li>\r\n    <li></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3342, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Review:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>shareholder and board minutes; </li>\r\n    <li>correspondence and invoices received from solicitors;</li>\r\n    <li>correspondence from regulatory authorities; to identify whether there are any ongoing matters which may lead to additional provisions or contingent liabilities. <b> (C)</b></li>\r\n    <li></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3343, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Ensure that specific confirmation is obtained in the letter of representation that all litigation and claims have been notified to the auditors. <b> (C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3344, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Where potential provisions or contingent liabilities have been identified, write to the legal adviser dealing with the matter, setting out a list of known litigation and claims, including management’s assessment of the outcome of each case, and request confirmation that management’s assessment is reasonable, and if there is any further information that the auditor should consider (see Proforma Documents / Appendix 8). <b> (C, R&O, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3345, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Ensure that reimbursements are only recognised when it is virtually certain that they will be received. <b> (V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3346, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Where a provision (other than deferred tax) has been discounted, ensure the unwinding of the provision is appropriately accounted for in the profit or loss section of the Statement of Comprehensive Income as a finance cost. <b> (P, V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3347, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Enquire into the existence of any forward exchange contracts. Where they exist obtain a counterparty valuation and agree them to market valuations such as those that can be obtained via premium subscription.  Ensure that an appropriate liability or asset has been recognised and complete the hedging audit programme where the client has opted to hedge account. <b>(P, E,C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3348, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>Enquire into the existence of non-basic financial instruments (other than forward exchange contracts, non-basic bank loans and interest rate swaps). Where they exist obtain a counterparty valuation and then obtain an expert valuation and complete the relevant tests on the N audit programme.  Ensure that an appropriate liability or asset has been recognised and complete the hedging audit programme where the client has opted to hedge account.  <b>(P, E,C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3349, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>If, during the audit work, there is any suspicion that a document may not be authentic, or has been altered, consider confirming the contents of the document directly with the third party from whom the document originated. <b>(E, R&O, C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3350, 28, '2.10 L2', '2.10 L2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:19:28'),
(3397, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Obtain schedules showing issued share capital, along with all movements in reserves. </p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>Agree all figures to the Statement of Changes in Equity (SOCE).  <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n</ol>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3398, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3399, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention and the permanent audit file is appropriately updated.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3400, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate.  <b>(D)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3401, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p><b>Share Capital</b></p>\r\n<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3402, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Agree allotted share capital to the trial balance and Register of Members. <b>(C, E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3403, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Ensure that all changes in the issued share capital (including the issue of additional shares, repurchase of shares etc.) are properly authorised and correctly accounted for in accordance with legislation. A <b><u>detailed</u></b> supporting working paper should be prepared. <b>(E, C,V)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3404, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Consider whether share capital is correctly reflected as equity or debt. <b>(D)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3405, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p><b>Directors and Secretary</b></p>\r\n<p>Enquire as to whether there have been any changes in directors and / or secretary and agree to the relevant statutory filings. <b> (C, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3406, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p><b>Ultimate Controlling Party</b></p>\r\n<p>Obtain confirmation in the letter of representation that appropriate disclosure has been made of whom the ultimate controlling party is. Review statutory filings to ensure that that it agrees with the disclosure given and assess whether any other information has come to light which draws into question the representations made by the directors. <b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3407, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p><b>Reserves</b></p>\r\n<p>Confirm description of reserves agrees with previous period’s financial statements. <b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c2` (`acID`, `c2tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `desc`, `controleffect`, `implemented`, `assessed`, `yesno`, `comment`, `corptax`, `statutory`, `accountancy`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(3408, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Ensure gains and losses are recognised in the correct statement. <b> (P)</b></p>\r\n<i> \r\n    <p>The following should be recognised directly in reserves:</p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Movements in Share Capital;</li>\r\n        <li>Dividends (actual and deemed);</li>\r\n        <li>Prior period adjustments.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p>The following should be recognised as other comprehensive income:</p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Revaluation gains (and certain losses) on property, plant and equipment;</li>\r\n        <li>Depreciation adjustment regarding revalued property, plant and equipment;</li>\r\n        <li>Revaluation gains on subsidiaries, associates and joint ventures carried at fair value where  the option is taken not to include movements in profit or loss;</li>\r\n        <li>Certain gains and losses on defined benefit pension schemes;</li>\r\n        <li>Movements on cash flow hedges;</li>\r\n        <li>Tax and deferred tax movement relating to the above items.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3409, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Ensure the composition of each reserve can be appropriately identified. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3410, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p><b>Dividends</b></p>\r\n<p>Whilst not mandatory, consider whether dividends are identified and disclosed as ‘actual’ dividends and ‘deemed’ dividends. <b> (P)</b></p>\r\n<i>‘Deemed’ dividends arise on the initial recognition of longer term intercompany / related party loans which do not carry a commercial rate of interest. </i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3411, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Confirm that all dividends (whether actual or ‘deemed’) have only been declared out of distributable profits and are permitted by the entity’s governing documents.<b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3412, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Ensure interim dividends have been paid prior to the period end (or deemed to be paid which usually occurs when they have been formally off-set against a shareholders’ overdrawn loan account, an interim dividend cannot create a creditor) and final dividends have been authorised prior to the period end. <b>(R&O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3413, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Ensure interim dividends have been paid prior to the period end (or deemed to be paid which usually occurs when they have been formally off-set against a shareholders’ overdrawn loan account, <b><u> an interim dividend cannot create a creditor</u></b>) and final dividends have been authorised prior to the period end. <b>(R&O)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3414, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Confirm the calculation of dividends is correct. Ensure that all dividend waivers have been correctly accounted for and that dividends ‘in specie’ have been accounted for based on the book value of the assets transferred.   <b>(C, E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3415, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>For dividends ‘in specie’ where assets have not been transferred proportionally to all shareholders based on their ownership of the company, ensure the fair value of the dividend ‘in specie’ is calculated and disclosed.</p>\r\n<p><i>This will occur when dividend waivers are in place or when there are different classes of shares which are owned by different shareholders or have a different percentage split between the shareholders. </i></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3416, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>Ensure that dividends declared after the reporting date have been identified but not recognised as a liability. These may be presented as a separate component of distributable reserves at the reporting date. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3417, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p><b>Minutes</b></p>\r\n<p><i>Tests on other sections of the file involve the review of minutes of shareholders and directors’ meetings for evidence of additional capital commitments, new loan agreements, additional provisions or contingencies, fraud and error, breaches of law and regulations and undisclosed related party transactions.</i></p>\r\n<p>Ensure that the company’s minutes do not allude to any other issues that are significant to the audit. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3418, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p><b>Statutory Books</b></p>\r\n<p>Verify any changes with the minutes and ensure that, if necessary, the companies’ registry has been notified.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3419, 29, '2.11 M2', '2.11 M2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:28:47'),
(3420, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>In respect of any material accounting estimates from the prior period, review how they have been utilised in the current period to determine their reasonableness.</p>\r\n<i>If this work has been undertaken in other sections of the file a summary schedule should be produced to allow an overall conclusion to be reached.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3421, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Ensure that Appendix 1.7 (Accounting Estimates) has been completed and concluded.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3422, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3423, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p><b>LAW AND REGULATION</b></p>\r\n<p>Obtain details of the law and regulations which:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>are central to the continuing operation of the entity; or</li>\r\n    <li>would lead to a material financial penalty if not complied with; or</li>\r\n    <li>are a contractual or licensing arrangement which is of critical importance to the entity; or</li>\r\n    <li>otherwise could have a material effect on the operation of the entity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Ensure that the permanent file has also been updated with these details.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3424, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Discuss with management procedures for compliance with relevant law and regulations.  Ensure the permanent file has also been updated with these details.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3425, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Review the following for evidence of non-compliance with law and regulations:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>correspondence with legal advisors and regulatory bodies;</li>\r\n    <li>correspondence with government bodies (including taxation authorities);</li>\r\n    <li>shareholder and board minutes; and</li>\r\n    <li>reports commissioned from experts.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3426, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Consider the entity’s knowledge of employment law. Are there procedures in place to adequately consider areas such as the following, where legislation covers the relevant areas:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>data protection, surveillance and privacy at work;</li>\r\n    <li>discrimination (covering age (including retirement); disability, race, religion, sex and sexual orientation);</li>\r\n    <li>discipline and grievance procedures;</li>\r\n    <li>employee status;</li>\r\n    <li>equal pay;</li>\r\n    <li>fixed-term working;</li>\r\n    <li>flexible working, parental rights and family-friendly procedures;</li>\r\n    <li>maternity, paternity, shared parental and adoption leave and pay;</li>\r\n    <li>minimum and living wage;</li>\r\n    <li>part time working;</li>\r\n    <li>recruitment and selection;</li>\r\n    <li>redundancy;</li>\r\n    <li>terms and conditions of employment;</li>\r\n    <li>trade union recognition and industrial action;</li>\r\n    <li>whistleblowing;</li>\r\n    <li>work based pension;</li>\r\n    <li>working time regulations;</li>\r\n    <li>wrongful dismissal; and</li>\r\n    <li>any other employment laws relevant to the entity?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>NB: The above represents a selection of employment law applicable around the world, whereas not all of these will be covered by legislation in each jurisdiction.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3427, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Where necessary, has the entity undertaken a health and safety risk assessment, which is up to date?</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3428, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Where necessary, has the entity undertaken a fire risk assessment, which is up to date?</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3429, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Document all areas of non-compliance, ensure that these have been adequately assessed in the L Section of the file and if appropriate, considered in the going concern review.  <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3430, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3431, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<h6>FRAUD AND ERROR</h6>\r\n<p>Review the following for potential signs of fraud and error (this work might also identify non-compliance with law and regulation or undisclosed related party transactions):</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>investigations by government departments;</li>\r\n    <li>payment of fines or penalties;</li>\r\n    <li>adverse media comment;</li>\r\n    <li>lavish lifestyles or extensive and potentially unnecessary foreign travel by senior management;</li>\r\n    <li>aggressive tax management by the entity whether deemed to be tax evasion or avoidance;</li>\r\n    <li>aggressive earnings management;</li>\r\n    <li>(other than where they represent part of an authorised remuneration package) assets used for private benefit;</li>\r\n    <li>complex group structures, including offshore entities where ownership cannot be identified</li>\r\n    <li>long delays in production of accounting records or financial statements;</li>\r\n    <li>unauthorised transactions or inadequately recorded transactions;</li>\r\n    <li>computer problems or other system problems which mean that an adequate audit trail is not given;</li>\r\n    <li>a poor control environment and lack of segregation of duties;</li>\r\n    <li>management refusal to provide information;</li>\r\n    <li>unusual accounting treatments not in accordance with accounting policies adopted by the entity;</li>\r\n    <li>payments for unspecified services and payments made for goods / services not received / required;</li>\r\n    <li>sales (including the disposal of fixed assets) or purchases at prices significantly above or below the market price;</li>\r\n    <li>payment in cash where this appears to be inappropriate;</li>\r\n    <li>transactions which have no apparent purpose or economic sense;</li>\r\n    <li>unusual related party transactions; </li>\r\n    <li>transactions with tax havens, high-risk and non-cooperative jurisdictions (as categorised by FATF) or third countries where the transaction did not originate;</li>\r\n    <li>sales commissions or agents fees that appear excessive, are undertaken on a split commission basis or are paid before the underlying transaction occurs;</li>\r\n    <li>unexpected balances and reversal of transactions after the period-end; and</li>\r\n    <li>unusual investments of funds</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3432, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>If, during the audit work, there is any suspicion that a document may not be authentic, or has been altered, consider confirming the contents of the document directly with the third party from whom the document originated. <b>(E, R&O, C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3433, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Document all areas of concern, ensure that these have been brought to the attention of the A.E.P. and consider whether these concerns could impact on the audit opinion or whether they draw into question the integrity of senior management and thus whether we should continue to act for the client.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3434, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3435, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Through discussions with the management ensure that all service organisation that process financial information have been identified.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3436, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Ensure that a full list of service organisations used by the entity is noted on the permanent file.  This should include (where appropriate):-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Payroll bureau;</li>\r\n    <li>Outsourced bookkeeper;</li>\r\n    <li>Accountants involved in the production of the financial statements;</li>\r\n    <li>Accountants involved in preparing tax and deferred tax computations;</li>\r\n    <li>Accountants involved in tax compliance work;</li>\r\n    <li>Third parties who hold and distribute stock on behalf of the entity;</li>\r\n    <li>Professional inventory counters;</li>\r\n    <li>Investment custodians; and</li>\r\n    <li>Investment managers.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3437, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Where the service organisation is also the audit practice ensure that adequate consideration has been given to the ethical impact of the non-audit services provided.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3438, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Obtain a copy of the letters of engagement between the entity and the service organisation, and ensure the following are documented and understood:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The terms of the contract;</li>\r\n    <li>The respective responsibilities of the client and the service organisation;</li>\r\n    <li>The respective responsibilities of the client and the service organisation;</li>\r\n    <li>What information is to be provided to and by the service organisation the timeframe for production; and</li>\r\n    <li>There are appropriate indemnity clauses to cover a performance failure by the service organisation.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3439, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Ensure that the service organization is able to provide a continuing service to the client, and that where appropriate contingency plans are in place if it is not possible for the service to continue, for whatever reason (for example, data loss, fire or liquidation).</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3440, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Ensure the permanent file documents the controls that operate regarding the provision of information to, and the receipt of information from, the service organisation (i.e. how is it ensured that accurate information passes between the two entities and that information is transferred by an authorised person).</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3441, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<i>Many service organisation provide a ‘Type 2’ report (as defined in ISA 402). These ‘Type 2’ reports are also sometimes produced by a service organisation’s internal auditors. They include information on the description, design and operating effectiveness of internal controls.  Organisations may alternatively provide a ‘Type 1’ report which cover just the description and design of internal controls. </i>\r\n<p>Review these documents where available and update the PAF regarding the controls operated within the service organisation</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3442, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Review the audit approach regarding the work of service organisations to determine whether any reliance is to be placed on their internal controls or whether a purely substantive approach will be adopted. </p>\r\n<i>For some audit assertions, for example ownership of shares is it unlikely that adequate assurance will be gained via a purely substantive approach.</i>\r\n<p>Update the planning documentation as necessary and where controls are to be relied upon complete tests 25 and 26. </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3443, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Due to client confidentiality it is unlikely that most service organisations will give third party auditors direct access to their accounting systems and controls. Thus it will only be possible to place reliance on a service organisation’s controls through placing reliance on either an internal or external auditors.  Review the Type 2 Report to determine which controls it gives an opinion on, then determine for which audit assertions reliance can be placed.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3444, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Ensure that the tests on this audit programme relating to reliance on another auditor or an internal auditor are completed.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3445, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3446, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p><b>USING THE WORK OF AN EXPERT (ISA 620)</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure that all financial information which has been provided by an expert has been identified, and that the terms of the contract, and the extent of responsibilities of both the client and the expert are understood.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3447, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Assess the competency and independence of the expert (for example, recognised professional qualifications, experience of the expert or membership of a recognised trade or professional body).</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3448, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Review the assumptions used, and the basis on which the expert’s work has been performed to identify any matters which are either inconsistent with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>prior periods, or</li>\r\n    <li>information provided by any counterparty; or</li>\r\n    <li>information provide by other experts; or</li>\r\n    <li>information provided by the client; or </li>\r\n    <li>are inconsistent with the auditor’s general knowledge of the client, or other audit evidence.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3449, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Where the expert’s work involves the use of source data that is significant to the work of the expert, consider the relevance, completeness and accuracy of the source data.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3450, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Ensure that the basis on which the expert’s work has been performed complies with the entity’s accounting policy.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3451, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Ensure that the expert’s work has been performed on a timely basis.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3452, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary to enable the auditor to conclude that the expert’s work provides sufficient, appropriate audit evidence in the area.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3453, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p><b>CONSIDERING THE WORK OF INTERNAL AUDIT (ISA 610)</b></p>\r\n<p>If not already documented on the file, document which auditors we are placing reliance on, whether they are internal or external to the organisation and why we are placing reliance on them.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3454, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Ensure that confirmation has been obtained from the other audit firm that they are independent of the audit client. </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3455, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>For the current year, have we reviewed their working papers and found them to be reliable?  If not when was the last time that we reviewed them and has an appropriate audit questionnaire been sent in the current year?</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3456, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Have any problems with the work of another auditor or internal audit been identified in prior years?</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3457, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Has the work on which we are seeking to rely been performed in accordance with ISA or equivalent guidance (such as a Type 2 Report)?</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3458, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Is the other auditor independent from the entity?</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3459, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>Are there any external quality control procedures?</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3460, 30, '2.12 N2', '2.12 N2', '<p>List and perform any tests considered necessary to comply with the requirements of the above ISA’s.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:39:56'),
(3549, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>) Obtain schedule of revenue <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n    <li>) Ensure that revenue is analysed based on class of business and geographical market.  Ensure the analysis of revenue also separately identifies the following:-\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Income from the sale of goods;</li>\r\n            <li>Income from the rendering of services; and</li>\r\n            <li>Income from undertaking construction contracts. <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ol>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3550, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Agree total shown on the lead schedule to the trial balance. <b>(A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3551, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3552, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Ensure the accounting policies for revenue comply with the requirements of IFRS 15.  <b>(C, A, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3553, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Review revenue for reasonableness and consistency, including any statutory disclosures given. <b>(C, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3554, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3555, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3556, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3557, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Calculate the gross profit percentage, disaggregated as far as possible, and compare to the previous period.  Analyse and verify any unexpected change. <b>(C, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3558, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Consider the results of the scrutiny tests completed in the F section. <b>(CL, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3559, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p><b>Walkthrough</b></p>\r\n<p>Undertake one walkthrough test for each system in operation (this must cover the transaction and associated controls).  Use the results, along with results of receivables’ testing, to decide whether to replace some or all tests of detail with detailed analytical procedures. <b>(A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3560, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p><b>Detailed analytical procedures</b></p>\r\n<p>Perform detailed analytical procedures as applicable to the client.  E.g. proof in total, ratio analysis (comparing periods and similar entities). <b>(C, CL, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3561, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p><b>Tests of detail</b></p>\r\n<p>13.	Trace a sample of items from the ‘point of inception’ (e.g. contract, order, timesheet or dispatch document) through to sales invoices, then to the sales day book and then to the sales ledger and nominal ledger. <b>(O, C, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3562, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>For cash sales, trace a sample of takings from till records (rolls or internal electronic logs) through to cashbook receipts banked.<b>(O, C, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3563, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>For a sample of entries in the sales nominal ledger account agree them back to documents that support their inception.<b>(O, C, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3564, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Where income is contingent on future events (such as “no win no fee scenarios”), review a sample of contracts on a portfolio basis to determine whether the recognition of revenue is appropriate <b>(O, C, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3565, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>For a sample of sales invoices, check </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>selling prices;</li>\r\n    <li>treatment of discounts;</li>\r\n    <li>casts and extensions. <b>(O, C, A)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3566, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Confirm that sales taxes have been excluded from the amount which has been recorded in the sales nominal ledger account. <b>(A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3567, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Check the sales day book casts.  <b>(A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3568, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Where sales credit notes are material, confirm that they are correctly authorised and represent valid credits. <b>(C, A, CO)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3569, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>Check the accuracy of the analysis of revenue noted on the lead schedule by agreeing to nominal ledger analysis and test a sample of entries in the nominal ledger accounts to underlying invoices to confirm appropriate allocation .<b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3570, 31, '2.13.1 O2', '2.13.1 O2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 13:52:48'),
(3590, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p><b>Identifying the contract</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure that the client has appropriately identified the contracts with customers in accordance with IFRS 15.9. </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3591, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>For two or more contracts entered into with the same customer at or near the same time, review whether these should be accounted for as a single contract per IFRS 15.17.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3592, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>Ensure that any contract modifications have been appropriately dealt with.</p>\r\n<i>See IFRS 15.18 – 21 for further detail.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3593, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p><b>Performance obligations See IFRS 15.22 – 45 for further detail.</b></p>\r\n<p>For each contract, ensure that the client has identified the performance obligations.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3594, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>If the performance obligations are settled over time, review the methods used for measuring progress towards satisfaction of those performance obligations and ensure that the revenue is recognised in line with those performance obligations.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3595, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p><b>Determining the transaction price</b></p>\r\n<p>Where there are contracts that include variable consideration, ensure this has been appropriately accounted for.</p>\r\n<i>See IFRS 15.50 – 59 for guidance.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3596, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>Where the entity makes sales with a right of return, ensure that revenue is only recognised for the amount of consideration which the entity expects to be entitled to. </p>\r\n<i>NB: Where consideration is received but the entity does not expect to be entitled to such amounts, this should be recognised as a refund liability.</i>\r\n<i>See IFRS 15.B20 – 27 for guidance</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3597, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>Where the contract has a significant financing component (e.g it is paid for over a period of more than 12 months), ensure that, where material, the promised amount of consideration has been adjusted for the effects of the time value of money.</p>\r\n<i>See IFRS 15, Illustrative examples 26-30 for guidance.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3598, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>If there is any non-cash consideration or consideration payable to the customer, ensure these have been appropriately treated.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3599, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p><b>Allocating the transaction price</b></p>\r\n<p>The transaction price should be allocated to each performance obligation on a relative stand-alone selling price basis unless:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A discount is received by the customer for purchasing a bundle of goods or services; or</li>\r\n    <li>There is variable consideration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Ensure that discounts and variable consideration have been treated appropriately.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3600, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p><b>Recognising the revenue</b></p>\r\n<p>Revenue should be recognised in accordance with the satisfaction of the performance obligations in the contract. </p>\r\n<p>However, if a contract does not meet the criteria of IFRS 15.9, ensure that revenue has only been recognised when either:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The entity has no remaining obligations to transfer goods or services to the customer and all, or substantially all, of the consideration promised by the customer has been received by the entity and is non-refundable; or</li>\r\n    <li>The contract has been terminated and the consideration received from the customer is non-refundable.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3601, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p><b>Contract costs</b></p>\r\n<p>12.	Ensure that incremental costs of obtaining a contract have only been recognised as an asset if the entity expects to recover those costs.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3602, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>Ensure that costs incurred to fulfil a contract are only recognised as an asset if:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The costs relate directly to a contract (see IFRS 15.97) that can be specifically identified;</li>\r\n    <li>The costs generate or enhance resources of the entity that will be used in satisfying performance obligations in the future; and</li>\r\n    <li>The costs are expected to be recovered. </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3603, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p> IFRS 15 is applied using one of the following two methods: </p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>) The “retrospective” method: apply the Standard retrospectively to each prior reporting period presented in accordance with IAS 8 <i>Accounting i Policies, Changes in Accounting Estimates and Errors</i> , subject to the expedients in paragraph IFRS 15.C5; or</li>\r\n    <li>) The “cumulative effect” method: retrospectively with the cumulative effect of initially applying IFRS 15 recognised as an adjustment to the opening balance of retained earnings (or other component of equity, as appropriate) of the annual reporting period that includes the date of initial application. The entity may elect to apply IFRS 15 retrospectively only to contracts that are not completed contracts at the date of initial application.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><i>The date of initial application is the start of the reporting period in which an entity first applies this Standard (i.e. 1 January 2018 for a 31 December 2018 year end);</i></p>\r\n<p><b>Confirm which transition method is being used:</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3604, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>Ensure that the transition to IFRS 15 has been appropriately dealt with in accordance with Appendix C of IFRS 15.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3605, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>Ensure that any practical expedients taken advantage of (as set out in Appendix C of IFRS 15) have been appropriately applied.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3606, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>Obtain a reconciliation that shows the impact of first-time adoption of IFRS 15. This should include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Narrative explanation of how the first-time adoption has been treated (i.e. full retrospective application or the “cumulative effect” approach);</li>\r\n    <li>Narrative explanation of the changes made on first time adoption (e.g. accounting for refund liabilities);</li>\r\n    <li><b><u>If the retrospective method has been used: </u></b>\r\n        <p>For the preceding period, an analysis of each line item in the financial statements affected by the change, showing:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The figure as originally stated under IAS 18/ IAS 11;</li>\r\n            <li>Any reclassification adjustments made (e.g. showing contract assets separately);</li>\r\n            <li>Any remeasurement changes from applying the IFRS 15 requirements;</li>\r\n            <li>The restated figure under IFRS 15.</li> \r\n            <li>The restated figure under IFRS 15.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n        <p><i>(NB: IFRS 15.C4 states that the entity is only required to give this disclosure for the comparative period, but may wish to do so for earlier periods and/or the current period)</i></p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li><b><u>If the cumulative effect method has been used: </u></b>\r\n        <p>For the current period, an analysis of the amount by which each financial statement line item is affected by the application of this IFRS 15 as compared to IAS 11, IAS 18 and related Interpretations that were in effect before the change; and an explanation of the reasons for the significant changes. </p>\r\n        <p>A reconciliation of opening retained earnings should be also be obtained.  </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3607, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>Obtain a breakdown of revenue disaggregated into categories that depict how the nature, amount, timing and uncertainty if revenue and cash flows are affected by economic factors. </p>\r\n<p>These categories may include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>type of good or service (for example, major product lines);</li>\r\n    <li>geographical region (for example, country or region);</li>\r\n    <li>market or type of customer (for example, government and non-government customers);</li>\r\n    <li>type of contract (for example, fixed-price and time-and-materials contracts);</li>\r\n    <li>contract duration (for example, short-term and long-term contracts);</li>\r\n    <li>timing of transfer of goods or services (for example, revenue from goods or services transferred to customers at a point in time and revenue from goods or services transferred over time); and</li>\r\n    <li>sales channels (for example, goods sold directly to consumers and goods sold through intermediaries)</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3608, 32, '2.13.2 O2-1', '2.13.2 O2-1', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:08:25'),
(3609, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Obtain a lead schedule for direct costs. <b>(P) </b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3610, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Agree total shown on the direct costs lead schedules to the trial balance. <b> (A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3611, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements.<b>  (P, C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3612, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Consider the appropriateness of the allocation of expenditure between direct costs and other expenses. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3613, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Review direct costs for reasonableness and consistency.<b> (P, C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3614, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3615, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3616, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3617, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Consider the results of the scrutiny tests completed in the I section. <b>(CL, A, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3618, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p><b>Walkthrough</b></p>\r\n<p>10.	Undertake one walkthrough test for each system in operation (this must cover the transaction and associated controls).  Use the results, along with results of payables testing, to decide whether to replace some or all tests of detail with detailed analytical procedures. <b>(A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3619, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p><b>Detailed analytical procedures</b></p>\r\n<p>Perform detailed analytical procedures as applicable to the client.  E.g. proof in total, ratio analysis (comparing periods and similar entities). <b>(C, CL, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3620, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p><b>Tests of detail</b></p><p>Trace a sample of purchases from the nominal ledger to the purchase ledger, the purchase day book and then to supporting documentation. <b>(O, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3621, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>For a sample of purchase invoices, check:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>quantities purchased to orders and goods received notes;</li>\r\n    <li>prices invoiced to any agreements;</li>\r\n    <li>casts and extensions. <b> (O, A)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3622, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>For a sample of purchases from originating documents (orders, contracts etc.) agree, where applicable to</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>goods received note;</li>\r\n    <li>purchase invoice;</li>\r\n    <li>purchase day book;</li>\r\n    <li>purchase ledger; and</li>\r\n    <li>nominal ledger. <b> (O, C, A)</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>This test can be combined with the test on the R programme when all purchases are processed in the same way.</i></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3623, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Check the purchase day book casts.<b> (A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3624, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>Where a material amount of goods or services are returned, ensure the corresponding credit notes are received and recognised in the financial statements. <b>(C, A, CO)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42'),
(3625, 33, '2.14 P2', '2.14 P2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:15:42');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c2` (`acID`, `c2tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `desc`, `controleffect`, `implemented`, `assessed`, `yesno`, `comment`, `corptax`, `statutory`, `accountancy`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(3626, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p><b>General</b></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>) Obtain a schedule of other operating income and gains. <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n    <li>) Ensure that other operating income and gains are analysed into the following categories: \r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Interest;</li>\r\n            <li>Royalties;</li>\r\n            <li>Dividends split between:\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>Income from shares in group undertakings</li>\r\n                    <li>Income from participating interests</li>\r\n                    <li>Income from other fixed asset investments.</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>Commissions;</li>\r\n            <li>Grants received;</li>\r\n            <li>Any of types of significant revenue streams appropriately described. <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ol>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3627, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Ensure that a schedule is prepared which separately shows income and gains recognised in profit or loss which relate to financial instruments, split between:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Financial assets measured at fair value through profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Financial liabilities measured at fair value through profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Financial assets measured on an amortised cost basis; and </li>\r\n    <li>Financial liabilities measured on an amortised cost basis.  <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3628, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Agree totals shown on the other income and gains lead schedule to the trial balance. <b>(A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3629, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Agree comparative to the previous period’s statutory financial statements. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3630, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Ensure that all items are correctly recognised in profit or loss rather than other comprehensive income. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3631, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3632, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3633, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate. <b>(D)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3634, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Consider the results of the scrutiny tests completed in the F section. <b>(CL, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3635, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p><b>Walkthrough</b></p>\r\n<p>Undertake one walkthrough test for each system in operation (this must cover the transaction and associated controls).  Use the results, along with results obtained in other sections of the audit file, to decide whether to replace some or all tests of detail with detailed analytical procedures. <strong>(A)</strong></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3636, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p><b>Detailed analytical procedures</b></p>\r\n<p>Perform detailed analytical procedures as applicable to the client.  E.g. proof in total, ratio analysis (comparing periods and similar entities). <b>(C, CL, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3637, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p><b>Tests of detail</b></p>\r\n<p>Verify any items of other income above performance materiality (either individually or in aggregate) shown in the nominal ledger to supporting documentation.<b> (C, A)</b></p>\r\n<i>Ensure this work does not duplicate work already undertaken on other sections of the audit file particularly debtors and creditors.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3638, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>For all known sources of other operating income undertake tests to confirm the completeness of each source of income above performance materiality (either individually or in aggregate). <b> (C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3639, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Ensure non-monetary government grants are recognised at either fair value or a nominal amount. <b> (A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3640, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Review the operations of the entity and consider whether all sources of other operating income have been identified and correctly accounted for, including:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Sales of scrap production material and production by-products;</li>\r\n    <li>Sales to staff;</li>\r\n    <li>Contributions by staff towards subsistence costs;</li>\r\n    <li>Income from vending machines;</li>\r\n    <li>Sales of obsolete items of property, plant and equipment and inventories. <b>(C)</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>Ensure that, where relevant, sales tax and duty has been correctly accounted for on these items</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3641, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>Review financial assets to ensure that all which are recoverable after more than 12 months from the reporting date and do not carry a commercial rate of interest have been accounted for on an amortised cost basis and that the unwinding of the discount has been appropriately accounted for as income in profit or loss.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3642, 34, '2.15 Q2', '2.15 Q2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:23:58'),
(3643, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Obtain schedules for other expenditure and losses which include lead schedules for:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Distribution costs;</li>\r\n    <li>Administrative expenses;</li>\r\n    <li>Interest payable and similar charges. <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3644, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Ensure a schedule is prepared which separately shows expenses and losses recognised in profit or loss relating to financial instruments, split between:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Financial assets measured at fair value through profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Financial liabilities measured at fair value through profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Financial assets measured on an amortised cost basis; and </li>\r\n    <li>Financial liabilities measured on an amortised cost basis. <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3645, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Agree the totals shown on the lead schedules to the trial balance. <b>(A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3646, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements.<b> (P, C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3647, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Ensure that all items are correctly recognised in profit or loss rather than other comprehensive income.<b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3648, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Consider the appropriateness of the allocation of expenditure between the expense classifications noted above and also direct costs. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3649, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Review other expenses for reasonableness and consistency. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3650, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3651, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3652, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Ensure that the conclusion is appropriate.<b> (P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3653, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Consider the results of the scrutiny tests completed in the I section. <b>(CL, A, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3654, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p><b>Walkthrough</b></p>\r\n<p>Undertake one walkthrough test for each system in operation (this must cover the transaction and associated controls).  Use the results, along with results of payables testing, to decide whether to replace some or all tests of detail with detailed analytical procedures. <b>(A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3655, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p><b>Detailed analytical procedures</b></p>\r\n<p>Perform detailed analytical procedures as applicable to the client.  E.g. proof in total, ratio analysis (comparing periods and similar entities). <b>(C, CL, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3656, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p><b>Tests of detail</b></p><p>Trace a sample of expenses from the nominal ledger (covering, administration, distribution and finance related costs) to either:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the purchase ledger and the purchase day book; or</li>\r\n    <li>cash book; or</li>\r\n    <li>journal book; and</li>\r\n    <li>then to supporting documentation. <b> (O, A)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3657, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>For a sample of purchases trace from originating documents (orders, contracts etc.) and agree, where applicable to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>goods received note;</li>\r\n    <li>purchase invoice;</li>\r\n    <li>purchase day book;</li>\r\n    <li>purchase ledger; and</li>\r\n    <li>nominal ledger. <b>(O, C, A) </b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>This test can be combined with the test on the P programme when all purchases are processed in the same way</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3658, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Where a material amount of goods or services are returned, ensure the corresponding credit notes are received and recognised in the financial statements. <b>(C, A, CO)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3659, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>Review financial liabilities to ensure that all which are recoverable after more than 12 months and do not carry a commercial rate of interest have been accounted for on an amortised cost basis and that the unwinding of the discount has been appropriately accounted for as an expense in profit or loss.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3660, 35, '2.16 R2-1', '2.16 R2-1', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:31:25'),
(3661, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p><b>General</b></p>\r\n<p>Obtain a schedule showing gross payroll, social security, and pension contributions split by category of employee, including directors.  <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3662, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Agree totals shown on the above schedule to the trial balance. <b>(E)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3663, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Obtain a schedule showing average employee numbers based on an average of the absolute number of contracts of employment in place each month.  This schedule should analyse employee numbers based on their role (e.g. sales, marketing, production, administration etc.).</p>\r\n<i>NB: Where applicable, ensure these figures agree with those used to determine the company’s ‘size’.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3664, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Agree comparatives for payroll costs and employee numbers to the previous period’s statutory financial statement. <b>(C, P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3665, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Review payroll and salaries by category for reasonableness and consistency. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3666, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3667, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3668, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Scrutinise the payroll records for any unusual items.  <b>(A & CO)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3669, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Obtain the net pay control account and ensure it represents the final period’s net pay due to employees by agreeing to payroll records and agree the balance to after date payment. <b>(CO)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3670, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Obtain the payroll deductions control account and ensure it represents the final period’s amount due to the appropriate taxation authority by agreeing to payroll records and to after date payment.<b> (CO)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3671, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p><b>Holiday pay accrual </b></p>\r\n<p>Obtain a holiday pay accrual schedule and ensure that where appropriate a holiday pay accrual has been calculated for a sample of employees, the schedule is arithmetically correct, details of entitlement to holidays have been agreed to contracts of employment or the entity’s Personnel Manual, details of holidays taken have been agreed to the entity’s holiday records, and the number of days accrued represents either a legal or constructive obligation. <b>(E, CO)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3672, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p><b>Directors’ emoluments <i>(where applicable)</i> </b></p>\r\n<p>Obtain a schedule that documents total directors’ emoluments and the number of directors who are accruing benefits under defined contribution schemes. Ensure that total emoluments include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Salary and bonuses,</li>\r\n    <li>Employers’ contributions to defined contribution pension schemes; </li>\r\n    <li>Gains made on share options (but not the value of options granted); and </li>\r\n    <li>Benefits in Kind.  <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3673, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Check that directors’ salaries (including bonuses) are authorised and correctly calculated.  <b>(A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3674, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Check that pension contributions made in respect of directors to defined contribution schemes are authorised and correctly calculated. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3675, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Review declarations of benefits and ensure all directors’ benefits have been fully identified and quantified. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3676, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p><b>Key Management Personnel (KMP) compensation</b></p>\r\n<p>16.	Obtain a schedule that documents KMP compensation. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3677, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Review the definition of key management and assess whether the entity has identified the correct persons to include as KMP. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3678, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Ensure that KMP compensation has been correctly calculated. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3679, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>For KMP who are not directors undertake tests 13 to 15. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3680, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Undertake one walkthrough test for each system in operation (this must cover the transaction and associated controls). Use the results to decide whether to replace some or all tests of detail with detailed analytical procedures.<b> (A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3681, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p><b>Detailed analytical procedures</b></p>\r\n<p>Perform detailed analytical procedures as applicable to the client.  E.g. average salary per category, ratio of salaries to social security, proof in total and trend analysis. <b>(C, CL, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3682, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p><b>Tests of detail</b></p>\r\n<p>For a sample of employees, check:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>their existence;</li>\r\n    <li>gross pay with reference to contracts, pay review letters, clock cards, timesheets, etc.; </li>\r\n    <li>deduction calculations;</li>\r\n    <li>net pay to cash book or electronic payments; and</li>\r\n    <li>inclusion on the payroll summary.  <b>(O, C, A)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3683, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Check that payroll and payroll summaries are correctly posted to the nominal ledger. <b> (O, C, A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3684, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Review payroll to ensure joiners and leavers have been correctly treated. <b> (A)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3685, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Check the accuracy of the employee number disclosures.  Ensure that figures have not been produced on a full time equivalent basis. For a sample of employees ensure their classification is appropriate by reference to supporting documentation, such as: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Job descriptions;</li>\r\n    <li>Personnel files;</li>\r\n    <li>Management schedules.  <b>(P)</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3686, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Where the entity contracts with self-employed persons who are not treated as employees consider whether this treatment in justified. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3687, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Where applicable, check that any pension enrolment legislation has been appropriately complied with <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3688, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>Check that any additional amounts payable have been correctly accounted for on benefits. <b>(C)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3689, 36, '2.17 R2-2', '2.17 R2-2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary:</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:49:35'),
(3690, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p><b>General Issues:</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure that where the client operates in multiple currencies, those charged with governance have justified what the entity’s functional currency is.  This should also be confirmed in the letter of representation.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3691, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p><b>Directors’ Report:</b></p>\r\n<p>Obtain a copy of the draft directors’ report as early as possible in the audit process. </p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>) Review it for consistency with the rest of the annual report and financial statements;</li>\r\n    <li>) Review it for accordance with applicable legal requirements;</li>\r\n    <li>) Review for any material misstatements in light of the firm’s knowledge and understanding of the company.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Where necessary consider the impact on the firm’s audit opinion. Ensure that any weaknesses (which are not subsequently addressed) are communicated to the client in the management letter.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3692, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Ensure that information disclosed regarding the company’s financial risk management strategy and the use of financial instruments is in line with the auditor’s understanding and is consistent with the information in the rest of the audit file.  Also, ensure that the management has appropriately identified its exposure to the following risks:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Price risk;</li>\r\n    <li>Credit risk;</li>\r\n    <li>Liquidity risk; and</li>\r\n    <li>Cash flow risk.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3693, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p><b>Performance Statement(s) ~ Exceptional Items</b></p>\r\n<p>Review any items the client has identified as exceptional to confirm they merit separate disclosure due to their size or incidence.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3694, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Review analytical procedures schedules in the O, P, Q and R sections of the file and those filed at Ac9 for other items which may be exceptional. If items exist, document the reason for disclosing/not disclosing them separately.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3695, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p><b>Performance Statement(s) ~ Discontinued Operations</b></p>\r\n<p>Discuss with management whether any activities ceased during the period and particularly just before the period end. Where material activities did cease during the period consider whether they represent a discontinued operation. </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3696, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Review analytical procedures schedules in the O, P, Q and R sections of the file and also filed at those at Ac9 for significant changes in operations and consider whether they should be classified as discontinued.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3697, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Ensure that ‘discontinued operations’ are disclosed as a single figure on the face of the Statement of Comprehensive Income.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3698, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Ensure all assets held for sale are presented in a separate disposal group on the face of the Statement of Financial Position.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3699, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Ensure the following items have been identified their completeness and validity have been verified:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Foreign exchange gains or losses (other than those relating to assets or liabilities recognised at fair value through profit or loss);</li>\r\n    <li>Auditor’s remuneration (where applicable).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3700, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p><b>Performance Statement(s) ~ Other Comprehensive Income</b></p>\r\n<p>11.	Obtain or prepare a schedule of all gains and loss that have been recognised in other comprehensive income.  Ensure that none of these items should have been recognised in profit or loss or directly in equity.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3701, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p><b>Statement of Financial Performance Notes</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure that a schedule is produced which shows the total (as opposed to the annual) operating lease commitment, analysed between those payable:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Not later than one year;</li>\r\n    <li>Later than one year but not later than five years;</li>\r\n    <li>Later than five years.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3702, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Ensure that the ageing of receivables which are past due but not subject to impairment have been identified.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3703, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p><b>Statement of Financial Performance Notes</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure that financial instruments are appropriately classified as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Financial assets and financial liabilities at fair value through profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Held to maturity investments;</li>\r\n    <li>Loans and receivables;</li>\r\n    <li>Available-for-sale financial assets and financial liabilities other than those at fair value through profit or loss</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3704, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p><b>Statement of Cash Flows </b> <i>(Note that it is necessary for every entity applying IFRS to prepare a Statement of Cash Flows)</i></p>\r\n<p>Discuss with the client which assets in their view meet the definition of ‘cash and cash equivalents’ and whether overdrafts are viewed as ‘cash equivalents’.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3705, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Documentation on the permanent file should ensure that a consistent accounting treatment is adopted each period for items such as:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Bank overdrafts (as noted above);</li>\r\n    <li>Taxation;</li>\r\n    <li>Interest receivable;</li>\r\n    <li>Interest payable;</li>\r\n    <li>Dividends receivable; and </li>\r\n    <li>Dividends payable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>NB:  This does not mean for example, that all taxation cash flows must be allocated to the same cash flow heading. However, it would be inappropriate to classify a taxation cash flow relating to the same underlying transaction in a different classification from prior periods (unless the treatment could be justified).</i></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3706, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Obtain from the client their draft statement of cash flows, ensuring that based on the nature of the transactions and the client’s policies as reviewed at test 16, that cash flows have been appropriately classified as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Operating;</li>\r\n    <li>Investing; and </li>\r\n    <li>Financing.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3707, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Review the reconciliation between profit or loss and cash flow from operating activities. Specifically, ensure that all changes in receivables and payables relate solely to operating activities rather than the sale and purchase of investments, property, plant and equipment etc. and that non cash transactions have been eliminated.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3708, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Ensure that all cash flows have been recognised on a gross basis.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3709, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p><b>Other</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure that, where an auditor’s limitation of liability agreement is in place, adequate disclosure is made.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3710, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Review the accounting policies and estimation techniques adopted to ensure that there is an appropriate policy for all material items.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3711, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Ensure that the accounting policies and estimation techniques adopted are the most appropriate to the entity’s circumstances, and that the wording of the accounting policies is appropriate.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3712, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Ensure that the directors have prepared adequate sensitivity analysis to address the sensitivity in the carrying values of items that involve sources of estimation uncertainty.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3713, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Ensure that the directors have undertaken a review of changes to IFRS that have not yet come into force and that an appropriate note has been included in the financial statements of their impact. This disclosure should be commensurate with the level of the impact.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3714, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Revisit the risk assessment, materiality calculation and assignment plan and update as appropriate where matters have been identified during the assignment.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3715, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>Ensure key findings from this section are included in the draft letter of representation, points for the management letter and points for A.E.P.’s attention.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3716, 37, '2.18.1 S2-1', '2.18.1 S2-1', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 14:58:44'),
(3717, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p>Does the permanent file include relevant information on the scheme, including copies of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The Scheme Rules;</li>\r\n    <li>The Trust Deed;</li>\r\n    <li>Scheme Financial Statements;</li>\r\n    <li>Actuarial valuations;</li>\r\n    <li>The letter of engagement between the entity and the actuary regarding the valuation; and</li>\r\n    <li>Details of how the actuary assures themselves the information they use is relevant?</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3718, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p>Does the assignment plan at Ac14 document the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The audit team has adequate knowledge;</li>\r\n    <li>The type of scheme;</li>\r\n    <li>The types of audit evidence to be obtained to support the pension scheme assets and actuarial liabilities;</li>\r\n    <li>The timetable agreed between the actuary and pension scheme auditors?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3719, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p>Has the pension scheme asset / liability been excluded from the main materiality assessment and a separate materiality assessment made for that balance?</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3720, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p>Has a risk assessment been carried out on the pension asset / liability and associated transactions (a short narrative assessment is probably appropriate)?</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3721, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p><i>if the scheme is audited by the same A.E.P. as the entity,</i>I has a memo been prepared noting the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>That the A.E.P. is the same for both the scheme and client;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether the scheme’s audit report was qualified or not; </li>\r\n    <li>That the subsequent event review on the scheme has been updated to the date of the client’s audit report;</li>\r\n    <li>A synopsis of key issues; and</li>\r\n    <li>A review of the pension scheme materiality and client materiality regarding the pension scheme asset / liability?</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3722, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p><i>If the scheme has been audited by the same firm but not the same A.E.P. as the client</i>, has a memo been prepared noting the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>That the A.E.P. is not the same for both the scheme and client;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether the scheme’s audit report was qualified or not; </li>\r\n    <li>That the subsequent event review on the scheme has been updated to the date of the client’s audit report;</li>\r\n    <li>A synopsis of key issues and details of the extent to which the A.E.P. has reviewed the pension scheme file; and</li>\r\n    <li>A review of the pension scheme materiality and the client materiality regarding the pension scheme asset / liability?</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3723, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p><i>If the scheme is audited by a different firm of auditors:</i></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The scheme auditor’s working papers should preferably be reviewed annually to establish the quality of the work; alternatively if this is not possible:</li>\r\n    <li>The working papers should be reviewed every few years to assess quality and send out a questionnaire in the interim years.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3724, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p><i>If the client and pension scheme period ends are not co-terminus:</i></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Have either interim audited financial statements been obtained or has adequate audit evidence been obtained for significant movements in the pension scheme asset / liability from the reporting date of the scheme to the reporting date of the client?</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3725, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p><i>Review of the actuarial liability:</i></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Has the objectivity and independence of the actuary been assessed;</li>\r\n    <li>Have the terms of engagement been reviewed for any potential limitation of scope;</li>\r\n    <li>Is the actuary a member of a recognised professional body of actuaries.</li>\r\n    <li>Has the actuary been informed in writing that their work is going to be used as audit evidence?</li>\r\n    <li>Have historic changes in actuarial assumptions been reviewed and has there been a history of errors (i.e. inappropriate mortality rates would be an error, whereas, changing mortality rates as a result of mortality tables being updated would not be)?</li>\r\n    <li>Have the following key assumptions been reviewed:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Mortality rates (appropriateness to the scheme);</li>\r\n            <li>Inflation (in light of government statistics);</li>\r\n            <li>Rate of wage increase (using historic rises and the client’s budgets);</li>\r\n            <li>Rate of pension increase (in relation to any indexation requirements in the scheme rules); and</li>\r\n            <li>Rate of discounting (is it based on a good quality corporate bond rate?).</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>If a wide range of options has been provided to those charged with governance ensure that flexing has been appropriately undertaken.</li>\r\n    <li>Review the source data used by the actuary and note the controls the actuary uses to ensure that it is accurate. The following constitute key data:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Membership statistics</li>\r\n            <li>Ages of members</li>\r\n            <li>Length of service</li>\r\n            <li>Gender</li>\r\n            <li>Salaries</li>\r\n            <li>Earnings history</li>\r\n            <li>Employee contributions etc.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3726, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p><i>Consider the reasonableness of and re-calculate the figures provided by the actuary:</i></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Agree the level of contributions to the scheme’s financial statements and schedule of contributions</li>\r\n    <li>Review current service costs recognised in profit or loss in light of previous periods and changes in payroll</li>\r\n    <li>Past service costs / curtailments etc. recognised in profit or loss.  Review the scheme’s documentation to get an understanding of what has occurred</li>\r\n    <li>Check the calculation of the net interest charge. This can be done by apply the discounting rate to the brought forward net pension scheme asset (whether recognised or not) / liability and to the contributions received during the period and the benefits paid out during the period;</li>\r\n    <li>The re-measurement of the net pension scheme liability or asset to fair value in other comprehensive income, the main elements to be understood will be:-\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Actuarial gains and losses;</li>\r\n            <li>The difference between the actual return on scheme assets and crudely the brought forward value of assets multiplied by the discounting rate; and</li>\r\n            <li>Changes resulting from the level of recoverability of a net scheme asset.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3727, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p>Consider the impact of accounting for the defined benefit pensions scheme liabilities on:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The client’s going concern status; and</li>\r\n    <li>(If a company) the legality of distributions.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3728, 38, '2.18.2 S2-2', '2.18.2 S2-2', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:08:07'),
(3729, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>Confirm the nature of the share-based payment plan in place:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Equity-settled;</li>\r\n    <li>Cash-settled; or Compound agreement where there is a choice of settlement (these are treated as either cash-settled or equity-settled depending on specific conditions).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Update the PAF as appropriate.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3730, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>Obtain the details of the share-based payment plan to ascertain its major terms, including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The grant date and vesting date of the options;</li>\r\n    <li>The number of share options awarded to each recipient;</li>\r\n    <li>The number of share options awarded to each recipient;</li>\r\n    <li>The fair value of the share options at the grant date;</li>\r\n    <li>The exercise price of the share options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>Typically there should be a share options award document issued to the recipients confirming the terms attached to the options which have been granted.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3731, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>Ascertain the process used to estimate the fair value of the share options:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Which option pricing model has been used?</li>\r\n    <li>How were the inputs into the pricing model determined?</li>\r\n    <li>Was an expert involved in performing the estimate of the fair value of the options?</li>\r\n    <li>For a non-listed entity, how has the value been estimated?</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3732, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>Obtain schedules from the client: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Agree comparative figures to the previous period’s statutory financial statements; </li>\r\n    <li>Cast the movements;</li>\r\n    <li>Check balances disclosed in the financial statements agree to supporting schedules.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3733, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>Obtain supporting documentation to gain assurance over the movements for the period:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Agree grants in the period to grant offer letters;</li>\r\n    <li>Agree exercises to share certificates;</li>\r\n    <li>Agree forfeits / cancellations to leavers documentation or other supporting information;</li>\r\n    <li>Confirm any other movements to relevant documentation.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3734, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>Review the calculations of the fair value of the equity instruments granted (i.e. review the valuation method used): </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Have the following key inputs been reviewed for their reasonableness:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Weighted average share price;</li>\r\n            <li>Exercise price;</li>\r\n            <li>Dividend yield;</li>\r\n            <li>Volatility rates;</li>\r\n            <li>Expected life of the options;</li>\r\n            <li>Interest rate.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>Has the appropriateness of the option pricing model itself been considered?</li>\r\n    <li>Have the inputs to the model been assessed against those of similar entities? Has a benchmarking study been undertaken?</li>\r\n    <li>Where an expert has been engaged to calculate the value of the options on behalf of the client, have they been assessed as being competent and holding the necessary qualifications and expertise to perform the calculations? <i>The appropriate tests on the N Audit Programme should be completed.</i></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>NB: If the transaction relates to the provision of goods or services for which the fair value is estimated, then review the fair value calculation of those goods and services received.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3735, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>Scrutinise the option plan document to determine whether there are vesting conditions and / or market conditions or non-market conditions attached to the options.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>For Market conditions, ensure that these are taken into account when estimating the fair value of the options at the date of grant ONLY, with no subsequent adjustments made at each reporting date; </li>\r\n    <li>For non-market conditions and / or vesting conditions, ensure that these are taken into account at each reporting date such that the fair value of the options granted is updated at each reporting date to reflect the estimated number of options expected to vest </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c2` (`acID`, `c2tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `desc`, `controleffect`, `implemented`, `assessed`, `yesno`, `comment`, `corptax`, `statutory`, `accountancy`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(3736, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>If there are modifications to the terms of the option plan:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>If the modification is beneficial to the employee (e.g. a reduction in the exercise price) and therefore increases the fair value of the options granted, ensure that the incremental fair value is recognised over the remaining vesting period;</li>\r\n    <li>If the modification is not beneficial to the employee, or the fair value is reduced, ensure that there is no change to the original estimate.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3737, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>If options are cancelled or settled early, these should be treated as an acceleration of vesting.  Ensure the expenses that would have been recognised over the remaining vesting period have been recognised immediately.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3738, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>If options are cancelled or settled early, these should be treated as an acceleration of vesting.  Ensure the expenses that would have been recognised over the remaining vesting period have been recognised immediately.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3739, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p><b>Cash-settled share-based payments</b></p>\r\n<p><i>The goods and services received under cash-settled share-based payment plans should be recognised at the fair value of the liability.  The liability should be remeasured at each reporting date until it is discharged with any changes in measurement passing through the profit or loss section of the Statement of Comprehensive Income for the period.</i></p>\r\n<p>Review the fair value calculation of the liability for reasonableness.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3740, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p><b>Group plans</b></p>\r\n<p><i>If a share-based payment award is granted by an entity to employees of another member of the group, there is an option for the expense of the share-based payment recognised to be based on a reasonable allocation of the expense for the group.</i></p>\r\n<p>In the event that this option has been taken, review the reasonableness of the allocation of the expense and document that the basis for the allocation. </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3741, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p><b>RECOGNITION</b></p>\r\n<p><i>The goods or services received under a share-based payment transaction should be recognised as they are received.  A corresponding increase in equity (if an equity-settled share-based payment) or liabilities (if a cash-settled share-based payment transaction) should also be recognised.</i></p>\r\n<p>If the share options granted vest immediately, there is no requirement for the completion of a specified service period before becoming entitled to the share-based payments.    Therefore ensure that the expense (or asset) has been recognised in full at the date of grant, with a corresponding increase in equity or liabilities (depending on the nature of the plan).</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3742, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>If the share options granted vest over a service period, then the services received are deemed to be received over that service period.  Therefore ensure that the expense is being allocated over the service period.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3743, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p><b>ACCOUNTING TREATMENT</b></p>\r\n<p><b>Equity-settled share-based payments</b></p>\r\n<p>Profit or loss – the charge through the profit or loss section of the Statement of Comprehensive Income for the period should be calculated as the fair value of the options granted spread over the vesting period.</p>\r\n<i>(e.g. 1,000 options granted in the year with a fair value per option of CU3 each. The options have a 4 year vesting period therefore the charge for the year is (1,000 x CU3)/4 =CU750).</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3744, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>Reserves - there should be a corresponding increase in equity, passing straight through to the Retained Earnings Reserve or a Share-Based Payment Reserve.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3745, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p><b>Cash-settled share-based payments</b></p>\r\n<p>Profit or loss – the charge through the profit or loss section of the Statement of Comprehensive Income for the period should be calculated as the change in the fair value of the liability that is due to be settled.</p>\r\n<i>NB: the corresponding entry goes to liabilities. </i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3746, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p><b>Disclosure requirements</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure that adequate disclosures are presented in the financial statements by reference to the Supplementary Disclosure checklist.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3747, 39, '2.18.3 S2-3', '2.18.3 S2-3', '<p>List and perform any additional tests considered necessary.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:17:00'),
(3748, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Confirm that <b>hedge accounting</b> has been adopted by the client. </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3749, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Confirm the accounting policy choice made by the client in accounting for financial instruments:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The recognition and measurement criteria of IAS 39; or</li>\r\n    <li>The recognition and measurement criteria of IFRS 9.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3750, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Obtain details of the hedged item and the hedging instrument. </p>\r\n<p><i>A  <b>hedged item</b> can be a recognised asset or liability, an unrecognised firm commitment, a highly probable forecast transaction or a net investment in a foreign operation, or a component of any such item, provided the item is reliably measurable.</i></p>\r\n<p>Only contracts with a party external to the reporting entity (i.e. external to the group or individual entity that is being reported on) can be designated as .<i>hedging instruments</i></p>\r\n<p> Most hedging instruments are derivatives measured at fair value through profit or loss.  Some written options, as described in paragraph B6.2.4, cannot be hedging instruments. Certain other financial assets/liabilities can be designated as hedging instruments – see IFRS 9.6.2.2</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3751, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Consider whether all of the qualifying criteria have been met in order for hedge accounting to be applied:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The hedging relationship only consists of eligible hedging instruments and eligible hedged items;</li>\r\n    <li>At inception of the relationship, there is formal designation and documentation of the hedging relationship and the entity’s risk management objective and strategy for undertaking the hedge (see test below); </li>\r\n    <li>There is an economic relationship between the hedged item and the hedging instrument;</li>\r\n    <li>The effect of credit risk does not dominate the value changes that result from that economic relationship; and</li>\r\n    <li>The hedge ratio of the hedging relationship is the same as that resulting from the quantity of the hedged item that the entity actually hedges and the quantity of the hedging instrument that the entity actually uses to hedge that quantity of hedged item.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3752, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Obtain the documentation of the hedging relationship and consider whether the following have been clearly identified: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The hedging instrument;</li>\r\n    <li>The hedged item;</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the risk being hedged; and</li>\r\n    <li>How the entity will assess whether the hedging relationship meets the effectiveness requirements, including sources of hedge ineffectiveness.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>An economic relationship between a hedged item and hedging instrument exists when the entity expects that the values of the hedged item and hedging instrument will typically move in opposite directions in response to movements in the same risk, which is the hedged risk.</i></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3753, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Confirm the type of hedging relationship in place. This will be one of the 3 following categories:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Fair Value hedge;</li>\r\n    <li>Cash Flow hedge</li>\r\n    <li>Hedge of a net investment in a foreign operation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>A <b>Fair Value hedge</b> is a hedge of the exposure to changes in fair value of a recognised asset or liability or an unrecognised firm commitment, or a component of any such item, that is attributable to a particular risk and could affect profit or loss.  For example – a contract to purchase stock from an overseas supplier, hedged by a compensating forward exchange contract.</i></p>\r\n<p><i>A <b>Cash Flow hedge</b> is a hedge of the exposure to variability in cash flows that is attributable to a particular risk associated with all, or a component of, a recognised asset or liability (such as all or some future interest payments on variable rate debt) or a highly probable forecast transaction, and could affect profit or loss. For example, an interest rate swap.</i></p>\r\n<p><i>A hedge of the foreign currency risk of an unrecognised firm commitment may be accounted for as a fair value hedge or as a cash flow hedge.</i></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3754, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p><b>Fair Value Hedges</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure the gain/loss on the hedging instrument has been recognised in profit or loss.</p>\r\n<p><i>If the hedging instrument hedges an equity instrument for which an entity has elected to present changes in fair value in other comprehensive income, the gain/loss should be recognised in OCI.</i></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3755, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>The hedging gain/loss on the hedged item should also be recognised in profit or loss, with the carrying value of the hedged item adjusted accordingly. Ensure this is the case.</p>\r\n<p><i>If the hedged item is an equity instrument for which an entity has elected to present changes in fair value in other comprehensive income, the hedging gain/loss should remain in OCI.</i></p>\r\n<p><i>If the hedged item is an unrecognised firm commitment, the cumulative hedging gain/loss on the hedged item is recognised as a separate asset/liability, with a corresponding entry through profit or loss.</i></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3756, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>If the hedged item is a financial instrument recognised at amortised cost, then any adjustment arising under test 9 above shall be amortised to profit or loss.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3757, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>If the hedged item is an unrecognised firm commitment to purchase an asset or assume a liability, has the initial carrying amount of the asset/liability that arises as a result of meeting the commitment been adjusted to include the cumulative hedging gain/loss of the hedged item that had been recognised in the statement of financial position?</p>\r\n<p><i>For example: the hedged item is a commitment to purchase a fixed asset from an overseas supplier, and the hedging instrument is a compensating forward exchange contract. The cumulative gain or loss on recognising the fair value of the purchase commitment is CU100. The asset, when acquired, costs CU500. The carrying value is consequently adjusted to be CU400.</i></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3758, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p><b>Cash Flow Hedge</b></p>\r\n<p>A <b>Cash Flow Hedge</b> Reserve should be recognised in equity (as a separate reserve), being the lower of, IN ABSOLUTE TERMS (i.e. ignoring positives or negatives):</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The cumulative gain/loss on the hedging instrument; and</li>\r\n    <li>The cumulative change in fair value on the hedged item</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3759, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Has the portion of the gain/loss on the hedging instrument that is an <b>effective hedge</b> been recognised through <b>other comprehensive income</b>?</p>\r\n<i>This is the portion of the gain/loss that is offset by the change in the cash flow hedge reserve. </i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3760, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Ensure that any gain/loss that relates to <b>hedge ineffectiveness</b> has passed through profit or loss.</p>\r\n<p><i>This is any gain/loss required to balance the change in the cash flow hedge reserve.</i></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3761, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Ensure that the cash flow hedge reserve has been appropriately treated: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>If the transaction results in the recognition of a non-financial asset or liability, the related amount should be removed from the cash flow hedge reserve and included directly in the initial carrying value of that non-financial asset or liability;</li>\r\n    <li>If not, the cash flow hedge reserve should be reclassified  to profit or loss in the same period or periods during which the hedged expected future cash flows affect profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>If the amount is a loss, and all or part of that loss is not expected to be recovered, the amount of the loss not expected to be recovered shall be reclassified to profit or loss immediately.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3762, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p><b>Net Investment in Foreign Operations</b></p>\r\n<p>This type of hedge is normally only relevant when consolidated accounts have been prepared, and are accounted for in a similar manner to cash flow hedges. Ensure that:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The portion of the gain or loss on the hedging instrument that is determined to be an effective hedge is recognised in other comprehensive income; and</li>\r\n    <li>The ineffective portion is recognised in profit or loss.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>Please note that the cumulative gain or loss on the hedging instrument relating to the effective portion of the hedge that has been accumulated in equity shall not be reclassified from equity to profit or loss on disposal or partial disposal of the foreign operation.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3763, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>If hedge accounting has been discontinued, ensure that this has occurred for one of the following reasons:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The hedging instrument has expired, is sold, terminated or exercised; or</li>\r\n    <li>The conditions for hedge accounting are no longer met; or</li>\r\n    <li>The entity has elected to discontinue hedge accounting and the entity has documented this decision. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>In all cases, hedge accounting shall be discontinued prospectively (i.e. not as a prior year adjustment).</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3764, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>The only significant impact of discontinuing hedge accounting arises where there was a cash flow hedge. </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>If the hedged future cash flows are no longer expected to occur, ensure that the amount that has been accumulated in the cash flow hedge reserve was reclassified to profit or loss immediately; and</li>\r\n    <li>If the hedged future cash flows are still expected to occur (for example when the entity has voluntarily elected to discontinue hedge accounting), the cumulative gain or loss in the cash flow hedge reserve should be retained in that reserve until the future cash flows occur (as per test 15 above).</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3765, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Review the detailed transition requirements set out in Chapter 7 of IFRS 9 and ensure these have been appropriately applied.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3766, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>Obtain a reconciliation that shows the impact of first-time adoption of IFRS 9. This should include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Narrative explanation of how the first-time adoption has been treated;</li>\r\n    <li>Narrative explanation of the changes made on first time adoption;</li>\r\n    <li>Narrative relating to any reclassifications made;</li>\r\n    <li>An analysis of each line item in the financial statements as at the end of the prior reporting period (e.g 31 December 2017 for a 31 December 2018 year end) affected by the change, showing:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The figure as originally stated under IAS 39;</li>\r\n            <li>Any reclassification adjustments made (e.g. showing contract assets separately);</li>\r\n            <li>Any remeasurement changes from applying the IFRS 9 requirements;</li>\r\n            <li>The restated figure under IFRS 9</li>\r\n            <li>This should also include a reconciliation of retained earnings as at the date of initial application. </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3767, 40, '2.18.4 S2-4', '2.18.4 S2-4', '<p>If the hedge accounting transition results in a retrospective amendment, ensure that this has been treated appropriately (per IFRS 9.7.2.26). </p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:25:37'),
(3768, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p>Each individual section of the audit file should confirm that the current year figures have been agreed to the trial balance and that comparative figures have been agreed to the prior period’s financial statements. Ensure that this has been undertaken.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3769, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p>Where comparatives period figures have been restated ensure they have been annotated as such and that the restatement is due to one of the following reasons:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A material change in accounting policies (as opposed to an accounting estimate);</li>\r\n    <li>A material error*;</li>\r\n    <li>A reclassification to make this period’s figures and the prior year figures comparable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>A reclassification to make this period’s figures and the prior year figures comparable.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3770, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p>Review the prior period’s unadjusted errors schedule and consider whether the errors identified in the prior period have a material impact on the current period’s financial statements.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3771, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p>Review to ensure that opening balances have been correctly brought forward and that the client correctly processed last period’s audit journal adjustments.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3772, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p><b>JOURNALS</b></p>\r\n<p>Ensure the permanent file documents how the client uses journals.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3773, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p>Undertake a walkthrough test on the client’s journal system (this must cover the actual transaction and associated controls).</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3774, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p>Verify a sample of journals from the nominal ledger to the journal file or similar document and vice versa.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3775, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p>Select a sample of journals, including all items above performance materiality and a random selection of other journals and agree to backing documentation to confirm their validity.  Ensure that the sample includes journals processed throughout the period and also journal posted to facilitate to production of the period-end financial statements.</p>\r\n<i>Ensure that this work does not duplicate work undertaken in other areas of the file, for example, all wage journals may have been reviewed via the work on payroll and depreciation journals may have already have been reviewed by the work in the fixed assets section of the file.</i>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3776, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p><b>SUSPENSE ACCOUNTS</b></p>\r\n<p>Review client suspense accounts (including those with zero balances at the period end) to ensure that entries have been appropriately reallocated.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3777, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p>Consider whether suspense accounts have been well controlled, or whether their usage represents a significant weakness in the client’s accounting system, which requires either additional audit procedures to be undertaken or for an appropriately worded point to be included in the management letter.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3778, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p><b>DETAILED TESTING OF THE NOMINAL LEDGER AND TRIAL BALANCE</b></p>\r\n<p><i>Where the client operates a manual accounting system or there are reservations about the integrity of the computer system used the following tests should be undertaken.</i></p>\r\n<p>Check extraction / casts of trial balance.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3779, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p>Cast on a sample basis a number of nominal ledger accounts.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3780, 41, '2.19.1 U2-1', '2.19.1 U2-1', '<p><b>OTHER TESTS</b></p>\r\n<p>Consider whether additional tests are required to meet audit objectives.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:30:47'),
(3781, 42, '2.19.2 U2-2', '2.19.2 U2-2', '<p>Obtain access to previous auditor’s working papers to assist in the audit of comparatives and opening balances.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:33:55'),
(3782, 42, '2.19.2 U2-2', '2.19.2 U2-2', '<p>Consider the level of work conducted by the previous auditor and whether it covers the requirements of the International Standards on Auditing.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:33:55'),
(3783, 42, '2.19.2 U2-2', '2.19.2 U2-2', '<p>Where reliance is being placed on the work of the previous auditor carry out the appropriate audit tests as included on the Other Audit Areas Audit Programme.</p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:33:55'),
(3784, 42, '2.19.2 U2-2', '2.19.2 U2-2', '<p>Ensure that appropriate accounting policies are consistently applied or changes in accounting policies have been properly accounted for and adequately presented and disclosed.  <b>(P)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:33:55'),
(3785, 42, '2.19.2 U2-2', '2.19.2 U2-2', '<p>Ensure that the comparatives comply in all material respects with the financial reporting framework applicable to the financial statements being audited. <b>(P)</b></p>\r\n', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:33:55'),
(3786, 42, '2.19.2 U2-2', '2.19.2 U2-2', '<p>If the audit report for the previous period was modified, consider the impact on the audit opinion of the current period. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:33:55'),
(3787, 42, '2.19.2 U2-2', '2.19.2 U2-2', '<p>Carry out additional analytical procedures and work on current year figures to give additional support to the opening balances and comparative figures.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:33:55'),
(3788, 42, '2.19.2 U2-2', '2.19.2 U2-2', '<p>Consider whether additional tests are required to meet     audit objectives.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:33:55'),
(3789, 43, '2.19.3 U2-3', '2.19.3 U2-3', '<p>Obtain opening and comparative figures from client / previous advisor.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:36:10'),
(3790, 43, '2.19.3 U2-3', '2.19.3 U2-3', '<p>Review balances for any areas where it will be difficult to audit the opening balance / comparatives (e.g. material inventory balances).</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:36:10'),
(3791, 43, '2.19.3 U2-3', '2.19.3 U2-3', '<p>Ensure that the comparatives comply in all material respects with the financial reporting framework applicable to the financial statements being audited.  <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:36:10'),
(3792, 43, '2.19.3 U2-3', '2.19.3 U2-3', '<p>Ensure that appropriate accounting policies are consistently applied or changes in accounting policies have been properly accounted for and adequately presented and disclosed. <b>(P)</b></p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:36:10'),
(3793, 43, '2.19.3 U2-3', '2.19.3 U2-3', '<p>Carry out analytical procedures and work on current year figures to give additional support to the opening balances and comparative figures.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:36:10'),
(3794, 43, '2.19.3 U2-3', '2.19.3 U2-3', '<p>Ensure an appropriately worded ‘other matter’ paragraph is included in the audit report, explaining that the corresponding period was not audited.  Where sufficient evidence has not been obtained regarding opening balances and comparatives, ensure the audit report is suitably modified.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:36:10'),
(3795, 43, '2.19.3 U2-3', '2.19.3 U2-3', '<p>Consider whether additional tests are required to meet     audit objectives.</p>', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 15:36:10');
