(1691, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'section3', '{\"a1\":\"1\",\"a2\":\"2\",\"a3\":\"5\",\"a4\":\"3\",\"a5\":\"4\",\"a6\":\"6\",\"a7\":\"7\"}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 13:05:07'),
(1693, 45, '3.2 Aa2', 'aa2', '{\"rat\":\"12\",\"rcae\":\"23\",\"atriaq\":\"34\",\"kcapet\":\"45\",\"fd\":\"56\",\"fs\":\"67\",\"oi\":\"78\"}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 13:10:01'),
(1707, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'ir', '5555', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 14:59:56'),
(1719, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>1.	Review the notes of the preplanning meeting with the client, the audit planning memorandum and briefing notes to ensure that any subsequent events noted have been adequately addressed.</p>', 'faf2', 'faf3', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1720, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>2.	Consider whether physical verification work or other audit procedures have indicated that any property, plant and equipment have been destroyed or that operating capabilities have significantly changed since the period end.</p>', 'faf5', 'faf6', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1721, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>3.	Revisit any work conducted on the valuation of intangible fixed assets, property, plant and equipment or investments (including properties).  Consider whether any valuations or reports have been received by the client which shows significant variations from the period end values.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1722, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>4.	Consider whether there have been sales of stock since the period-end that would affect ‘net realisable value’.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1723, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>5.	Consider whether any further information has been received that would impact on the recognition of revenue / profit on sales contracts.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1724, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>6.	Consider the implications if any major debtors have become insolvent or if negotiations have been entered into that affect recoverability of debts or if the period-end debts still outstanding are above the performance materiality level.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1725, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>7.	Consider whether any information has been received in respect of subsidiaries, joint ventures, jointly controlled operations, jointly controlled assets or associates that may impact on the way in which these investments have been treated or the figures included in the financial statements.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1726, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>8.	Enquire into, or extend previous oral or written enquiries of the entity’s legal advisors concerning litigation, claims or disputes.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1727, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>9.	Review our practices’ correspondence and tax files / folders for the period after the reporting date for unusual items.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1728, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>10.	Consider whether disclosure is required of any changes in the tax rates or tax laws enacted or announced since the year end that have significantly affected on either the current or deferred tax liabilities;</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1729, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>11.	Consider if any of the final journal adjustments require additional disclosure in the financial statements.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1730, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>12.	Consider whether any events which have occurred, or are likely to occur bring into question the appropriateness of accounting policies used in the financial statements, including the going concern basis of preparation. </p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1731, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>13.	If there have been any adjusting subsequent events, ensure the materiality and performance materiality calculations are revisited and revised (if necessary), and then reconsider unadjusted audit errors to ensure that the financial statements remain free from material error.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1732, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'faf', '<p>14.	Ensure that an appropriate paragraph is included in the letter of representation.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 15:08:53'),
(1770, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3', '<p>1.  <strong>No material uncertainty:</strong></p>\r\n<p>If events or conditions have been identified that may cast significant doubt on the entity’s ability to continue as a going concern but, based on the audit evidence obtained the auditor concludes that no material uncertainty exists, have adequate disclosures been made about these events or conditions?</p>\r\n<p>Where the auditor concludes that management’s use of the going concern basis is appropriate and no material uncertainty exists, the auditor is required to report by exception in the audit report on such matters.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 16:08:38'),
(1771, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3', '<p>2.  <strong>Material uncertainty:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Where events and conditions are identified which give rise to a material uncertainty with respect to going concern, has adequate disclosure been made in the financial statements?</p>\r\n<p>The financial statements must:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>adequately disclose the principal events or conditions that may cast significant doubt on the entity’s ability to continue as a going concern and management’s plans to deal with these events or conditions; and </li>\r\n    <li>Disclose clearly that there is a material uncertainty related to events or conditions that may cast significant doubt on the entity’s ability to continue as a going concern and, therefore, that it may be unable to realize its assets and discharge its liabilities in the normal course of business.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If adequate disclosure has been made, the opinion shall be unmodified but the audit report shall include a separate section under the heading “Material uncertainty related to Going Concern”.</p>\r\n<p>If adequate disclosure is not made, the auditor shall express a qualified opinion or adverse opinion, in accordance with ISA 705.</p>\r\n', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-03-25 16:19:48'),
