(2029, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has the Regulation of Auditor’s Checklist been completed and adequate consideration given to non-audit services?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2030, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Where necessary, has our anti-money laundering due diligence assessment on this client been reviewed and updated. Also, have all key issues documented on this assessment been incorporated into the staff briefing?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2031, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have points forward from the prior period (including, if appropriate, last year’s management letter and financial statements) been reviewed and suitably actioned?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2032, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have any prior period modifications of the audit opinion or emphasis of matter paragraphs been reviewed and consideration given to the effect on corresponding amounts and whether a modification or emphasis of matter paragraph is required in this period?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2033, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has the Permanent File Checklist been completed, and have all assumptions used to arrive at accounting estimates used by the client been documented?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2034, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have preliminary analytical procedures been undertaken and has client involvement in the preplanning process been adequately documented?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2035, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has the businesses inherent risk and control environment been assessed?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2036, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has inherent risk been assessed for each material class of transaction or balance down to assertion level and have audit programmes been tailored to address the risks? </p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2037, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Where it is planned to test controls, has control risk been assessed for each material class of transaction or balance down to assertion level and have higher level controls also been assessed?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2038, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has materiality and performance materiality been calculated?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2039, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has an assignment plan been prepared?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2040, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Are there any special or additional reporting requirements    relevant to this client (including to parent company auditors), if so have they been adequately addressed?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2041, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have sample sizes been calculated?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2042, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have staff discussed fraud, risk and related parties, including considering the possibility of breaches of law and regulations, and been briefed on all other relevant matters?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2043, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has a planning letter been set to the client?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2044, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p><b>Recording</b></p>\r\n<p>Has the Systems Overview and Computer Systems Review checklist been reviewed and has adequate consideration been given to the risk that IT systems pose to the client?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2045, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has the detailed description of the accounting system and controls been adequately recorded for every material transaction cycle (including those operated by service organisations)?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2046, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Does the accounting system provide a reliable basis for the preparation of accurate financial statements and has the audit practice got an adequate understanding of systems and controls as confirmed by walkthrough tests?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2047, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has an adequate understanding been obtained on non-transaction based controls, such as the use of budgets, management accounts and internal audit functions etc.?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2048, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Based on the information on the permanent file, and audit tests, have adequate accounting records been kept?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2049, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>If reliance has been placed on internal controls:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Did the tests of control justify reliance?</li>\r\n    <li>Were weaknesses, identified in the evaluation process, followed up by adequate substantive tests?</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2050, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p><b>Fieldwork</b></p>\r\n<p>Has the fieldwork addressed the risks identified at the planning stage and been adequately directed by suitably tailored audit programmes?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2051, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have sample sizes calculated at planning been followed and is the basis of selection clearly recorded on working papers?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2052, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Did the period-end substantive testing reflect the reliance obtained from internal control or interim substantive testing?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2053, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Are the conclusions on each account area adequately recorded on the appropriate section of the audit file?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2054, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have all audit programmes been fully completed?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2055, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have proper working papers been prepared?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2056, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has adequate audit evidence been obtained for every material balance and transaction class for each key assertion?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2057, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have all outstanding points been listed for consideration at the final review stage?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2058, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has adequate consideration been given to opening balances and corresponding amounts?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2059, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p><b>Compliance with GAAP </b></p>\r\n<p>Is the financial reporting framework being used appropriate for the company?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2060, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have the financial statements been reviewed in conjunction with an appropriate disclosure checklist and critically reviewed?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2061, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have the accounting policies and estimation techniques selected by the entity been reviewed and are they the most appropriate to the entity’s particular circumstances in order to give a true and fair view?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2062, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Where disclosed in the financial statements, reconcile audit and non-audit fees disclosed to the services and fees noted on the Provision of Non-Audit Services form.</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2063, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p><b>Review and completion </b></p>\r\n<p>Have the materiality and risk forms been updated and reviewed at the finalisation stage by the manager?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2064, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have the following, which arose through the course of the audit, been summarised for review by the audit engagement partner:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Significant changes to the planning;</li>\r\n    <li>Conclusions reached on significant risks;</li>\r\n    <li>Key consultation (both internal and external);</li>\r\n    <li>Departures from an ISA requirement where alternative audit procedures have been performed; and</li>\r\n    <li>Where it has not been possible to achieve an ISA objective and alternative procedures were not possible, a note of the potential impact on the audit report?</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2065, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have all relevant points been included as points forward to next year?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2066, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has a comprehensive subsequent event review and going concern review been carried out?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2067, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has a Letter of Representation been drafted?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2068, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have audit adjustments been communicated and agreed with the client and has it been ensured that the client has posted these to correct the opening balances for the next financial period?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2069, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Has the management letter been drafted?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2070, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Have analytical procedures at finalisation been undertaken?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2071, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Where unadjusted errors exist in the financial statements, are they deemed clearly trivial?  If errors are deemed not to be trivial have they been included in the Letter of Representation?</p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2072, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'planning', '<p>Where fraud or breaches of law and regulations have been identified, has action been taken where relevant (including appropriate communication with those charged with governance and whistle-blowing to the relevant authority)?</p>\r\n', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:38:15'),
(2078, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'audit finalisation', '<p>Confirm that there are no matters which have altered any of the Ethical Considerations set out on the Regulation of Auditor’s Checklist (Ac2), and Provision of Non-Audit Services to Audit Clients (Ac3).  </p>\r\n<p>If matters have arisen, are we able to continue as auditors?</p>\r\n<p><i>The following matters should be considered:</i></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><i>Any matters brought to the attention of the Audit Engagement Partner regarding the audit firm’s independence from the client.</i></li>\r\n    <li><i>Any matters brought to the attention of the firm’s Ethics Partner regarding the audit firm’s independence from the client.</i></li>\r\n    <li><i>Any new non-audit services being provided requiring the completion of form “Provision of Non-Audit Services to Audit Clients”.</i></li>\r\n    <li><i>Any fraud which brings into consideration the integrity of management.</i></li>\r\n</ul>', '', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:53:34'),
(2079, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'audit finalisation', '<p>Have the following findings from the audit been communicated to those charged with governance <i>(ensure there is a note on file to confirm how / when the communication occurred):</i></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The auditor’s views about the appropriateness of the accounting policies and estimation techniques adopted by the company?</li>\r\n    <li>The auditor’s view about the adequacy of the disclosures given in the financial statements?</li>\r\n    <li>Significant difficulties, if any, encountered during the audit?</li>\r\n    <li>The final draft of the representation letter, including any non-standard paragraphs for which the auditor specifically requires a representation, and appendices covering corrected and uncorrected misstatements (if appropriate)?</li>\r\n    <li>Expected modifications to the auditor’s report? <i>(Where a modified audit opinion or an emphasis of matter paragraph is included, has this been fully discussed with the directors and where applicable how it could have been avoided?)</i></li>\r\n    <li>Any other matters of governance interest?</li>\r\n</ul>', '', '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:53:34'),
(2080, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'audit finalisation', '<p>Has a management letter been sent to the client?</p>', '', '3', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:53:34'),
(2081, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'audit finalisation', '<p>Has the two way communication process between the auditors and those charged with governance been adequate for an effective document (ISA 260.22)?</p>', '', '4', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:53:34'),
(2082, 44, '3.1 Aa1', 'audit finalisation', '<p>If the firm’s criteria have been met, has an EQCR been undertaken?</p>', '', '5', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 20:53:34'),
(2083, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'cr', '<p>Determine the nature and extent of accounting records the client has prepared since the period end which can be reviewed by the auditor.  These may include:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>Subsequent interim financial statements;</li>\r\n    <li>Management accounts;</li>\r\n    <li>Budgets (to aid review of management accounts for unusual or unexpected items);</li>\r\n    <li>Nominal ledger, including material journals;</li>\r\n    <li>Sales and purchase records or invoices (including credit notes);</li>\r\n    <li>Payroll records;</li>\r\n    <li>Cashbooks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>NB: It is not expected that all records highlighted above will be reviewed – the most appropriate records based on the client’s circumstances should be reviewed.</i></p>\r\n<p>Document a review of these records.  In particular highlight the date these records have been prepared to and whether this is sufficiently close to the date of the audit report, or whether this work will need to be subsequently revisited.</p>', NULL, '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:43:37'),
(2084, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'cr', '<p>Review minutes of directors’ / shareholders’ meetings and other committees for the period since the reporting date and document any key items which may require disclosure or adjustment in the financial statements.</p>', NULL, '4', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:43:37'),
(2085, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'cr', '<p>Review all entries in ‘sensitive’ nominal ledger accounts, including legal and professional accounts for significant or unusual items and seek appropriate explanations.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:43:37'),
(2094, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'dc', '<p>Document the person(s) with whom subsequent events were discussed and the date of this discussion.  </p>\r\n<p><i>NB: Whether there is no overlap between those persons charged with governance and the entity’s management then it will normally be necessary to have discussion with a representative from both bodies.</i></p>', NULL, '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:49:16'),
(2095, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'dc', '<p>a.	The procedures that management have established (if any) to ensure that subsequent events are identified and what issues (if any) management have identified;</p>', NULL, '2', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:49:16'),
(2096, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'dc', '<p>b.	Where management or other meetings have been held, but no minutes are available, enquire about what matters have been discussed;</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:49:16'),
(2097, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'dc', '<p>c.	Developments regarding any legal claims (for or against the entity); </p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:49:16'),
(2098, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'dc', '<p>d.	Whether significant changes have been made or are proposed which may require disclosure as a non-adjusting event; </p>\r\n<i>NB: This might include, change in the ultimate controlling party, significant sales or purchases of assets or investments, natural disasters, major litigation or substantial changes in asset prices or foreign exchange rates. </i>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:49:16'),
(2099, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'dc', '<p>e.	Whether there have been any developments regarding risk areas and contingencies;</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:49:16'),
(2100, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'dc', '<p>f.	Any evidence of fraud and error being discovered;</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:49:16'),
(2101, 46, '3.3 Aa3a', 'dc', '<p>g.	Significant items identified through the auditors’ review of the client’s records.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-10 21:49:16'),
(2116, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p1', '<p>Date(s) on which the going concern assumption was discussed with the client:</p>', NULL, '123123', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-11 14:46:53'),
(2117, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p1', '<p>Names of the audit team members involved in the discussion:</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-11 14:46:53'),
(2118, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p1', '<p>3.	Names of the person(s) from the entity involved in the discussion:</p>\r\n<i>This must include a representative from ‘those charged with governance’ (e.g. a director of the company) and management. Whilst for many entities ‘those charged with governance’ will also be ‘management’, where Ac2 identifies that this is not the case, it must be ensured that going concern is discussed with both groups.</i>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-11 14:46:53'),
(2119, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p1', '<p>Has the entity prepared formal forecasts or similar for a period at least twelve months from the end of the reporting period?</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-11 14:46:53'),
(2120, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p1', '<p>If the entity has not prepared formal forecasts or similar for a period of at least twelve months from the end of the reporting period, document the nature of the client’s assessment of going concern. </p>\r\n<i>This assessment could include:</i>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><i>Formal budgets on a rolling quarterly basis looking forward, supported by a more informal assessment of the subsequent period</i></li>\r\n    <li><i>Informal assessment by way of expectations of the level of repeat custom and expenses, timing of significant orders, working capital requirements, significant future ‘one-off’ expenditure etc.</i></li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-11 14:46:53'),
(2121, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p1', '<p>Do those charged with governance or management have any concerns about the going concern status of the entity?</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-11 14:46:53'),
(2122, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p1', '<p>Where the answer is ‘yes’, document on a supporting schedule the client’s concerns and how significant they are.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-11 14:46:53'),
(2123, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p2', '<p>Where a formal assessment of going concern has been prepared by the entity obtain a copy, along with backing schedules and supportive information. Consider whether entity’s expectations are realistic and can be supported by evidence obtained elsewhere on file. In particular, compare any budgets and projections to post year end management accounts, review the reasonableness of the assumptions and consider how reliable management information has historically been.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 10:54:22'),
(2124, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p2', '<p>Where the client has not made a formal assessment of going concern, or this assessment does not cover the period up to twelve months from the end of the reporting period, consider whether the informal assessment of going concern is supported by evidence elsewhere on file. Document whether it is considered that this ‘informal’ assessment is sufficient given the going concern risks identified.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 10:54:22'),
(2125, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p2', '<p>Confirm that the entity has (formally or informally) considered a period at least twelve months from the end of the reporting period.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 10:54:22'),
(2126, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p2', '<p>Review the following documents on the audit file and ensure that they support (or don’t conflict with) the client’s assessment of the entity’s going concern status:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Planning documentation, including: points forward, preliminary discussions with the client; preliminary analytical procedures, the assignment plan and briefing notes [Ac Section];</li>\r\n    <li>The subsequent events review [Aa3a];</li>\r\n    <li>Review of ISA compliance critical issues memorandum / significant risks [Aa7];</li>\r\n    <li>Final analytical procedures, including particularly key performance indictors regarding, profitability; liquidity, and gearing [Aa10];</li>\r\n    <li>Review of bank covenants [I Section];</li>\r\n    <li>Review of contingent liabilities [L Section]; and</li>\r\n    <li>The results of the review of board and shareholder meetings [M Section].</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 10:54:22'),
(2127, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p2', '<p>Consider whether the procedures adopted (including the period considered) by the client to identify potential going concern problems are appropriate for this entity.</p>\r\n', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 10:54:22'),
(2128, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p2', '<p>Obtain written confirmation from the client confirming their view that the entity is a going concern and (where applicable) confirming that they have considered a period of at least one year from the end of the reporting period.</p>\r\n', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 10:54:22'),
(2136, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3a', '<p>If the entity has given guarantees to any related party, review the health of these entities or individuals to ensure that it is either unlikely that a liability will crystallise, or if it does, it will not be significant to the going concern status of the entity.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 11:04:27'),
(2137, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3a', '<p>Where the entity is dependent on key customers or key suppliers (that could not be easily replaced), including related parties, has there being any indication that the trade relationship is in jeopardy, or the going concern status of the counterparty is in jeopardy?</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 11:04:27'),
(2138, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3a', '<p>Where the entity is depended on a key employee (who could not be easily replaced) has there been any indication that they are looking to leave the organisation?</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 11:04:27'),
(2139, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3a', '<p>Where the entity is coming to the end of a property lease, is there any indication that a suitable property will not be able to found, or that the level of rent will render the business unviable?</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 11:04:27'),
(2140, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3a', '<p>Where the company is dependent on funding from a related party, has it been ensured that a letter of support has been obtained, and has it been assessed whether the related party has the financial resources to continue to support the client for the foreseeable future?</p>\r\n', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 11:04:27'),
(2141, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3a', '<p>Consider any other specific issues that could impact on the going concern status of the client, these might include:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Impending litigation, or regulatory action against the client;</li>\r\n    <li>Changes in legislation or government (both national and local) policy;</li>\r\n    <li>Changes to local planning law which could adversely affect the client; and</li>\r\n    <li>Technological or market developments which would render the client’s products or services obsolete or uncompetitive.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 11:04:27'),
(2142, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3a', '<p>Where bank finance is significant to the entity and banking covenants are in place, ensure that, if not already addressed on file, compliance with them has been fully assessed and where breaches of covenant have occurred, that the intentions of the bank have been confirmed.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 11:04:27'),
(2143, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3b', '<p><b>No material uncertainty:</b> <br>If events or conditions have been identified that may cast significant doubt on the entity’s ability to continue as a going concern but, based on the audit evidence obtained the auditor concludes that no material uncertainty exists, have adequate disclosures been made about these events or conditions?</p><p>Where the auditor concludes that management’s use of the going concern basis is appropriate and no material uncertainty exists, the auditor is required to report by exception in the audit report on such matters.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 11:12:32'),
(2144, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3b', '<p><b>Material uncertainty:</b><br>Where events and conditions are identified which give rise to a material uncertainty with respect to going concern, has adequate disclosure been made in the financial statements?</p>\r\n', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 11:12:32'),
(2145, 47, '3.4 Aa3b', 'p3b', '<p>The financial statements must:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>) adequately disclose the principal events or conditions that may cast significant doubt on the entity’s ability to continue as a going concern and management’s plans to deal with these events or conditions; and </li>\r\n    <li>) Disclose clearly that there is a material uncertainty related to events or conditions that may cast significant doubt on the entity’s ability to continue as a going concern and, therefore, that it may be unable to realize its assets and discharge its liabilities in the normal course of business.</li>\r\n</ol><p>If adequate disclosure has been made, the opinion shall be unmodified but the audit report shall include a separate section under the heading “Material uncertainty related to Going Concern”.</p><p>If adequate disclosure is not made, the auditor shall express a qualified opinion or adverse opinion, in accordance with ISA 705.</p>', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 11:12:32'),
(2146, 51, '3.7 Aa7', 'aepapp', 'summm', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-12 13:51:15'),
(2159, 54, '3.10 Aa11', 'con', '{\"bdr1\":\"1\",\"bcr1\":\"2\",\"bdr2\":\"3\",\"bcr2\":\"4\",\"cdr1\":\"4\",\"ccr1\":\"3\",\"cdr2\":\"2\",\"ccr2\":\"1\",\"ddr1\":\"11\",\"dcr1\":\"22\",\"ddr2\":\"33\",\"dcr2\":\"44\",\"edr1\":\"44\",\"ecr1\":\"33\",\"edr2\":\"22\",\"ecr2\":\"11\",\"fdr1\":\"111\",\"fcr1\":\"222\",\"fdr2\":\"333\",\"fcr2\":\"444\",\"hdr1\":\"444\",\"hcr1\":\"333\",\"hdr2\":\"222\",\"hcr2\":\"111\",\"idr1\":\"1\",\"icr1\":\"1\",\"idr2\":\"1\",\"icr2\":\"1\",\"jdr1\":\"2\",\"jcr1\":\"2\",\"jdr2\":\"2\",\"jcr2\":\"2\",\"ldr1\":\"3\",\"lcr1\":\"3\",\"ldr2\":\"3\",\"lcr2\":\"3\",\"mdr1\":\"4\",\"mcr1\":\"4\",\"mdr2\":\"4\",\"mcr2\":\"4\",\"odr1\":\"11\",\"ocr1\":\"11\",\"odr2\":\"11\",\"ocr2\":\"11\",\"pdr1\":\"22\",\"pcr1\":\"22\",\"pdr2\":\"22\",\"pcr2\":\"22\",\"qdr1\":\"33\",\"qcr1\":\"33\",\"qdr2\":\"33\",\"qcr2\":\"33\",\"rdr1\":\"44\",\"rcr1\":\"44\",\"rdr2\":\"44\",\"rcr2\":\"44\"}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 19:02:20'),
(2160, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Where exemptions are being applied, has it been ensured that the company is still eligible to take advantage of these (Appendix 1.4, Ab2)?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', '1', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2161, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Has other information in documents containing the audited financial statements, including the Directors’ Report (if applicable), been reviewed to ensure that it is consistent with the audited financial statements, prepared in accordance with applicable legal requirements and is it, to the best of the auditors’ knowledge, free from error (ISA 720.14)?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '99', '99', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2162, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Are references to the length of the accounting period correct (i.e. year or period ended)?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '88', '88', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2163, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Has the name of the company and the director(s) been spelt correctly throughout the annual report and does the company name agree exactly to that registered at our companies’ registry? </p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2164, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Have the financial statements been cast?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2165, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Are references to ‘Director(s)’ consistent with the number of directors?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2166, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Are all pages numbered and are these in agreement with   references given in the contents page and audit report?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2167, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Have the corresponding amounts been checked?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2168, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>If corresponding amounts are unaudited, have they been annotated as such, and has an “Other Matter” paragraph been included in the audit report (ISA 710.14 / ISA 706.10 and 11)?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2169, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Is the use of brackets correctly and consistently applied throughout the primary statements and notes?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2170, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Does the Statement of Financial Position balance?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c3` (`acID`, `c3tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `drps`, `crps`, `drfp`, `crfp`, `issue`, `recommendation`, `result`, `yesno`, `comment`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(2171, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Have items in the Statement of Financial Position and Performance Statement(s) been cross-referenced to the lead schedules?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2172, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Does any additional ‘management information’ such as a detailed analysis of profit or loss (if applicable) agree to the information in the statutory section of the financial statements and has it been annotated, as <i>‘These pages do not form part of the audited financial statements’</i>?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2173, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Do the note numbers agree to the Statement of Financial Position, Statement of Changes in Equity, Statement of Cash Flows and the Performance Statement(s) (where relevant) and are they consecutively numbered?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2174, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p><i>(If applicable)</i> Has the Statement of Cash Flows (including notes) been cross referenced to the S section of the file?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2175, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Where notes contain references to page numbers or other notes are they correct?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2176, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Does the detail in the notes agree to the primary statements?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2177, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p><i>(If applicable)</i> Do the pages referred to in the audit report exclude the Directors’ Report and any ‘management information’?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2178, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Does the Audit Report correctly refer to ‘profit’ or ‘loss’ or ‘results’ as applicable?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2179, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Does the sign off on the Audit Report refer to, and include the name of the “Statutory Auditor”?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2180, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>Does the period covered by the Audit Report and (if applicable) the Directors’ Report agree to the front cover of the financial statements?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2181, 57, '3.13 Ab1', 'ab1', '<p>(If applicable) Does the Directors’ Report include the correct profit or loss figure?</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-15 21:00:02'),
(2218, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Does the Annual Report contain the following documents:', '1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2219, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '•  Front Page;', '1.1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2220, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '•  Contents Page;', '1.2', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2221, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '•  Directors’ Report;', '1.3', 'Best Practice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2222, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '•  Statement of Financial Position;', '1.4', 'IAS 1.9a', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2223, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Statement of Comprehensive Income (SCI);\r\n<p>This either needs to be presented as: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A single statement that has two sections, where the top half contains profit or loss items and must be subtotalled, and the bottom section contains other comprehensive income (OCI).; or</li>\r\n    <li>Two separate statements; a Profit and Loss Account, and a Statement of Comprehensive Income (this will begin with the profit or loss for the period).</li>\r\n</ul>', '1.5', 'IAS 1.10(b)\r\n\r\nIAS 1.10A\r\nIAS 1.80A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2224, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '•  A Statement of Changes in Equity;', '1.6', 'IAS 1.9(c)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2225, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '•  A Statement of Cash Flows', '1.7', 'IAS 1.9(d)\r\nIAS 7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2226, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Have notes been presented in a systematic manner?  \r\n<p>The following order is recommended by IAS 1:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Statement of compliance with the IFRSs,</li>\r\n    <li>Summary of significant accounting policies;</li>\r\n    <li>Supportive information for items presented in the primary statements;</li>\r\n    <li>Other disclosures, including:-\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Contingent liabilities and unrecognised contractual commitments; and</li>\r\n            <li>Non-financial disclosures e.g. the entity’s financial risk management objectives and policies.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '2', 'IAS 1.9(e)\r\nIAS 1.112\r\nIAS 1.113\r\nIAS 1.114', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2227, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Are the financial statements clearly distinguished from other information in the Annual Report?', '3', 'IAS 1.49', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2228, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Have all of the primary statements within the financial statements been presented with equal prominence?', '4', 'IAS 1.11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2229, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Are the primary statements adequately cross referenced to their supporting notes?', '5', 'IAS 1.113', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2230, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<b>Identification of the Financial Statements</b>', '<b>6</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2231, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Are the following disclosed in the financial statements:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The name of the entity (or other means of identification);</li>\r\n    <li>Any changes in the name of the entity (or other means of identification) during the reporting period;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether the financial statements cover an individual entity or a group (i.e. whether they are consolidated or not);</li>\r\n    <li>The date of the end of the reporting period and the period covered by the financial statements;</li>\r\n    <li>The presentational currency; and</li>\r\n    <li>The level of rounding used in the financial statements?</li>\r\n</ul>', '6.1', 'IAS 1.51\r\n(a) to (e) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2232, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Are the following disclosed in the notes to the financial statements:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The domicile and legal form of the entity;</li>\r\n    <li>The country of incorporation;</li>\r\n    <li>The address of its registered office; and</li>\r\n    <li>The principal place of business (if different from the registered office)?</li>\r\n</ul>', '6.2', 'IAS 1.138 (a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2233, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<b>Presentational Currency</b>', '<b>7</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2234, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Where the presentational currency is different from the functional currency, is this fact stated, together with disclosure of the functional currency and the reasons why a different presentational currency has been used?', '7.1', 'IAS 21.53', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2235, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Where there is a change in the functional currency of either the entity, or a significant foreign operation, has this been disclosed, along with the reason for the change?', '7.2', 'IAS 21.54', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2236, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Where information is disclosed in a currency which is neither the functional currency nor the presentational currency is the information in IAS 21 paragraph 57 given?', '7.3', 'IAS 21.57', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2237, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Where an entity is reporting in a hyperinflationary functional currency have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The fact that financial statements and other prior period data have been restated for changes in the general purchasing power of the functional currency, and as a result, are stated in terms of the measuring unit current at the end of the reporting period;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether the financial statements are based on a historic cost approach or a current cost approach, and </li>\r\n    <li>The identity and level of the price index at the reporting date and changes during the current reporting period and the previous reporting period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '7.4', 'IAS 29.39', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2238, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<b>Principal Activities </b>', '<b>8</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2239, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Unless disclosed in the Directors’ Report or Strategic Report, are the following disclosed in the notes to the financial statements:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A description of the nature of the entity’s operations; and</li>\r\n    <li>Its principal activity? </li>\r\n</ul>', '8.1', 'IAS\r\n1.138 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2240, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<b>Limited Life Entities</b>', '<b>9</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2241, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'If the entity is a limited life entity, has information regarding the length of its life been given?', '9.1', 'IAS \r\n1.138 (d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2242, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<b>Company Registration Number</b>', '<b>10</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2243, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Has the company\'s registered number been disclosed in a prominent position?', '10.1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2244, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<b>Comparatives</b>', '<b>11</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2245, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<p>Except when IFRS permits or requires otherwise, has the entity presented comparative information in respect of <b><u>at least</u></b> the preceding period for all amounts presented in the current period’s financial statements (primary statements and notes)?</p>\r\n<p>NB1: The entity must include comparative information for narrative and descriptive information when it is relevant to gain an understanding of the current period’s financial statements.</p>\r\n<p>NB2: Where specific disclosures do not need comparatives, this will be made clear on this disclosure checklist. </p>\r\n<p>NB3: There is no restriction on disclosing comparative amounts that relate to periods earlier than the prior year (and sometimes this is specifically required), however, subject to IFRS 1, this information must be prepared in accordance with IFRS and where additional primary statements are disclosed, then the related note information must also be disclosed.</p>', '11.1', 'IAS \r\n1.10 (ea), 38, 38A\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIAS 1.38B\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIAS 1.38C\r\nIAS 1.38D\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2246, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Where comparatives have been restated either in the primary statement or the notes, have they been annotated as such?', '11.2', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2247, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<p>Where there is a prior period adjustment due to an error, the retrospective application of a new IFRS, or when items have been reclassified, then is necessary to present the Statement of Financial Position as at the beginning of the preceding period <b>(i.e. a third Statement of Financial Position).</b></p>\r\n<p>Where applicable has this disclosure been given?</p>\r\n<p><b>NB 1: THIS WILL BE REQUIRED IF IFRS 9 / 15 / 16 HAVE RETROSPECTIVE IMPACT</b></p>\r\n<p>NB2: It is unnecessary to disclose the related notes.</p>', '11.3', 'IAS 1.9f, 40A, 40B\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIAS 1.40C', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2248, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<b>Materiality and Aggregation</b>', '<b>12</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2249, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Has it been ensured that the financial statements are not cluttered with immaterial disclosures?  Notes which relate to immaterial items should ideally be removed and items disclosed on the face of the primary statements or in the notes should be aggregated with other similar items where they are immaterial.', '12.1', 'IAS 1.29 – 31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2250, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<b>Statement of Directors’ Responsibilities</b>', '<b>13</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2251, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Are the following disclosed:<ul>\r\n    <li>A full Statement of Directors’ Responsibilities (see Appendix 3.12 for suggested wording);</li>\r\n    <li>That as far as the directors are aware, there is no relevant audit information of which the company’s auditors are unaware; and</li>\r\n    <li>That the directors have taken all the steps that they ought to have taken as a director in order to make themselves aware of any relevant audit information and to establish that the company’s auditors are aware of that information?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This disclosure may be given either as a part of the Directors’ Report, or as a separate statement.</p>', '13.1', 'Best Practice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2252, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', '<b>Audit Report</b>', '<b>14</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2253, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section1', 'Has the Audit Report been checked to ensure that it is up to date?', '14.1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:42:31'),
(2254, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section2', 'Is there a fair review of the development and performance of the business of the company and its subsidiaries during the financial period, a description of the principal risks and uncertainties facing the company and its subsidiaries, the position at the period-end and an analysis using financial key performance indicators?\r\n<p><b><i>N.B. It is usually possible to omit some disclosures as follows:-</i></b></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><i>Disclosure of information about impending developments or matters in the course of negotiation if the disclosure would, in the opinion of the directors, be seriously prejudicial to the interests of the company; or</i></b></li>\r\n    <li><b><i>(Disclosure of information about a person) the disclosure would, in the opinion of the directors, be seriously prejudicial to that person and contrary to public interest.</i></b></li>\r\n</ul>', '1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:48:45'),
(2255, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section2', '<b>Financial Instruments</b>', '2', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:48:45'),
(2256, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section2', 'In relation to the use of financial instruments by a company, does the report disclose:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The financial risk management objectives and policies of the company, including the policy for hedging each major type of forecasted transaction for which hedge accounting is used; and</li>\r\n    <li>The exposure of the company to price risk, credit risk, liquidity risk and cash flow risk?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Unless this information is not material for the assessment of the assets, liabilities, financial position and profit or loss of the entity.</p>\r\n<p>NB: If full disclosure is given in the body of the financial statements, then it is acceptable to have a cross-reference to those disclosures.</p>', '2.1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:48:45'),
(2257, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section3', 'Are the names of directors who served at any time during the period disclosed?', '1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:53:22'),
(2258, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section3', 'Are the principal activities of the company and its subsidiaries during the period and any significant changes in activities disclosed?', '2', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:53:22'),
(2259, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section3', 'Is there disclosure of proposed dividends?', '3', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:53:22'),
(2260, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section3', 'In relation to the company and its subsidiaries is there disclosure of:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Particulars of any important events which have occurred post balance sheet;</li>\r\n    <li>An indication of likely future developments in the business; and</li>\r\n    <li>An indication of any activities in the field of research and development?</li>\r\n</ul>', '4', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:53:22'),
(2261, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section3', 'Where a company has acquired its own shares during the period, are the following disclosed: \r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The number and nominal value of shares purchased;</li>\r\n    <li>The consideration paid;</li>\r\n    <li>The reason for purchase; and</li>\r\n    <li>Percentage of called-up share capital these shares represent?</li>\r\n</ul>', '5', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:53:22'),
(2262, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section3', 'In respect of own share acquisitions other than purchases, or a lien or charge on these shares:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Number and nominal value of shares acquired or charged during the period;</li>\r\n    <li>The maximum number and nominal value of such shares held at any time during the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Number and nominal value of shares acquired or charged that were disposed of or cancelled during the period;</li>\r\n    <li>In relation to the above, the amount of called-up share capital those shares represent; and</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of any charge?</li>\r\n</ul>', '6', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:53:22'),
(2263, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section3', 'Does the Directors\' Report state the date of approval by the Board and the names of the directors signing on their behalf?', '7', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 09:53:22'),
(2396, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Format</b>', '<b>1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2397, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Does the Profit and Loss Account (or the top half of the SCI) include the following headings where applicable:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Revenue, presenting separately interest revenue calculated using the effective interest method;</li>\r\n    <li>Gains and losses arising from the derecognition of financial assets measured at amortised cost;</li>\r\n    <li>Finance costs;</li>\r\n    <li>Impairment losses (including reversals of impairment losses or impairment gains) determined in accordance with Section 5.5 of IFRS 9;</li>\r\n    <li>Share of the profit or loss of associates and joint ventures accounted for using the equity method;</li>\r\n    <li>If a financial asset is reclassified out of the amortised cost measurement category so that it is measured at fair value through profit or loss, any gain or loss arising from a difference between the previous amortised cost of the financial asset and its fair value at the reclassification date (as defined in IFRS 9); </li>\r\n    <li>If a financial asset is reclassified out of the fair value through other comprehensive income measurement category so that it is measured at fair value through profit or loss, any cumulative gain or loss previously recognised in other comprehensive income that is reclassified to profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Tax expense; and</li>\r\n    <li>A single amount of discontinuing operations?</li>\r\n</ul>', '1.1', 'IAS 1.82', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2398, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Items in Profit and Loss can either be presented based on their nature or function, has the entity chosen the most appropriate presentation basis?', '1.2', 'IAS 1.99', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2399, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Where items are presented <b><u>based on nature</u></b> the following headings are commonly used on the face of the performance statement:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Revenue;</li>\r\n    <li>Other income;</li>\r\n    <li>Changes in inventories of finished goods and work in progress;</li>\r\n    <li>Raw materials and consumables used;</li>\r\n    <li>Employee benefits expense;</li>\r\n    <li>Depreciation and amortisation expense;</li>\r\n    <li>Other expenses;</li>\r\n    <li>Total expenses; and </li>\r\n    <li>Profit before tax?</li>\r\n</ul>', '1.3', 'IAS 1.102', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2400, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Where items are presented <b><u>based on function of the expense</u></b> the following headings are commonly used on the face of the performance statement:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Revenue;</li>\r\n    <li>Cost of Sales;</li>\r\n    <li>Gross Profit;</li>\r\n    <li>Other Income;</li>\r\n    <li>Distribution Costs;</li>\r\n    <li>Administrative Expenses;</li>\r\n    <li>Other Expenses; and </li>\r\n    <li>Profit before Tax.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If an entity classifies expenses by function, then has additional information been given regarding the nature of expenses, including depreciation and amortisation expense and employee benefit expenses?</p>', '1.4', 'IAS 1.103\r\nIAS 1.104\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2401, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'In the performance statement(s) have additional lines, headings and subtotals been added, when such presentation is relevant to an understanding of the entity’s financial performance?', '1.5', 'IAS 1.85, 85A, 85B', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2402, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Exceptional Items</b>\r\n<p>An exceptional item is one which arises from events within the ordinary activities of the entity, but which due to its size or incidence needs to be separately disclosed (explaining both the amount and the nature) to give a true and fair view.</p>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2403, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Regarding exceptional items, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Their amount; and</li>\r\n    <li>Their nature?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.1', 'IAS 1.97', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2404, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Is separate disclosure given for the following items:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>Write-downs of inventories to NRV or reversal of such a write down;</li>\r\n    <li>Write-downs of PPE to recoverable amount or reversal of such a write down;</li>\r\n    <li>Restructuring of the activities of an entity or reversal of any provision for the costs of restructuring;</li>\r\n    <li>Disposal of items of PPE;</li>\r\n    <li>Disposal of investments;</li>\r\n    <li>Discontinued operations;</li>\r\n    <li>Litigation settlements; and </li>\r\n    <li>Other reversal of provisions?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>NB1: Regarding (a) above IAS 2 specifically notes that the circumstances that lead to the write down or reversal of inventories should be disclosed.</p>', '2.2', 'IAS 1.98\r\nIAS 2.36 (e) (f)\r\nIAS 2.36(g)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2405, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Revenue from Contracts with Customers</b>\r\n<p>IFRS 15 Revenue from Contracts with Customers is mandatory for accounting periods commencing on/after 1 January 2018. The disclosure requirements are <b><u>much</u></b> more substantial than those previouslSy required by IAS 18 and IAS 11. </p>\r\n<p>All disclosures required under IFRS 15 have been listed below in this section, rather than split between the SCI, Statement of Financial Position and Accounting Policies sections of the Checklist. It is considered that, in the circumstances of the significant additional disclosures required, it is more straightforward to provide the disclosure requirements in one section. </p>\r\n<p><b>First time adoption of IFRS 15 will also require additional transitional disclosures; see question 5.2 of Section 8 – “<span style=\"color:blue;\"><u>Accounting Policies and Estimation Techniques</u></span>” below. This will require completion of a supplementary checklist. </b></p>', '<b>3</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2406, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'To enable users of the financial statements to understand the nature, amount, timing and uncertainty of revenue and cash flows arising from contracts with customers, has qualitative and quantitative information been disclosed about <b><u>all</u></b> of the following: \r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The entity’s contracts with customers;</li>\r\n    <li>The significant judgements, and changes in the judgements, made in applying IFRS 15 to those contracts; and</li>\r\n    <li>Any assets recognised from the costs to obtain or fulfil a contract with a customer? </li>\r\n</ul>', '3.1', 'IFRS 15. 110', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2407, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have the disclosures been aggregated or disaggregated as appropriate so that useful information is not obscured by a large amount of insignificant detail or by the aggregation of items with different characteristics?', '3.2', 'IFRS 15. 111', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2408, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Contracts with customers</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2409, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has revenue recognised from contracts with customers been disclosed separately from other sources of revenue?', '3.3', 'IFRS 15. 113 (a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2410, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have any impairment losses recognised on any receivables or contract assets arising from an entity’s contracts with customers been disclosed separately from impairment losses arising on other contracts?<br><i>(NB: This is replicated in the Impairment section below)</i>', '3.4', 'IFRS 15. 113 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2411, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Disaggregation of revenue</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2412, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has revenue recognised from contracts with customers been disaggregated into categories that depict how the nature, amount, timing and uncertainty of revenue and cash flows are affected by economic factors? \r\n<p>NB: IFRS 15 does not prescribe any specific factors to be used as a basis for disaggregating revenue. Guidance is provided in Appendix B “Application Guidance”. Paragraph B87 states that “this disclosure depends on the facts and circumstances that pertain to the entity’s contracts with customers. Some entities may need to use more than one type of category to meet the objective in paragraph 114 for disaggregating revenue. Other entities may meet the objective by using only one type of category to disaggregate revenue”.</p>\r\n<p>Paragraph B89 provides examples of categories that might be appropriate which include, but are not limited to, all of the following:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>type of good or service (for example, major product lines);</li>\r\n    <li>geographical region (for example, country or region);</li>\r\n    <li>market or type of customer (for example, government and non-government customers);</li>\r\n    <li>type of contract (for example, fixed-price and time-and-materials contracts);</li>\r\n    <li>contract duration (for example, short-term and long-term contracts);</li>\r\n    <li>timing of transfer of goods or services (for example, revenue from goods or services transferred to customers at a point in time and revenue from goods or services transferred over time); and</li>\r\n    <li>sales channels (for example, goods sold directly to consumers and goods sold through intermediaries).</li>\r\n</ol>', '3.5', 'IFRS 15. 114\r\nIFRS 15.  B87-B89\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2413, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'If the entity voluntarily applies IFRS 8, has sufficient information been given to allow users to understand the relationship between the disclosure of disaggregated revenue and revenue information disclosed for each reportable segment?', '3.6', 'IFRS 15. 115', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2414, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Contract balances</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2415, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has disclosure been given of all of the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The opening and closing balances of receivables, contract assets and contract liabilities from contracts with customers;</li>\r\n    <li>Revenue recognised in the reporting period that was included in the contract liability balance at the beginning of the period; and </li>\r\n    <li>Revenue recognised in the reporting period from performance obligations satisfied (or partially satisfied) in previous periods? </li>\r\n</ul>', '3.7', 'IFRS 15. 116', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2416, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has an explanation been given of how the timing of satisfaction of the performance obligations relates to the typical timing of payment and the effect that those factors have on the contract asset and contract liability balances? ', '3.8', 'IFRS 15. 117', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2417, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has an explanation been given of the significant changes in contract assets and contract liabilities?\r\n<p>Examples of changes in contract asset and contract liability balances include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>changes due to business combinations;</li>\r\n    <li>cumulative catch-up adjustments to revenue that affect the corresponding contract asset or contract liability, including adjustments arising from a change in the measure of progress, a change in an estimate of the transaction price (including any changes in the assessment of whether an estimate of variable consideration is constrained) or a contract modification;</li>\r\n    <li>impairment of a contract asset;</li>\r\n    <li>a change in the time frame for a right to consideration to become unconditional (i.e. for a contract asset to be reclassified to a receivable); and</li>\r\n    <li>a change in the time frame for a performance obligation to be satisfied (i.e. for the recognition of revenue arising from a contract liability).</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.9', 'IFRS 15. 118', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2418, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Performance obligations</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2419, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has disclosure been given of the entity’s performance obligations in contracts with customers, including a description of all of the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>when the entity typically satisfies its performance obligations (for example, upon shipment, upon delivery, as services are rendered or upon completion of service), including when performance obligations are satisfied in a bill-and-hold arrangement;</li>\r\n    <li>the significant payment terms (for example, when payment is typically due, whether the contract has a significant financing component, whether the consideration amount is variable and whether the estimate of variable consideration is typically constrained in accordance with paragraphs 56–58 of IFRS 15);</li>\r\n    <li>the nature of the goods or services that the entity has promised to transfer, highlighting any performance obligations to arrange for another party to transfer goods or services (i.e. if the entity is acting as an agent);</li>\r\n    <li>obligations for returns, refunds and other similar obligations; and</li>\r\n    <li>types of warranties and related obligations?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<i>This disclosure is likely to be given as an accounting policy. </i>', '3.10', 'IFRS 15. 119', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2420, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Transaction price allocated to the remaining performance obligations</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2421, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has disclosure of the following been given in relation to the entity’s remaining performance obligations:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the aggregate amount of the transaction price allocated to the performance obligations that are unsatisfied (or partially unsatisfied) as of the end of the reporting period; and</li>\r\n    <li>an explanation of when the entity expects to recognise this amount as revenue, either:\r\n        <ol type=\"i\">\r\n            <li>on a quantitative basis using the time bands that would be most appropriate for the duration of the remaining performance obligations; or</li>\r\n            <li>by using qualitative information?</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>NB: As a practical expedient, an entity need not disclose this information for a performance obligation if either of the following conditions is met:</i></p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li><i>the performance obligation is part of a contract that has an original expected duration of one year or less; or</i></li>\r\n    <li><i>the entity recognises revenue from the satisfaction of the performance obligation in accordance with paragraph B16.</i></li>\r\n</ol>', '3.11', 'IFRS 15. 120\r\nIFRS 15. 121\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2422, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has a qualitative explanation been given whether the entity is applying the practical expedient in paragraph 121 and whether any consideration from contracts with customers is not included in the transaction price and, therefore, not included in the information disclosed in accordance with paragraph 120 of IFRS 15? \r\n<p><i>For example, an estimate of the transaction price would not include any estimated amounts of variable consideration that are constrained (see paragraphs 56-58 of IFRS 15)</i></p>', '3.12', 'IFRS 15. 122', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2423, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Significant judgements in the application of IFRS 15</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2424, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the entity disclosed the judgements, and changes in the judgements, made in applying IFRS 15 that significantly affect the determination of the amount and timing of revenue from contracts with customers?\r\n<p>In particular, an entity shall explain the judgements, and changes in the judgements, used in determining both of the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the timing of satisfaction of performance obligations (see paragraphs 124–125); and</li>\r\n    <li>the transaction price and the amounts allocated to performance obligations (see paragraph 126).</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.13', 'IFRS 15. 123', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2425, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Determining the timing of satisfaction of performance obligations</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2426, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'For performance obligations that are satisfied over time, has the entity disclosed both of the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the methods used to recognise revenue (for example, a description of the output methods or input methods used and how those methods are applied); and</li>\r\n    <li>an explanation of why the methods used provide a faithful depiction of the transfer of goods or services?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.14', 'IFRS 15. 124', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2427, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'For performance obligations that are satisfied at a point in time (for example the supply of a single good), has disclosure been given of the judgements the entity made in determining when the customer obtains control over the promised goods or services?\r\n<br>\r\n<i>The disclosure requirements of IFRS 15.124 and 125 are likely to be dealt with in the accounting policies.</i>', '3.15', 'IFRS 15. 125', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2428, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Determining the transaction price and the amounts allocated to performance obligations</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2429, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has information about the methods, inputs and assumptions used for all of the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>determining the transaction price, which includes, but is not limited to, estimating variable consideration, adjusting the consideration for the effects of the time value of money and measuring non-cash consideration;</li>\r\n    <li>assessing whether an estimate of variable consideration is constrained;</li>\r\n    <li>allocating the transaction price, including estimating stand-alone selling prices of promised goods or services and allocating discounts and variable consideration to a specific part of the contract (if applicable); and</li>\r\n    <li>measuring obligations for returns, refunds and other similar obligations?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.16', 'IFRS 15. 126', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2430, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Assets recognised from the costs to obtain or fulfil a contract with a customer</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2431, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has a description of both of the following been given?\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the judgements made in determining the amount of the costs incurred to obtain or fulfil a contract with a customer (in accordance with paragraph 91 or 95); and</li>\r\n    <li>the method it uses to determine the amortisation for each reporting period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.17', 'IFRS 15. 127', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2432, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the closing balances of assets recognised from the costs incurred to obtain or fulfil a contract with a customer (in accordance with paragraph 91 or 95), by main category of asset (for example, costs to obtain contracts with customers, pre-contract costs and setup costs); and</li>\r\n    <li>the amount of amortisation and any impairment losses recognised in the reporting period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.18', 'IFRS 15. 128', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2433, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Practical expedients</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2434, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'If the entity has elected to use the practical expedient in either paragraph 63 (about the existence of a significant financing component) or paragraph 94 (about the incremental costs of obtaining a contract), has it disclosed that fact? ', '3.19', 'IFRS 15. 129', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2435, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Third Party Compensation in Respect of Items of PPE</b>', '<b>4</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2436, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has it been disclosed either on the face of SCI or in the notes, the amount of compensation received from third parties for items of PPE that were impaired, lost or given up during the period?', '4.1', 'IAS 16.74(d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2437, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Discontinued Operations </b> <br>NB: Information regarding previous periods must be re-presented so that it shows all operations that were discontinued by the end of the current reporting period.', '<b>5</b>', 'IFRS 5.34', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2438, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have the following been disclosed as a single line in the SCI (or profit or loss where presented separately):\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The post-tax profit or loss from discontinued operations; and</li>\r\n    <li>The post-tax gain or loss recognised on the measurement to fair value less costs to sell or the disposal of the assets or disposal group(s) constituting the discontinued operation?</li>\r\n</ul>', '5.1', 'IFRS \r\n5.33 (a)\r\n33A\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2439, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Is there an analysis in the notes to the financial statements or integrated into the SCI of the total required to be disclosed by IFRS 5.33(a) into the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The revenue, expense and pre-tax profit or loss of discontinued operations;</li>\r\n    <li>The gain or loss recognised on the measurement to fair value less costs to sell or on the disposal of the assets or disposal group(s) constituting the discontinued operations; and </li>\r\n    <li>The related tax expense?</li>\r\n</ul>', '5.2', 'IFRS \r\n5.33 (b)\r\nIAS 12.81 (h)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2440, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have adjustments in the current period to amounts previously presented in discontinued operations that are directly related to the disposal of a discontinued operation in the prior period been separately disclosed in discontinuing operations?  This disclosure should include both the nature and the amount.\r\n<p>NB1: Practical examples are noted in Paragraph 35 of IFRS 5</p>', '5.3', 'IFRS 5.35', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2441, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Where an entity ceases to classify a component as held for resale, have the results of the component previously presented in discontinued operations been represented as continuing activities and described as such?', '5.4', 'IFRS 5.36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2442, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Where assets or disposal groups are initially or subsequently written down, or the impairment is written back, are these gains and losses separately disclosed in the SCI or alternatively disclosed in the notes to the financial statements?', '5.5', 'IFRS 5.41 (c)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2443, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Research and Development Expenditure (R&D)</b>', '<b>6</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2444, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the aggregated amount of research and development expenditure recognised in the period been disclosed?', '6.1', 'IAS 38.126', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2445, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Amortisation</b>', '<b>7</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2446, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Regarding the amortisation charge on intangible fixed assets, has it been noted in which line item(s) in the SCI they have been included?', '7.1', 'IAS 38.118 (d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2447, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Investment Properties</b>', '<b>8</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c3` (`acID`, `c3tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `drps`, `crps`, `drfp`, `crfp`, `issue`, `recommendation`, `result`, `yesno`, `comment`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(2448, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the amount recognised in profit or loss in relation to the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Rental income;</li>\r\n    <li>Direct operating expenses (including repairs and maintenance) split between those properties that did and did not generate income during the period; and</li>\r\n    <li>The cumulative change in fair value recognised on a sale of investment property from a cost model pool to a fair value model pool?</li>\r\n</ul>', '8.1', 'IAS 40.75(f)\r\n(i) to (iv)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2449, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Impairment (Recognised or Reversed) </b>\r\n<p>The disclosures noted in 9.1 to 9.4 below would normally be given in an operating profit note or on the face of the performance statement(s), however, alternatively these disclosures could be given as part of the reconciliation notes which support the Statement of Financial Position [IAS 36.128].</p>\r\n<p>The disclosures below need to be given separately for each class of asset [IAS 36.127]</p>', '<b>9</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2450, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the amount of impairment losses recognised in profit or loss during the period and the line item(s) of the SCI in which those impairment losses are included been disclosed?', '9.1', 'IAS 36 126(a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2451, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has a similar analysis been given for the reversal of historic impairments?', '9.2', 'IAS 36\r\n126 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2452, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the amount of impairment losses on revalued assets recognised in OCI been disclosed?', '9.3', 'IAS 36\r\n126 (c) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2453, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the amount of impairment losses which have been reversed during the period in relation to revalued assets recognised in OCI been disclosed?', '9.4', 'IAS 36\r\n126 (d) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2454, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have any impairment losses recognised on any receivables or contract assets arising from an entity’s contracts with customers been disclosed separately from impairment losses arising on other contracts? <br>\r\n<i>(Duplicated from the Revenue section above)</i>', '9.5', 'IFRS 15. 113 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2455, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the following been disclosed for an individual asset (including goodwill) or a cash-generating unit, for which an impairment loss has been recognised or reversed during the period:-\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the events and circumstances that led to the recognition or reversal of the impairment loss;</li>\r\n    <li>the amount of the impairment loss recognised or reversed;</li>\r\n    <li>for an individual asset:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>the nature of the asset; and</li>\r\n            <li>if the entity reports segmentally, the reportable segment to which the asset belongs;</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>for a cash-generating unit:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>a description of the cash-generating unit (e.g. production line, a plant, a business operation, or reportable segment as defined by IFRS 8);</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '9.6', 'IAS 36\r\n129 \r\n(a) to (b)\r\n\r\nIAS 36\r\n130\r\n(a) to (d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2456, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the following been disclosed for an individual asset (including goodwill) or a cash-generating unit, for which an impairment loss has been recognised or reversed during the period:-\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the recoverable amount of the asset (cash-generating unit) and whether the recoverable amount of the asset (cash-generating) unit is its fair value less cost of disposal or its value in use;</li>\r\n    <li>if the recoverable amount is fair value less costs of disposal, the entity shall disclose the following information:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>the level of fair value hierarchy (see IFRS 13) within which the fair value measurement of the asset (cash-generating unit) is categorised in its entirety;</li>\r\n            <li>for fair value measurements categorised with Level 2 and Level 3:\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>a description of the valuation technique(s) used to measure fair value less cost of disposal.  If there has been a change in valuation technique, that change and the reason(s) for making it;</li>\r\n                    <li>each key assumption on which management has based its determination of fair value less cost of disposal;</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>the discounting rate(s) used in the current measure and previous measurement if fair value less cost of disposal is measured using a present value technique;</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>if the recoverable amount is based on value in use, the discount rate(s) used in the current estimate and previous estimate (if any) of value in use.</li>\r\n</ul>', '9.7', 'IAS 36\r\n130\r\n(e) to (g)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2457, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Where the information required in IAS 36.130 has not been disclosed (presumably on the grounds of immateriality), has the entity disclosed the following:-\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the main classes of assets affected by impairment losses and the aggregate reversals of impairment losses and the main classes of assets affected by reversal of impairment losses; and</li>\r\n    <li>the main events and circumstances that led to the recognition of these impairment losses and reversal of impairment losses?</li>\r\n</ul>', '9.8', 'IAS 36 \r\n131\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2458, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have the assumptions used to determine the recoverable amount of assets (cash-generating units) during the period been disclosed (other than the disclosures specifically required by IAS 36.134 (see below), this is voluntary disclosure)?', '9.9', 'IAS 36\r\n132', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2459, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Impairment ~ Goodwill Not Allocated to a Cash-Generating Unit</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2460, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Where any portion of the goodwill acquired in a business combination during the period has not been allocated to a cash-generating unit (group of units) at the end of the reporting period, has the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the amount of the unallocated goodwill; and</li>\r\n    <li>the reasons why that amount remains unallocated?</li>\r\n</ul>', '9.10', 'IAS 36\r\n133, 84\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2461, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Impairment ~ Goodwill and Intangible Fixed Assets with Indefinite Useful Lives</b><br>\r\nNB: Where, in certain circumstances, detailed calculations are carried forward and used in the current year’s consideration of impairment in accordance with IAS 36 (paragraphs 24 to 99), the disclosure requirements of paragraphs 134 and 135 noted below relate to these calculations.\r\n<p>Has the following been disclosed for each cash-generating unit (group of units) for which the carrying amount of goodwill or intangible assets with indefinite useful lives allocated to that unit (group of units) is significant in comparison with the entity’s total carrying amount of goodwill or intangible assets with indefinite useful lives:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the carrying amount of goodwill allocated to the unit (group of units);</li>\r\n    <li>the carrying amount of intangible assets with indefinite useful lives allocated to the unit (group of units);</li>\r\n    <li>the basis on which the unit’s (group of units’) recoverable amount has been determined (i.e. value in use or fair value less costs of disposal);</li>\r\n    <li>if the unit’s (group of units’) recoverable amount is based on value in use:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>each key assumption on which management has based its cash flows projections for the period covered by the most recent budget / forecasts.  Key assumptions are those to which the unit’s (group of units’) recoverability is most sensitive;</li>\r\n            <li>a description of management’s approach to determining the value(s) assigned to each key assumption, whether those value(s) reflect past experience or, if appropriate, are consistent with external sources of information, and, if not, why they differ from past experience or external sources of information;</li>\r\n            <li>the period over which management has projected cash flows based on financial budgets / forecasts approved by management and, when a period >5yrs is used for a cash-generating unit (groups of units), an explanation of why that longer period is justified;</li>\r\n            <li>the growth rate used to extrapolate cash flow projections beyond the period covered by the most recent budgets / forecasts, and the justification for using any growth rate that exceeds the long-term average growth rate for the products, industries, or country or countries in which the entity operates, or for the market to which the unit (group of units) is dedicated;</li>\r\n            <li>the discount rate(s) applied to the cash flow projection.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>if the unit’s (group of units’) recoverable amount is based on fair value less costs of disposal, the valuation technique(s) used to measure fair value less cost to disposal\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>If not measured using a quoted price for an identical unit (group of units’):\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>each assumption on which the management has based its determination of fair value less costs of disposal.  Key assumptions are those to which the unit’s (group of units’) recoverable amount is most sensitive;</li>\r\n                    <li>a description of management’s approach to determining the value (or values) assigned to each key assumption, whether those values reflect past experience or, if appropriate, are consistent with external sources of information, and if not, how and why they differ from past experience or external sources of information;</li>\r\n                    <li>the level of fair value hierarchy (see IFRS 13) within which the fair value measurement is categorised in its entirety;</li>\r\n                    <li>if there has been a change in valuation techniques, the change and the reason for making it.</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n            </li>\r\n            <li>If fair value less costs of disposal is measured using discounted cash flow projections then the following need to be disclosed:\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>the period over which management has projected cash flows;</li>\r\n                    <li>the growth rate used to extrapolate cash flow projections;</li>\r\n                    <li>the discount rate(s) applied to the cash flow projections;</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>If a reasonably possible change in a key assumption on which management has based its determination of the unit’s (group of units’) recoverable amount would cause the unit’s (group of units’) carrying amount to exceeds its recoverable amount:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>the amount by which the unit’s (group of units’) recoverable amount exceeds it carrying amount;</li>\r\n            <li>the value assigned to the key assumptions;</li>\r\n            <li>the amount by which the value assigned to key assumptions must change, after incorporating any consequential effects of the change on the other variables used to measure recoverable amount, in order for the unit’s (group of units’) recoverable amount to equal its carrying amount?</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>9.11</b>', 'IAS 36\r\n136\r\n\r\nIAS 36\r\n134\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2462, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'If some or all of the carrying amount of goodwill or intangible assets with indefinite useful lives is allocated across multiple cash-generating units (groups of units), and the amounts so allocated to each unit (group of units) is not significant in comparison with the entity’s total carrying amount of goodwill or intangible asset with indefinite useful lives are the following disclosed:-\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>that fact;</li>\r\n    <li>aggregate carrying value of goodwill or intangible with indefinite useful lives allocated to those units (groups of units) ;</li>\r\n    <li>additionally, if the recoverable amounts of any of those units (groups of units) are based on the same key assumption(s) and the aggregate carrying amount of goodwill or intangible assets with indefinite useful lives allocated to them is significant in comparison with the entity’s total carrying amount of goodwill or intangible assets with indefinite useful lives, an entity shall disclose that fact, together with:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>the aggregate carrying amount of goodwill allocated to those units (groups of units);</li>\r\n            <li>the aggregate carrying amount of intangible assets with indefinite useful lives allocated to those units (group of units);</li>\r\n            <li>a description of the key assumptions;</li>\r\n            <li>a description of management’s approach to determining the value(s) assigned to the key assumption(s), whether those value(s) reflect past experience or, if appropriate, are consistent with external sources of information, and if not, how and why they differ from past experience or external sources of information;</li>\r\n            <li>if a reasonably possible change in the key assumption(s) would cause the aggregate of the units’ (groups of units’) carrying amounts to exceed the aggregate of their recoverable amounts:\r\n                <ul>\r\n                    <li>the amount by which the aggregate of the units’ (groups of units’) recoverable amounts exceed the aggregate of their carrying amounts;</li>\r\n                    <li>the value(s) assigned to the key assumption(s);</li>\r\n                    <li>the amount by which the value(s) assigned to the key assumption(s) must change, after incorporating any consequential effects of the change on the other variables used to measure recoverable amount, in order for the aggregate of the units’ (groups of units’) recoverable amount to be equal to the aggregate of their carrying amounts?</li>\r\n                </ul>\r\n            </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '9.12', 'IAS 36\r\n135', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2463, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Inventories</b>', '<b>10</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2464, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the total value of inventories items sold in the period been disclosed? <br>\r\n\r\nNB: This requirement is not simply satisfied by disclosing the COS figure, this is due to both opening inventories and closing inventories figures sometimes including production overheads, however, the purchases element of the COS often does not.\r\n', '10.1', 'IAS 2.36 (d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2465, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Foreign Currency Gains and Losses</b>', '<b>11</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2466, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the amount of exchange differences recognised in profit or loss except those arising on financial instruments measured at fair value through profit or loss, been disclosed?', '11.1', 'IAS 21\r\n52(a)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2467, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Employee Costs</b>', '<b>12</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2468, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Is the average monthly number of employees (including directors and employees working wholly or mainly overseas) in the period disclosed both in total and by category of employee?', '12.1', 'Best Practice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2469, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Is the aggregate of each of the following amounts disclosed in respect of the employees included above:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Payroll costs paid or payable;</li>\r\n    <li>Social security costs; and</li>\r\n    <li>Other pension costs so incurred?</li>\r\n</ul>', '12.2', 'Best Practice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2470, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Key Management Personnel (KMP) Compensation</b>\r\n<p>Key management is defined as ‘those persons having authority and responsibility for planning, directing and controlling the activities of the entity, directly or indirectly, including any director (whether executive or non-executive) of that entity’.</p>\r\n<p>If an entity obtains key management personnel services from another entity (the management entity), the entity is not required to give the disclosure noted below.</p>\r\n', '<b>13</b>', 'IAS 24.9\r\n\r\nIAS 24.17A\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2471, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the entity disclosed key management compensation in total and for each of the following categories;\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Short-term employee benefits;</li>\r\n    <li>Post-employment benefits;</li>\r\n    <li>Other long-term benefits;</li>\r\n    <li>Termination benefits; and</li>\r\n    <li>Share-based payment?</li>\r\n</ul>', '13.1', 'IAS 24.17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2472, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Auditors’ Remuneration</b>', '<b>14</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2473, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has disclosure been made of remuneration receivable by the auditor of the company (including non-cash benefits and expenses) disclosed, split into the following headings:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>statutory audit of the annual accounts</li>\r\n    <li>total fees charged for other assurance services; </li>\r\n    <li>total fees charged for tax advisory services; and</li>\r\n    <li>total fees charged for other non-audit services?</li>\r\n</ul>', '14.1', 'Best Practice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2474, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Entity is a Lessee: Lease related expenses</b>', '<b>15</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2475, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'IFRS 16 Leases requires information about leases for which the entity is a lessee to be presented in a single note (or separate section) in the financial statements.\r\n<p>Therefore, all disclosures required for lessees under IFRS 16 have been included in Section 6 – Statement of Financial Position below.</p>\r\n<i>It is considered that, in the circumstances of the significant additional disclosures required, it is more straightforward to provide the disclosure requirements in one section, rather than split between the SCI, Statement of Financial Position and Accounting Policies sections of the Checklist. </i>', '15.1', 'IFRS 16 \r\n52\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2476, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Entity is a Lessor: Lease related income</b>', '<b>16</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2477, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'As per above, all IFRS 16 disclosure requirements for lessors have also been included in Section 6 - Statement of Financial Position below.', '16.1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2478, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Tax on Profit and Loss on Ordinary Activities</b>', '<b>17</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2479, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have the major components of tax expense (income) been disclosed separately?\r\n<p>NB:  Components of tax expense (income) may include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>current tax expense (income);</li>\r\n    <li>any adjustments recognised in the period for current tax of prior periods;</li>\r\n    <li>any amounts of deferred tax expenses (income) relating to the origination and reversal of temporary differences;</li>\r\n    <li>the amount of deferred tax expense (income) relating to changes in tax rates or the imposition of new taxes;</li>\r\n    <li>the amount of the benefit arising from a previously unrecognised tax loss, tax credit or temporary difference of a prior period that is used to reduce current tax expense;</li>\r\n    <li>the amount of the benefit arising from a previously unrecognised tax loss, tax credit or temporary difference of a prior period that is used to reduce deferred  tax expense;</li>\r\n    <li>deferred tax expense arising from the write-down, or reversal of a previous written-down, or a deferred tax asset to reflect its recoverable amount (IAS 12.56);</li>\r\n    <li>the amount of tax expense (income) relating to those changes in accounting policies and errors that are included in profit or loss in accordance with IAS, because they cannot be accounted for retrospectively.</li>\r\n</ul>', '17.1', 'IAS 12\r\n79, \r\n80 (a) to (g)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2480, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Is there an explanation of the relationship between tax expense (income) and accounting profit in either or both of the following forms:-\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>a numerical reconciliation between tax expense (income) and the product of accounting profit multiplied by the applicable tax rate(s), disclosing, also the basis on which the applicable tax rate(s) is (are) computed, or</li>\r\n    <li>a numerical reconciliation between the average effective tax rate and the applicable tax rate, disclosing also the basis on which the applicable tax rate is computed?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nNB: There is guidance on creating this note, plus worked examples in sections 84 to 86 of IAS 12.', '17.2', 'IAS 12 \r\n81 (c)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2481, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Is there an explanation of any changes in the applicable tax rate(s) compared with the previous reporting period?', '17.3', 'IAS 12\r\n81 (d)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2482, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Is the amount (and expiry date, if any) of deductible temporary differences, unused tax losses, and unused tax credits for which no deferred tax asset is recognised?', '17.4', 'IAS 12\r\n81 (e) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2483, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Dividends in Specie</b>', '<b>18</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2484, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Dividends in specie must be measured at fair value. Any  difference between this fair value and the book value of the assets distributed needs to be shown as a separate line in profit or loss; has this been disclosed?<br>\r\nNB: IFRIC 17 does not apply to a distribution of a non cash asset that is ultimately controlled by the same party or parties before and after the distribution.', '18.1', 'IFRIC 17.15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2485, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Extinguishing Financial Liabilities with Equity Instruments</b>', '<b>19</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2486, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Where an equity instrument has been issued which extinguishes, or part extinguishes a financial liability, has any gain or loss either been disclosed as a separate line in profit or loss or disclosed in the notes to the financial statements?', '19.1', 'IFRIC\r\n19.11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2487, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Other Comprehensive Income (OCI)</b>', '<b>20</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2488, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Are items charged or credited to OCI suitably classified by their nature?\r\n<p>This should include net exchange differences.</p>', '20.1', 'IAS 1.82A\r\n\r\nIAS 21.52(a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2489, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Is the share of the OCI of associates and joint ventures separately disclosed?\r\n<br>\r\nNB: Equity accounting is currently only allowed in consolidated financial statements, however, a change to IAS 27 will allow this in individual entity financial statements. ', '20.2', 'IAS 1.82A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2490, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Are items in OCI group based on those that:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>will not be reclassified subsequently to profit or loss; and</li>\r\n    <li>will be reclassified subsequently to profit or loss when specific conditions are met?</li>\r\n</ul>', '20.3', 'IAS 1.82A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2491, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the amount of income tax relating to each item of OCI been disclosed (this can either be done on the face of the performance statement or in the notes)?', '20.4', 'IAS 1.90', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2492, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have reclassification adjustments relating to components of OCI been disclosed?', '20.5', 'IAS 1.92', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2493, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'For each component, is the aggregate of current tax charged or credited to OCI disclosed?', '20.6', 'IAS 12\r\n81 (ab)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2494, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'For each component, is the aggregate of deferred tax charged or credited to OCI disclosed?', '20.7', 'IAS 12\r\n81 (ab)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2495, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the change in the revaluation surplus of an item of PPE arising from a change in a decommissioning, restoration or similar liability been separately identified and disclosed?', '20.8', 'IFRIC 1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2496, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', '<b>Financial Instrument Disclosures</b>\r\n<p>The following items of income, expense, gains or losses relate both to the Profit and Loss Account and to OCI.  The following information either needs to be given on the face or the primary statement(s) or in the notes to the financial statements.</p>', '<b>21</b>', 'IFRS 7.20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2497, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have net gains or net losses on the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>financial assets or financial liabilities measured at fair value through profit or loss, showing separately:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>those on financial assets or financial liabilities designated as such upon initial recognition or subsequently in accordance with paragraph 6.7.1 of IFRS 9; and </li>\r\n            <li>those on financial assets or financial liabilities that are mandatorily measured at fair value through profit or loss in accordance with IFRS 9 (eg financial liabilities that meet the definition of held for trading in IFRS 9). </li>\r\n            <li>For financial liabilities designated as at fair value through profit or loss, an entity shall show separately the amount of gain or loss recognised in other comprehensive income and the amount recognised in profit or loss.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>financial liabilities measured at amortised cost;</li>\r\n    <li>financial assets measured at amortised cost;</li>\r\n    <li>investments in equity instruments designated at fair value through other comprehensive income in accordance with paragraph 5.7.5 of IFRS 9; and</li>\r\n    <li>financial assets measured at fair value through other comprehensive income in accordance with paragraph 4.1.2A of IFRS 9, showing separately the amount of gain or loss recognised in other comprehensive income during the period and the amount reclassified upon derecognition from accumulated other comprehensive income to profit or loss for the period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '21.1', 'IFRS 7.20(a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2498, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has the total interest income and total interest expense (calculated using the effective interest method) been disclosed for financial assets held at amortised cost or FVOCI, or financial liabilities that are not held at fair value through profit or loss?', '21.2', 'IFRS 7\r\n20 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2499, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Have income and expenses (other than amounts included in determining the effective interest rate) arising from:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Financial assets or financial liabilities that are not at fair value through profit or loss; and</li>\r\n    <li>Trusts and other fiduciary activities that result in the holding or investing of assets on behalf of individuals, trusts, retirement benefit plans, or other institutions, been disclosed?</li>\r\n</ul>', '21.3', 'IFRS 7\r\n20 (c) \r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2500, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section4', 'Has an analysis of the gain or loss recognised in the statement of comprehensive income arising from the derecognition of financial assets measured at amortised cost, showing separately gains and losses arising from derecognition of those financial assets, been disclosed?\r\n<p>This disclosure shall include the reasons for derecognising those financial assets.</p>', '21.4', 'IFRS 7.20A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 11:27:25'),
(2501, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', 'Does the Statement of Changes in Equity show changes in equity, this should be a columnar analysis showing both a total and each component in equity, including the following items ', '1', 'IFRS 1.106', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2502, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  Brought forward balances;', '', '(d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2503, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  Profit or loss for the period;', '', '(d)(i)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2504, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  OCI (each element either needs to be disclosed on the face of this Statement or in supplementary notes);', '', '(d)(ii), A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2505, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  Prior period adjustments resulting from material errors;', '', '(b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2506, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  Prior period adjustments resulting from changes in accounting policy that led to a material adjustment;', '', '(b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2507, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  Issue of shares;', '', '6.3 (c) (iii)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2508, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  Purchase of own shares;', '', '6.3 (c) (iii)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2509, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  Dividends and other distributions to shareholders;', '', '(d) (iii)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2510, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  Capital contributions;', '', '(d) (iii)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2511, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  Transfers between different reserves?', '', '6.3 (c) (iii)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2512, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', '•  Carried forward balances.', '', 'IFRS 1.106 (d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2513, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', 'Is the aggregate of current tax charged or credited to equity disclosed?', '2', 'IAS 12 81(a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2514, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section5', 'Is the aggregate of deferred tax charged or credited to equity disclosed?', '3', 'IAS 12\r\n81(a)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 12:33:43'),
(2700, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Format and Presentation of the Balance Sheet</b>', '<b>1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2701, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b><u>As a minimum</u></b>, does the statement of financial position include line items that present:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>Property, plant and equipment;</li>\r\n    <li>Investment property;</li>\r\n    <li>Intangible assets;</li>\r\n    <li>Financial assets (excluding amounts shown under e., h, and i);</li>\r\n    <li>Investments accounted for using the equity method;</li>\r\n    <li>Biological assets;</li>\r\n    <li>Inventories;</li>\r\n    <li>Trade and other receivables;</li>\r\n    <li>Cash and cash equivalents;</li>\r\n    <li>The total of assets classified as held for sale and assets included in disposal groups classified as held for resale in accordance with IFRS 5;</li>\r\n    <li>Trade and other payables;</li>\r\n    <li>Provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>Financial liabilities (excluding amounts shown under k. and l.)</li>\r\n    <li>Liabilities and assets for current tax;</li>\r\n    <li>Deferred tax liabilities and assets;</li>\r\n    <li>Liabilities included in disposal groups classified as held for sale in accordance with IFRS 5;</li>\r\n    <li>Issued capital and reserves attributable to owners of the parent.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>NB1: The Standard does not prescribe either the format or the order in which these items are presented.</p>', '1.1', 'IAS 1.54\r\n\r\nIAS 1.57', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2702, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where necessary to give a true and fair view, have additional line items, headings and subtotals been included in the Statement of Financial Position?', '1.2', 'IAS 1.55, 58,59', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2703, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '(Unless a liquidity based or ‘mixed’ basis presentation is more relevant) an entity shall present the following as separate elements of the Statement of Financial Positions:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Current Assets;</li>\r\n    <li>Non-Current Assets;</li>\r\n    <li>Current Liabilities; and</li>\r\n    <li>Non-Current Liabilities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB1:  All deferred tax balance must be classified as non-current.</p>\r\n<p>NB2: Different terminology can be used for the above classifications.</p>', '1.3', 'IAS 1.60\r\n\r\nIAS 1.56\r\n\r\nIAS 1.67', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2704, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Irrespective of how the Statement of Financial Position is presented, has the entity disclosed the amount expected to be recovered or settled after more than 12 months for each asset and liability line item that combines amounts expected to be recovered or settled:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>No more than twelve months after the reporting period; and </li>\r\n    <li>More than twelve months after the reporting period?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Specific IFRS require extensive maturity disclosure regarding financial instruments (and thus there is some overlap in the requirements of the Standards), however, IAS 1.61 requires maturity analysis about all classifications, thus for example, provisions and stock would need the above analysis.</p>', '1.4', 'IAS 1.61\r\n\r\nIAS 1.64.65', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2705, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<p>An entity shall disclose, either on the face of the Statement of Financial Position or in the notes a suitable sub-classification of the line items presented in the Statement of Financial Position (i.e. a split of receivables into: trade, related party, prepayment and other).</p>\r\n<p>IAS 1 gives examples only, and some specific Standards prescribe a minimum level of analysis (these issues have been specifically noted later in the checklist), however, management of the entity must consider whether the level of analysis is detailed enough to be meaningful.</p>\r\n<p>Has an adequate level of analysis been given for Statement of Financial Position items?</p>', '1.5', 'IAS 1.77', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2706, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Non-Current Assets classified as Held for Resale and the Assets of a Disposal Group</b>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2707, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Have non-current assets classified as held for sale and the assets of disposal groups classified as held for sale been disclosed separately?', '2.1', 'IFRS 5.38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2708, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Have the liabilities of disposal groups been disclosed separately within liabilities?', '2.2', 'IFRS 5.38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2709, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Have the major classes of assets or liabilities classified as held for sale been separately disclosed either in the Statement of Financial Position or the notes?', '2.3', 'IFRS 5.38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2710, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is there a description of the non-current assets (or disposal group)?', '2.4', 'IFRS 5.41(a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2711, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is there a description of the facts and circumstances of the sale, or leading to the expected disposal, and the expected manner and timing of that disposal?', '2.5', 'IFRS 5.41(b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2712, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where a non-current asset (or disposal group) ceases to be treated as such have the following been disclosed:-\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A description of the facts and circumstances leading to the decision; and </li>\r\n    <li>The effect of the decision on the results of operations for the period and any prior periods presented?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.6', 'IFRS 5.42', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2713, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Approval and Signature</b>', '<b>3</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2714, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is the date on which the financial statements are to be authorised for issue by the board of directors disclosed?', '3.1', 'IAS 10.17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2715, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where applicable has it been disclosed that under legislation, on a voluntary basis, the directors can amend these financial statements if they subsequently prove to be defective?', '3.2', 'IAS 10.17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2716, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Are the names of the directors signing on behalf of the board stated?\r\n<p><i>If there is only one director, only one signature is needed.</i></p>', '3.3', 'Best Practice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2717, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Intangible Assets (Including Goodwill)</b>', '<b>4</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2718, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Are intangible assets suitably analysed, IAS 38 gives the following examples, which could be aggregated or disaggregated to make the information more meaningful:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Brand names;</li>\r\n    <li>Mastheads and publishing titles;</li>\r\n    <li>Computer software;</li>\r\n    <li>Licences and franchises;</li>\r\n    <li>Copyrights, patents and other industrial property rights, service and operating rights;</li>\r\n    <li>Recipes, formulae, models, designs and prototypes; and</li>\r\n    <li>Intangible assets under development?</li>\r\n</ul>', '4.1', 'IAS 38.119\r\n\r\nIAS 38.125', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2719, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Entities are encouraged to disclose the following information by IAS 38.128:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A description of any fully amortised intangible assets that are still in use; and</li>\r\n    <li>A brief description of significant intangible assets controlled by the entity but not recognised because they did not meet the recognition criteria in IAS 38 or because they were acquired or generated before the version of IAS 38 issued in 1998 was effective?</li>\r\n</ul>', '4.2', 'Voluntary Disclosure', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2720, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where intangible fixed assets are revalued have the following disclosures been given by class of asset:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The effective date of the revaluation;</li>\r\n    <li>The carry value of the intangible assets;</li>\r\n    <li>The carrying value that would have been recognised had the assets been carried under the historic cost model?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: It is illegal to revalue goodwill and other intangibles can rarely be revalued.</p>', '4.3', 'IAS 38.124 (a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2721, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is the following reconciliation note disclosed for each class of intangible fixed assets noted above and distinguishing between internally generated intangibles and other intangibles?\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Aggregate cost / valuation at the beginning and end of the financial period;</li>\r\n    <li>Additions, indicating separately those from internal development and those actually acquired;</li>\r\n    <li>Acquisitions through businesses combinations;</li>\r\n    <li>Assets now classified as held for sale or included in a disposal group classified as held for sale in accordance with IFRS 5;</li>\r\n    <li>Other disposals;</li>\r\n    <li>Increases and decreases in revaluation;</li>\r\n    <li>Net exchange difference arising on the translation of the financial statement into the presentation currency, and on translation of a foreign operation into the presentation currency of the entity;</li>\r\n    <li>Other changes;</li>\r\n    <li>Aggregate cumulative amortisation / impairment losses at the beginning and end of  the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Amortisation;</li>\r\n    <li>Impairment losses recognised in the profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Impairment losses reversed in the profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Any adjustments as a result of disposals in the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Assets now classified as held for sale or included in a disposal group classified as held for sale in accordance with IFRS 5; </li>\r\n    <li>Other disposals;</li>\r\n    <li>Net exchange differences arising on the translation of the financial statements into the presentation currency, and on translation of a foreign operation into the presentation currency of the entity;</li>\r\n    <li>Other changes;</li>\r\n    <li>Net carrying amount at the beginning and end of the period?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: Full corresponding amounts <b><u>need</u></b> to be disclosed.</p>', '4.4', 'IAS 38.118 (c), (e) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2722, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where an <b><u>individual</u></b> intangible fixed asset is material, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A description of the asset;</li>\r\n    <li>The carrying value;</li>\r\n    <li>The remaining amortisation period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '4.5', 'IAS 38.122\r\n(b)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2723, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Have any contractual commitments for the acquisition of intangible assets been disclosed?', '4.6', 'IAS 38.122 (e) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2724, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where any intangible assets have restricted title or have been pledged as security for a liability, has this been disclosed?', '4.7', 'IAS 38.122 (d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c3` (`acID`, `c3tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `drps`, `crps`, `drfp`, `crfp`, `issue`, `recommendation`, `result`, `yesno`, `comment`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(2725, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where intangible assets have been acquired by way of a grant and have been recognised at fair value in accordance with IAS 38.44, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The fair value initially recognised for these assets;</li>\r\n    <li>The carrying value of these asset; and </li>\r\n    <li>Whether they are measured after recognition under the cost model or the revaluation model?</li>\r\n</ul>', '4.8', 'IAS 38.122 (c )', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2726, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where an intangible asset is deemed to have an indefinite useful economic life, have the following been disclosed:-\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Its carrying value; and</li>\r\n    <li>The reasons supporting the assessment of an indefinite useful life (IAS 38.90 gives examples)?</li>\r\n</ul>', '4.9', 'IAS 38.122 (a),\r\nIAS 38.123\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2727, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Property Plant and Equipment (PPE)</b>', '<b>5</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2728, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is PPE suitably classified?\r\n<p>The following examples are given in IAS 16:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Land;</li>\r\n    <li>Land and buildings;</li>\r\n    <li>Machinery;</li>\r\n    <li>Ships;</li>\r\n    <li>Aircraft;</li>\r\n    <li>Motor vehicles;</li>\r\n    <li>Furniture and fixtures; and </li>\r\n    <li>Office equipment.</li>\r\n</ul>', '5.1', 'IAS 1.77(a)\r\n\r\nIAS 16.36\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2729, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the existence and carrying amounts of PPE to which the entity has restricted title, or that is pledged as security for a liability been disclosed?', '5.2', 'IAS 16.74 (a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2730, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the amount of expenditure recognised in the carrying amount of an items of PPE in the course of construction been disclosed?', '5.3', 'IAS 16.74 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2731, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where useful to the user of the financial statements, have the following disclosures been given:-\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The carrying amount of temporarily idle items of PPE;</li>\r\n    <li>The gross carrying amount of any fully depreciated items of PPE that are still in use;</li>\r\n    <li>The carrying value of items of PPE retired from active use and not classified as held for sale in accordance with IFRS 5; and </li>\r\n    <li>When the cost model is used, the fair value of PPE when this is materially different from the carrying amount?</li>\r\n</ul>', '5.4', 'IAS 16.79', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2732, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is the following reconciliation note disclosed for each class of PPE:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Aggregate cost / valuation at the beginning and end of the financial period;</li>\r\n    <li>Additions;</li>\r\n    <li>Acquisitions through businesses combinations;</li>\r\n    <li>Assets classified as held for sale or included in a disposal group as classified as held for sale in accordance with IFRS 5 or other disposals;</li>\r\n    <li>Foreign exchange movements;</li>\r\n    <li>Revaluations;</li>\r\n    <li>Other changes.</li>\r\n    <li>Aggregate cumulative depreciation / impairment losses at the beginning and end of  the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Depreciation;</li>\r\n    <li>Revaluations;</li>\r\n    <li>Impairment losses recognised in profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Impairment losses reversed in profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Any adjustments as a result of assets being classified as held for sale or included in a disposal group as classified as held for sale in accordance with IFRS 5 or other disposals;</li>\r\n    <li>Foreign exchange movements;</li>\r\n    <li>Other changes.</li>\r\n    <li>Net carrying amount at the beginning and end of the period?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB1: Full corresponding amounts need to be disclosed.</p>\r\n<p>NB2: Transfers to and from investment properties will also need to be disclosed.</p>', '5.5', 'IAS 16.73\r\n\r\nIAS 40.76(f)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2733, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where items of PPE have been revalued, have the following disclosures been given in addition to the disclosures required by IFRS 13:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The effective date of the revaluation;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether an independent valuer was involved;</li>\r\n    <li>For each classification of PPE, the carrying value that would have been recognised if a cost model had been adopted?</li>\r\n</ul>', '5.6', 'IAS 16.77\r\n(a) (b) (d)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2734, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Right of Use Assets and Assets Used in Operating Leases</b>', '<b>6</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2735, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'IFRS 16 Leases disclosure requirements are collated into questions 13 to 16 below.', '6.1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2736, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Investment Properties</b>', '<b>7</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2737, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<p>Has the extent to which the fair value of investment properties is based on a valuation by an independent, qualified valuer, with recent experience in the location and class of asset been disclosed?</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, where no such valuation has been undertaken has this fact been disclosed?</p>\r\n<p>NB: This disclosure would also apply where valuations are disclosed rather than accounted for.</p>', '7.1', 'IAS.40 75 (e) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2738, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where there are restrictions on the realisability of investment properties or the remittance of income and proceeds of disposal has this been disclosed?', '7.2', 'IAS 40.75 (g)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2739, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'For accounting periods beginning <b><u>on or after 1 January 2018,</u></b> review paragraphs 57 and 58 of IAS 40 in relation to transfers of investment properties. These have been amended by <i>Transfers of Investment Property (Amendments to IAS 40).</i>\r\n<p>If, in accordance with paragraph 84C, an entity reclassifies property at the date of initial application of the Amendments, has the entity disclosed the amounts reclassified to, or from, investment property in accordance with paragraph 84C?</p>\r\n<i>The entity shall disclose those amounts reclassified as part of the reconciliation of the carrying amount of investment property at the beginning and end of the period as required by paragraphs 76 and 79.</i>', '7.3', 'IAS 40.84C& 84E', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2740, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Investment Properties ~ Where the Fair Value Model has been Adopted</b>\r\n<p>Is the following information disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Carrying value at the beginning and end of the financial period;</li>\r\n    <li>Aggregate additions (showing separately additions arising from acquisitions, subsequent expenditure or as a result of a business combinations);</li>\r\n    <li>Assets re-classified as held for sale or included in a disposal group classified as held for sale in accordance with IFRS 5 and other disposals;</li>\r\n    <li>Net gains and losses from fair value adjustments;</li>\r\n    <li>Net exchange differences;</li>\r\n    <li>Transfers to and from inventories and owner-occupied properties (PPE); and</li>\r\n    <li>Other changes?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: Full corresponding amounts <b><u>need</u></b> to be disclosed.</p>\r\n<p>NB: Where in <b><u>exceptional circumstances</u></b> some assets are held at cost, then the above analysis would need to be given for assets held at fair value and assets held at cost.</p>', '<b>7.4</b>', 'IAS 40.76\r\n\r\nIAS 40.78', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2741, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where a valuation obtained for an investment property is adjusted significantly before being incorporated into the financial statements (e.g. to avoid the double-counting of assets that are recognised as separate assets) is there a reconciliation between the two figures, showing separately the aggregated amount of any recognised lease obligations that have been added back?', '7.5', 'IAS 40.77', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2742, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'In exceptional circumstances, where the entity has adopted the fair value model, however certain investment properties are carried at cost as their fair value cannot be established, have the following disclosures been given:-\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A description of the investment property;</li>\r\n    <li>An explanation of why fair value cannot be reliably measures;</li>\r\n    <li>(If possible) The range of estimates within which fair value is highly likely to lie; and</li>\r\n    <li>On disposal:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The fact that the entity has disposed of an investment property not carried at fair value;</li>\r\n            <li>The carrying value at the time of sale; and</li>\r\n            <li>The amount of gain or loss recognised?</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '7.6', 'IAS 40.78\r\n(a) to (d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2743, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where an entity capitalises a property interest held under an operating lease for the first time, then it is encouraged but not required to undertake a PYA <b><u>if the fair value of the property has been disclosed in the prior year financial statements</u></b> (this is a different treatment than that which is normally required by IAS 8), however, if in the above circumstances a PYA is not undertaken, has this fact been disclosed?', '7.7', 'IAS 40.80', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2744, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Investment Properties ~ Where the Cost Model has been Adopted</b>\r\n<p>Is the following reconciliation disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Aggregate cost at the beginning and end of the financial period;</li>\r\n    <li>Aggregate additions (showing separately additions arising from acquisition, subsequent expenditure or as a result of a business combinations);</li>\r\n    <li>Assets classified as held for sale or included in a disposal group as classified as held for sale in accordance with IFRS 5 or other disposals;</li>\r\n    <li>Transfers to and from inventories and owner-occupied properties (PPE);</li>\r\n    <li>Foreign exchange movements;</li>\r\n    <li>Other changes.</li>\r\n    <li>Aggregate cumulative depreciation / impairment losses at the beginning and end of the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Depreciation;</li>\r\n    <li>Impairment losses recognised in the profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Impairment losses or reversed in the profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>Any adjustments as a result of assets being classified as held for sale or included in a disposal group as classified as held for sale in accordance with IFRS 5 or other disposals;</li>\r\n    <li>Transfers to and from inventories and owner-occupied properties (PPE) due to change of usage;</li>\r\n    <li>Foreign exchange movements;</li>\r\n    <li>Other changes;</li>\r\n    <li>Net carrying amount at the beginning and end of the period?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: Full corresponding amounts <b><u>need</u></b> to be disclosed.</p>', '7.8', 'IAS 40.79 (c) to (d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2745, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where it is not possible to <b><u>disclose</u></b> the fair of investment properties carried at cost, are the following disclosures given:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A description of the investment property;</li>\r\n    <li>An explanation of why fair value cannot be reliably measures;</li>\r\n    <li>(If possible) The range of estimates within which fair value is highly likely to lie?</li>\r\n</ul>', '7.9', 'IAS 40.79\r\n(e) (i) to (iii)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2746, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Investments in Associates and Joint Ventures (Where Consolidated Financial Statements are Not Being Prepared)</b>', '<b>8</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2747, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'For each significant investment in a joint venture or associate are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Name;</li>\r\n    <li>The principal place of business (and country of incorporation, if different);</li>\r\n    <li>The holding company’s proportion of the ownership interest (and its proportion of the voting rights, if different) held in those investees?</li>\r\n</ul>', '8.1', 'IAS 27.17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2748, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Inventories</b>', '<b>9</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2749, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<p>Has the total carrying value of inventories been disclosed, have inventories been appropriately classified and a carrying value disclosed for each classification?</p>\r\n<p>NB: The key issue is that the classification of inventories must be appropriate to the entity. IAS 2 notes that the following are common classifications:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Merchandise;</li>\r\n    <li>Product supplies;</li>\r\n    <li>Materials;</li>\r\n    <li>Work in progress; and</li>\r\n    <li>Finished goods.</li>\r\n</ul>', '9.1', 'IAS 2.36 (b)\r\n\r\nIAS\r\n1.78\r\n(c)\r\n\r\nIAS 2.37', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2750, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the carrying value of inventories carried at fair value less cost to sell been disclosed?', '9.2', 'IAS 2.36\r\n(c )', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2751, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where stock has been pledged as security for liability, has the total carrying value of such items been disclosed?', '9.3', 'IAS 2.36\r\n(h)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2752, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Receivables</b>', '<b>10</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2753, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Are receivables analysed as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Amounts receivable from trade customers;</li>\r\n    <li>Receivable from related parties;</li>\r\n    <li>Prepayments; and</li>\r\n    <li>Other amounts?</li>\r\n</ul>', '10.1', 'IAS 1.78 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2754, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'When either party to a contract has performed, has the contract been presented in the statement of financial position as a contract asset or a contract liability, depending on the relationship between the entity’s performance and the customer’s payment? ', '10.2', 'IFRS\r\n15.\r\n105', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2755, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the entity disclosed any unconditional rights to consideration as a receivable? ', '10.3', 'IFRS 15. 105', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2756, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<p>IFRS 15 uses the terms ‘contract asset’ and ‘contract liability’ but does not prohibit an entity from using alternative descriptions in the statement of financial position for those items. </p>\r\n<p>If an entity uses an alternative description for a contract asset, has sufficient information been provided for a user of the financial statements to distinguish between receivables and contract assets?</p>', '10.4', 'IFRS 15. 109', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2757, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Deferred Tax Assets</b>\r\n<p>There are additional disclosures regarding deferred tax assets, however, to avoid duplication these have been in included in the ‘Provisions’ section of this checklist.</p>', '<b>11</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2758, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Cash and Cash Equivalents </b>', '<b>12</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2759, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where client money has been derecognised, is the total amount disclosed, and has the accounting policy adopted by the entity been disclosed?', '12.1', 'Best\r\nPractice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2760, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>IFRS 16 Leases</b>\r\n<p>IFRS 16 Leases is mandatory for accounting periods commencing on/after 1 January 2019. The disclosure requirements are more substantial than those previously required by IAS 17. </p>\r\n<p>The disclosures required under IFRS 16 have been listed below in this section, rather than split between the SCI, Statement of Financial Position and Accounting Policies sections of the Checklist. It is considered that, in the circumstances of the significant additional disclosures required, it is more straightforward to provide the disclosure requirements in one section.</p>\r\n<p>The disclosure requirements have been broken down as follows :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>13 – Entity is a lessee</li>\r\n    <li>14 – Entity is lessor: finance leases</li>\r\n    <li>15 – Entity is a lessor: operating leases</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><b>First time adoption of IFRS 16 will also require additional transitional disclosures; see question 5.2 of Section 8 – </b>“Accounting Policies and Estimation Techniques” <b>below. This will require completion of a supplementary checklist.</b> </p>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2761, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Entity is a Lessee</b>', '<b>13</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2762, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'A lessee shall disclose information about its leases for which it is a lessee in a single note or separate section in its financial statements. Has a separate note been presented which includes all of the appropriate information, including that detailed in the questions below? \r\n<p><i>NB: A lessee need not duplicate information that is already presented elsewhere in the financial statements, provided that the information is incorporated by cross-reference in the single note or separate section about leases.</i></p>', '13.1', 'IFRS 16.52', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2763, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has disclosure been given of the following amounts <b>relating to profit or loss and other comprehensive income</b>, in tabular format (unless another format is more appropriate):\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>depreciation charge for right-of-use assets by class of underlying asset (*);</li>\r\n    <li>interest expense on lease liabilities;</li>\r\n    <li>the expense relating to short-term leases where the recognition exemption (per paragraph 6 of IFRS 16) has been applied (NB: This expense need not include the expense relating to leases with a lease term of one month or less);</li>\r\n    <li>the expense relating to leases of low-value assets where the recognition exemption (per paragraph 6 of IFRS 16) has been applied (NB: This expense shall not include the expense relating to short-term leases of low-value assets included in paragraph (c) above);</li>\r\n    <li>the expense relating to variable lease payments not included in the measurement of lease liabilities;</li>\r\n    <li>income from subleasing right-of-use assets (*); and</li>\r\n    <li>gains or losses arising from sale and leaseback transactions?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><b>NB: if the right of use asset meets the definition of investment property, the disclosures marked (*) are not required to be given.</b></p>', '13.2', 'IFRS 16.53', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2764, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has disclosure been given of the following amounts <b>relating to the statement of cash flows</b>:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the total cash outflow for leases?</li>\r\n</ul>', '13.3', 'IFRS 16.53', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2765, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has disclosure been given of the following amounts <b>relating to the statement of financial position</b>:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Additions to right of use assets (*);</li>\r\n    <li>The carrying amount of right of use assets at the end of the reporting period, analysed by class of underlying asset (*); and</li>\r\n    <li>If the right of use assets are not shown separately in the statement of financial position, disclosure of which line items in the statement of financial position include the right of use assets?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><b>NB: if the right of use assets meet the definition of investment property, these should be presented as investment property and the disclosure requirements of IAS 40 should be applied. The disclosures marked (*) above are not required to be given in this instance.</b></p>', '13.4', 'IFRS 16.53\r\n\r\nIFRS 16.47\r\n\r\nIFRS 16.48', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2766, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has disclosure been given of the following amounts <b>relating to the statement of financial position</b>:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The lease liabilities; and</li>\r\n    <li>If the lease liabilities are not shown separately in the statement of financial position, disclosure of which line items in the statement of financial position include the lease liabilities?</li>\r\n</ul>', '13.5', 'IFRS 16.47', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2767, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<p>Has the entity provided a maturity analysis of lease liabilities, disclosed separately from the maturity of other financial liabilities? </p>\r\n<p><b><i>NB: IFRS 16 does not mandate the time bands for the maturity analysis; instead, reference is made to IFRS 7 which suggests the entity uses judgement to determine an appropriate number of time bands.</i></b></p>', '13.6', 'IFRS 16.58', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2768, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<p>If the entity has taken advantage of the exemption to not apply the IFRS 16 recognition principles to short-term leases, has it disclosed that fact? </p>\r\n<p><b><i>NB: a short-term lease is a lease with a term of 12 months or less from the commencement date.</i></b></p>', '13.7', 'IFRS 16.60', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2769, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If the portfolio of short-term leases to which the entity is committed at the end of the reporting period is dissimilar to the portfolio of short-term leases to which the current short-term-leases expense relates, is there disclosure of the lease commitments for short-term leases for which the exemption referred to above has been applied? ', '13.8', 'IFRS 16.55', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2770, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If the entity has taken advantage of the exemption to not apply the IFRS 16 recognition principles to leases of low-value assets, has it disclosed that fact?\r\n<p><b><i>NB: the “low value” criteria is an absolute criteria, based on the underlying asset having a value, when new, of US$5,000 or less. Materiality does not come into the equation.</i></b></p>', '13.9', 'IFRS 16.60', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2771, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where necessary to meet the objective of providing users of the financial statements with sufficient information to assess the effect that leases have on the financial position, financial performance and cash flows of the lessee, has additional qualitative and quantitative information been disclosed? \r\n<p>This may include the following: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the nature of the lessee’s leasing activities;</li>\r\n    <li>future cash outflows to which the lessee is potentially exposed that are not reflected in the measurement of lease liabilities. This includes exposure arising from:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>variable lease payments;</li>\r\n            <li>extension options and termination options;</li>\r\n            <li>residual value guarantees; and</li>\r\n            <li>leases not yet commenced to which the lessee is committed.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>restrictions or covenants imposed by leases; and</li>\r\n    <li>sale and leaseback transactions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><b>Additional guidance is available in IFRS 16 B48 to B52</b></p>', '13.10', 'IFRS 16.59', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2772, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Entity is a Lessor: Finance Leases</b>', '<b>14</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2773, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has disclosure been given of the following, in tabular format (unless another format is more appropriate):\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>selling profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>finance income on the net investment in the lease; and</li>\r\n    <li>income relating to variable lease payments not included in the measurement of the net investment in the lease?</li>\r\n</ul>', '14.1', 'IFRS16.9016.91', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2774, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has a qualitative and quantitative explanation of the significant changes in the carrying amount of the net investment in finance leases been given? ', '14.2', 'IFRS16.93', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2775, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is there a maturity analysis of lease payments receivable, which shows the undiscounted lease payments to be received on an annual basis for a minimum of each of the first five years and a total of the amounts for the remaining years?', '14.3', 'IFRS16.94', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2776, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has a reconciliation between the undiscounted lease payments and the net investment in the lease been given?\r\n<p><i>NB: this reconciliation shall identify the unearned finance income relating to the lease payments receivable and any discounted unguaranteed residual value.</i></p>', '14.4', 'IFRS16.94', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2777, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Entity is a Lessor: Operating Leases</b>', '<b>15</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2778, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is there disclosure of lease income, analysed as follows: \r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Income relating to variable lease payments that do not depend on an index or a rate; and</li>\r\n    <li>Other lease income?</li>\r\n</ul>', '15.1', 'IFRS16.90', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2779, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is there a maturity analysis of lease payments receivable, which shows the undiscounted lease payments to be received on an annual basis for a minimum of each of the first five years and a total of the amounts for the remaining years?', '15.2', 'IFRS16.97', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2780, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'For items of property, plant and equipment subject to an operating lease, the disclosure requirements of IAS 16 shall be applied. \r\n<p>In applying the disclosure requirements in IAS 16, have the disclosures been provided separately for assets subject to an operating lease (by class of underlying asset) from those owned assets held and used by the lessor?</p>', '15.3', 'IFRS16.95', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2781, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where applicable, have the disclosure requirements of IAS 36 <i>Impairment of Assets</i>, IAS 38 <i>Intangible Assets</i>, IAS 40 <i>Investment Property</i> or IAS 41 <i>Agriculture</i> been complied with?', '15.4', 'IFRS16.96', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2782, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Entity is a Lessor: Additional disclosures relevant to both finance and operating leases</b>', '<b>16</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2783, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where necessary to meet the objective of providing users of the financial statements with sufficient information to assess the effect that leases have on the financial position, financial performance and cash flows of the lessor, has additional qualitative and quantitative information been disclosed?\r\n<p>This may include the following: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the nature of the lessor’s leasing activities; and</li>\r\n    <li>how the lessor manages the risk associated with any rights it retains in underlying assets. In particular, a lessor shall disclose its risk management strategy for the rights it retains in underlying assets, including any means by which the lessor reduces that risk.</li>\r\n</ul>', '16.1', 'IFRS16.92', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2784, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Creditors Regarding a Dividend in Specie</b>', '<b>17</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2785, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the carrying amount of the dividend payable at the beginning and end of the period; and</li>\r\n    <li>the increase or decrease in the carrying amount recognised in the period in accordance with IFRIC 17, paragraph 13 as result of a change in the fair value of the assets to be distributed?</li>\r\n</ul>', '17.1', 'IFRIC \r\n16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2786, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Service Concession Arrangements</b>', '<b>18</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2787, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'All aspects of a service concession arrangement shall be considered in determining the appropriate disclosures in the notes.\r\n<p>An operator and a grantor shall disclose the following in each period: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>a description of the arrangement;</li>\r\n    <li>significant terms of the arrangement that may affect the amount, timing and certainty of future cash flows (e.g. the period of the concession, re-pricing dates and the basis upon which re-pricing or re-negotiation is determined);</li>\r\n    <li>the nature and extent (e.g. quantity, time period or amount as appropriate) of: \r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>rights to use specified assets;</li>\r\n            <li>obligations to provide, or rights to expect, provision of services;</li>\r\n            <li>obligations to acquire or build items of property, plant and equipment;</li>\r\n            <li>obligations to deliver or rights to receive specified assets at the end of the concession period;</li>\r\n            <li>renewal and termination options; and</li>\r\n            <li>other rights and obligations (e.g. major overhauls);</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>changes in the arrangement occurring during the period; and</li>\r\n    <li>how the service arrangement has been classified?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: These disclosures need to be provided individually for each service concession arrangement, or in aggregate for each class of service concession arrangements.</p>', '18.1', 'SIC 29 6, 7', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2788, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Service Concession Arrangements</b>', '<b>19</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2789, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If the entity is an operator, has it disclosed the amount of revenue and profits or losses recognised in the period on exchanging construction services for a financial asset or an intangible asset?', '19.1', 'SIC 29.6A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2790, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Provisions for Liabilities</b>', '<b>20</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2791, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Are Provisions analysed as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Provisions for employee benefits</li>\r\n    <li>Other items.</li>\r\n</ul>', '20.1', 'IAS 1.78(d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2792, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'For each class of provision are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The carrying amount at the beginning and end of the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Additional provisions made in the period, including increases to existing provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>Amounts used (i.e. incurred and charged against the provision) during the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Unused amounts reversed during the period; and</li>\r\n    <li>The increase during the period in the discounted amount arising from the passage of time and the effective change in the discount rate?</li>\r\n</ul>', '20.2', 'IAS 37.85\r\n(a) to (e)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2793, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is the following disclosed for each class of provision:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A brief description of the nature of the obligation;</li>\r\n    <li>The expected amount and timing of any resulting payments;</li>\r\n    <li>An indication of uncertainties about the amount or timing of those outflows; </li>\r\n    <li>(Where necessary to provide adequate information) the major assumptions made concerning future events; and</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of any expected reimbursements, stating the amount of any asset that has been recognised for that expected reimbursement?</li>\r\n</ul>', '20.3', 'IAS 37.85\r\n(a) to (c)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2794, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'The disclosure requirements of 20.3 do not have to be complied with if deemed to be seriously prejudicial (unless required by statute, which some of them are):\r\n<p>If advantage is taken of this exemption, are the following disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the general nature of the dispute; </li>\r\n    <li>the fact that full disclosure has not been given, and</li>\r\n    <li>the reason why the required information has not been given?</li>\r\n</ul>', '20.4', 'IAS 37.92', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2795, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Deferred Tax (Liabilities and Assets)</b>', '<b>21</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2796, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the amount of any deferred tax asset been disclosed together with the nature of the evidence to supporting its recognition, when:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The utilization of the deferred tax assets is dependent on future taxable profits in excess of the profits arising from the reversal of existing taxable temporary differences; and</li>\r\n    <li>The entity has suffered a loss in either the current or preceding period in the tax jurisdiction to which the deferred tax asset relates?</li>\r\n</ul>', '21.1', 'IAS 12\r\n82', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2797, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If, as a result of a business combination, the parent entity has changed the amount recognized for its pre-acquisition deferred tax asset, has the amount of the change been disclosed?', '21.2', 'IAS 12\r\n81 (j)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2798, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'In respect of each type of temporary difference, and in respect of each type of unused tax losses and unused tax credits are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The amount of deferred tax assets and liabilities recognised in the Statement of Financial Position for each period presented; and</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of the deferred tax income or expense recognized in profit or loss, if this is not apparent from the changes in the amounts recognized in the Statement of Financial Position?</li>\r\n</ul>', '21.3', 'IAS 12\r\n81 (g)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2799, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'In some jurisdictions the payment of dividends can augment or reduce the tax charge payable by the company, where this occurs, has the following been disclosed: \r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature of potential tax consequences for a company that would result from the payment of dividends to its shareholders; and</li>\r\n    <li>Quantification of these consequences where practicable, determinable, or noted where they are none?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: Specific disclosure is needed regarding the effects of any dividends that were proposed or declared before the financial statements were authorized for issue, but are not recognized as a liability.</p>', '21.4', 'IAS 12\r\n82A\r\n\r\nIAS 12\r\n81 (i)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2800, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Equity Capital and Reserves</b>', '<b>22</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2801, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Is Equity Capital and Reserves analysed as follows:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Paid-In Capital;</li>\r\n    <li>Share Premium;</li>\r\n    <li>Reserves?</li>\r\n</ul>', '22.1', 'IAS 1.78\r\n(e)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2802, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'For each reserve within equity, has a description of it nature and purpose been disclosed?', '22.2', 'IAS 1.79B', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2803, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has a separate revaluation reserve been shown in equity where items of PPE have been revalued, also have any restrictions on the distribution of the PPE revaluation reserve to shareholders been disclosed?', '22.3', 'IAS 16.40\r\n16.77 (f)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2804, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the amount of the revaluation surplus that relates to intangible assets at the beginning and the end of the period been disclosed, indicating the changes during the period and any restriction on the distribution of the balance to shareholders?', '22.4', 'IAS 38.124 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2805, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the cumulative income or expense recognized in OCI relating to a non-current asset (or disposal group) classified as held for sale been disclosed?', '22.5', 'IFRS 5.38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2806, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Share Capital</b>\r\n<p>It is necessary to understand the key terminology:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Authorised Share Capital = The maximum shares that a company can have;</li>\r\n    <li>Issued Shares = The number of shares in existence;</li>\r\n    <li>Allotted Shares = The number of shares allocated to shareholders;</li>\r\n    <li>Called-Up Shares = Shares where payment has been requested;</li>\r\n    <li>Paid-Up Shares = Payment has been received.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>23</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2807, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Have the following been disclosed for each class of share capital:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The number of authorised shares;</li>\r\n    <li>The number of shares issued and fully paid;</li>\r\n    <li>The number of shares issued and not fully paid;</li>\r\n    <li>A reconciliation of the number of shares outstanding at the beginning and end of the reporting period;</li>\r\n    <li>The rights, preferences and restrictions attaching to that class including: restrictions on the distribution of dividends and the repayment of capital; and</li>\r\n    <li>Shares in the entity held by the entity or by its subsidiaries or associates; and share reserved for issue under options and contracts for sale of shares, including terms and amounts?</li>\r\n</ul>', '23.1', 'IAS 1.79\r\n(a)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2808, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If the entity has no share capital, has information equivalent to that noted in 23.1 been disclosed?  This must show changes during the period in each category of equity interest, and rights, preference and restriction attaching to each category of equity instrument.', '23.2', 'IAS 1.80', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2809, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If an entity has reclassified:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A puttable financial instrument classified as an equity instrument; or</li>\r\n    <li>An instrument that imposes on the entity an obligation to deliver to another party a pro rata share of the net assets of the equity only on liquidation and is classified as an equity instrument;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>between financial liabilities and equity, has it been disclosed the amount reclassified into and out of each category, and the timing and reason for that reclassification?</p>', '23.3', 'IAS 1.80A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2810, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If an entity has puttable financial instruments classified as equity, have the following disclosures been given (unless provided elsewhere):\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Summary quantitative data about the amount classified as equity;</li>\r\n    <li>The entity’s objectives, policies and processes for managing its obligations to repurchase or redeem the instrument when required to do so by the instrument holders, including any changes from previous period;</li>\r\n    <li>The expected cash outflow on redemption or repurchase of that class of financial instrument; and</li>\r\n    <li>Information about how the expected cash outflow on redemption or repurchase will be determined?</li>\r\n</ul>', '23.4', 'IAS 1.136A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2811, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Financial Instruments</b>\r\n<p>Disclosures relating to financial instruments affect receivables, payables, investments, bank and cash, and equity.  Rather than trying to lace these requirements into the specific Statement of Financial Position areas noted above and potentially having to repeat disclosures in this checklist on a number of occasions, the requirements of IFRS 7 <i>Financial Instruments: Disclosures</i> have been noted below.  </p>\r\n<p>IFRS 9 <i>Financial Instruments</i> became mandatory for accounting periods commencing on/after 1 January 2018. Whilst IFRS 9 itself does not contain any disclosure requirements, it contains a number of changes to classification and measurement compared to IAS 39. </p>\r\n<p>Reference should be made to Appendix B of IFRS 7 to assist with the disclosure requirements set out below.</p>', '<b>24</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2812, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Classification of Financial Instruments</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2813, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Does either the Statement of Financial Position or the notes disclose the carrying value of the following classifications of financial instruments:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>financial assets measured at fair value through profit or loss, showing separately:\r\n        <ol type=\"i\">\r\n            <li>those designated as such upon initial recognition or subsequently in accordance with paragraph 6.7.1 of IFRS 9; and </li>\r\n            <li>those mandatorily measured at fair value through profit or loss in accordance with IFRS 9;</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>financial assets measured at amortised cost;</li>\r\n    <li>financial assets measured at fair value through other comprehensive income, showing separately:\r\n        <ol type=\"i\">\r\n            <li>financial assets that are measured at fair value through other comprehensive income in accordance with paragraph 4.1.2A of IFRS 9; and</li>\r\n            <li>investments in equity instruments designated as such upon initial recognition in accordance with paragraph 5.7.5 of IFRS 9;</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>financial liabilities at fair value through profit or loss, showing separately:\r\n        <ol type=\"i\">\r\n            <li>those designated as such upon initial recognition or subsequently in accordance with paragraph 6.7.1 of IFRS 9; and</li>\r\n            <li>those that meet the definition of held for trading in IFRS 9.</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>financial liabilities measured at amortised cost?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.1', 'IFRS 7.8', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2814, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Financial assets or financial liabilities at fair value through profit or loss</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c3` (`acID`, `c3tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `drps`, `crps`, `drfp`, `crfp`, `issue`, `recommendation`, `result`, `yesno`, `comment`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(2815, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If the entity has designated a financial asset (or group of financial assets) as measured at fair value through profit or loss that would otherwise be measured at fair value through other comprehensive income or amortised cost, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The maximum exposure to credit risk (see IFRS 7, paragraph 36 (a)) at the end of the reporting period;</li>\r\n    <li>The amount by which any related credit derivatives or similar instruments mitigate that maximum exposure to credit risk;</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of change, during the period and cumulatively, in the fair value that is attributable to changes in the credit risk of the financial asset determined either:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>As the amount of change in its fair value that is not attributable to changes in market conditions that give rise to market risk; or</li>\r\n            <li>Using an alternative method which the entity believes more faithfully represents the amount of change in its fair value that is attributable to changes in credit risk of the asset;</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>The amount of the change in the fair value of any related credit derivatives or similar instruments that has occurred during the period and cumulatively since the financial asset was designated?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.2', 'IFRS 7.9 ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2816, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where an entity has designated a financial liability as at fair value through profit or loss in accordance with IFRS 9.4.2.2 and is required to present the effects of changes in that liability’s credit risk in other comprehensive income (see paragraph 5.7.7 of IFRS 9), have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The amount of change, cumulatively, in the fair value of the financial liability that is attributable to changes in the credit risk;</li>\r\n    <li>The difference between the carrying amount of the financial liability and the amount the entity would be contractually required to pay at maturity to the holder of the obligation;</li>\r\n    <li>Any transfers of the cumulative gain or loss within equity during the period including the reason for such transfers; and</li>\r\n    <li>If a liability is derecognised during the period, the amount (if any) presented in other comprehensive income that was realised at derecognition?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.3', 'IFRS 7.10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2817, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If the entity has designated a financial liability as at fair value through profit or loss in accordance with paragraph 4.2.2 of IFRS 9 and is required to present all changes in the fair value of that liability (including the effects of changes in the credit risk of the liability) in profit or loss (see paragraphs 5.7.7 and 5.7.8 of IFRS 9), have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the amount of change, during the period and cumulatively, in the fair value of the financial liability that is attributable to changes in the credit risk of that liability (see paragraphs B5.7.13–B5.7.20 of IFRS 9 for guidance on determining the effects of changes in a liability’s credit risk); and</li>\r\n    <li>the difference between the financial liability’s carrying amount and the amount the entity would be contractually required to pay at maturity to the holder of the obligation? </li>\r\n</ul>', '24.4', 'IFRS 7.10A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2818, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>a detailed description of the methods used to calculate the change in fair value as required by IFRS 7, paragraphs 9(c), 10(a), 10A(a) and IFRS 9.5.7.7(a), including an explanation of why the method is appropriate;</li>\r\n    <li>if the entity believes that the disclosures given do not faithfully represent the change in the fair value attributable to changes in its credit risk, the reasons for reaching this conclusion and the factors it believes are relevant;</li>\r\n    <li>a detailed description of the methodology or methodologies used to determine whether presenting the effects of changes in a liability’s credit risk in other comprehensive income would create or enlarge an accounting mismatch in profit or loss (see paragraphs 5.7.7 and 5.7.8 of IFRS 9). If an entity is required to present the effects of changes in a liability’s credit risk in profit or loss (see paragraph 5.7.8 of IFRS 9), the disclosure must include a detailed description of the economic relationship described in paragraph B5.7.6 of IFRS 9?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.5', 'IFRS 7.11', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2819, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If the entity has designated investments in equity instruments to be measured at fair value through other comprehensive income, as permitted by paragraph 5.7.5 of IFRS 9, has the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>which investments in equity instruments have been designated to be measured at fair value through other comprehensive income;</li>\r\n    <li>the reasons for using this presentation alternative;</li>\r\n    <li>the fair value of each such investment at the end of the reporting period;</li>\r\n    <li>dividends recognised during the period, showing separately those related to investments derecognised during the reporting period and those related to investments held at the end of the reporting period; and</li>\r\n    <li>any transfers of the cumulative gain or loss within equity during the period including the reason for such transfers?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.6', 'IFRS 7.11A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2820, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If an entity derecognised investments in equity instruments measured at fair value through other comprehensive income during the reporting period, has it disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the reasons for disposing of the investments;</li>\r\n    <li>the fair value of the investments at the date of derecognition; and</li>\r\n    <li>the cumulative gain or loss on disposal?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.7', 'IFRS 7.11B', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2821, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Reclassifications of financial assets</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2822, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If, in the current or previous reporting periods, the entity has reclassified any financial assets in accordance with paragraph 4.4.1 of IFRS 9, has it disclosed that fact? \r\n<p>For each such event, has the following also been disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the date of reclassification;</li>\r\n    <li>a detailed explanation of the change in business model and a qualitative description of its effect on the entity’s financial statements; and</li>\r\n    <li>the amount reclassified into and out of each category?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.8', 'IFRS 7.12B', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2823, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If financial assets have been reclassified out of the FVTPL category to amortised cost or FVOCI, have the following been disclosed (until derecognition):\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the effective interest rate determined on the date of reclassification; and</li>\r\n    <li>the interest revenue recognised?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.9', 'IFRS 7.12C', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2824, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If, since its last annual reporting date, financial assets have been reclassified out of the FVOCI category so that they are measured at amortised cost or out of the FVTPL category so that they are measured at amortised cost or FVOCI, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the fair value of the financial assets at the end of the reporting period; and</li>\r\n    <li>the fair value gain or loss that would have been recognised in profit or loss or other comprehensive income during the reporting period if the financial assets had not been reclassified?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.10', 'IFRS 7.12D', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2825, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Off-setting of Financial Instruments</b>\r\n<p>Where offsetting of financial assets and financial liabilities in accordance with IAS 32, paragraph 42 the following disclosures need to be given. </p>\r\n<p>NB: These disclosures also apply to recognised financial instruments that are subject to an enforceable master netting off arrangment or similar agreement, irrespecive of whether they are set of in accordance with IAS 32, paragraph 42.</p>', '', 'IFRS 7.13A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2826, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has information been disclosed which allows the effect or potential effect of netting off arrangements on the entity’s financial position to be clear?\r\n<p>To faciliate this, the following specific disclosures should be given, in tabular format (unless another format is more appropriate:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>The gross amount of those recognised financial assets and recognised financial liabilities;</li>\r\n    <li>The amounts that are set-off in accordance with the criteria in IAS 32, paragraph 42 when determining the net amounts presented in the Statement of Financial Position;</li>\r\n    <li>The net amounts presented;</li>\r\n    <li>The amounts subject to an enforceable master netting arrangment or similar agreement that are not otherwise included in b, including:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Amounts related to recognised financial instruments that do not meet some or all of the offsetting criteria in IAS 32, paragraph 42; and</li>\r\n            <li>Amounts related to financial collateral (including cash collateral);</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>The amount after deducting the amount in d from the amounts in c?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>The total amount disclosed in accordance with d. for an instrument shall be limited to the amount in c. for that instrument.</p>\r\n<p>Regarding d the nature of those rights need to be disclosed. </p>\r\n<p>If the information required to be disclosed by IFRS 7 13B to 13E is disclosed in more than one note, then a cross reference must be included.</p>', '', 'IFRS 7.13 B,C\r\n\r\nD\r\n\r\nE\r\n\r\nF', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2827, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Collateral</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2828, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The carrying amount of financial assets that the entity has pledged as collateral for liabilities or contingent liabilities, including amounts that have been reclassified in accordance with IFRS 9.3.3.23(a), and</li>\r\n    <li>The terms and conditions relating to its pledge?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.12', 'IFRS 7.14', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2829, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where an entity holds collateral (of financial or non-financial assets) and is permitted to sell or repledge the collateral in the absence of default by the owner of the collateral, is the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The fair value of the collateral held;</li>\r\n    <li>The fair value of any such collateral sold or repledged, and whether the entity has an obligation to return it; and</li>\r\n    <li>The terms and conditions associated with its use of the collateral?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.13', 'IFRS 7.15', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2830, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Allowance Account for Credit Losses</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2831, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<p>The carrying amount of financial assets measured at FVOCI in accordance with paragraph 4.1.2A of IFRS 9 is not reduced by a loss allowance and an entity shall not present the loss allowance separately in the statement of financial position as a reduction of the carrying amount of the financial asset. </p>\r\n<p>However, an entity shall disclose the loss allowance in the notes to the financial statements. Has this disclosure been given?</p>', '24.14', 'IFRS\r\n7.16A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2832, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Compound Financial Instruments with Multiple Embedded Derivatives</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2833, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where compound instruments exist, and the instrument has mutliple embedded derivatives whose values are interdependent (such as callable convertible debt instruments), has the existence of these features been disclosed?', '24.15', 'IFRS \r\n7.17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2834, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Defaults and Breaches</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2835, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'For loans payable recognised at the end of the reporting period, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Details of any defaults during the period of principal, interest, sinking fund, or redemption terms of those loans;</li>\r\n    <li>The carrying amount of the loans payable in default at the end of the reporting period;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether the default was remedied, or the terms of the loans were renegotiated, before the financial statements were authorised for issue?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.16', 'IFRS \r\n7.18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2836, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If, during the period, there were breaches of loan agreement terms other than those covered by IFRS 7.18, has the entity disclosed the informaiton required by IFRS 7, paragraph 18 if those breaches permitted the lender to demand accelerated repayment (unless the breaches were remedied, or the terms of the loan were renegotiated, on or before the end of the reporting period)?', '24.17', 'IFRS \r\n7.19', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2837, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Except as set out in IFRS 7, paragraph 29, for each class of financial assets and financial liabilities, has their fair value been disclosed in a way that permits it to be compared with their carrying amounts?\r\n<p>NB: Offsetting is only allowed to the extent that carrying amounts are offset in the Statement of Financial Position.</p>', '24.18', 'IFRS \r\n7.25,26\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2838, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where a gain or loss on intial recognition of a financial asset or liability has not been recognsied because the fair value is neither evidenced by a quoted price in an active market for an identical asset or liability (i.e. a level 1 input), nor based on a valuation technique that uses only data from observable markets, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The accounting policy for recognising in profit or loss the difference between the fair value at initial recognition and the transaction price to reflect a change in factors (including time) that market participants would take into account when pricing the asset or liability (see IFRS 9.B5.1.2A(b));</li>\r\n    <li>The aggregate difference yet to be recognised in profit or loss at the beginning and end of the period and a reconciliation of changes in the balance of this difference;</li>\r\n    <li>Why the entity concluded that the transaction price was not the best evidence of fair value, including a description of the evidence that supports the fair value?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.19', 'IFRS\r\n7.28\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2839, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Disclosure of fair values are <b><u>not</u></b> required in the following circumstances:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>When the carrying amount is a reasonable approximation of fair value, for example, for financial instruments such as short-term trade receivables and payables; or</li>\r\n    <li>For a contract containing a discretionary participation feature (as described in IFRS 4), if the fair value of that feature cannot be measured reliably; or</li>\r\n    <li>For lease liabilities.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>However, in the case of b above, have disclosures been given to allow readers of the financial statements to make their own judgements about the extext of possible differences between the carrying amount of those contracts and their fair value, including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The fact that fair value information has not been disclosed for these instruments because their fair value cannot be measured reliably;</li>\r\n    <li>A description of the financial instruments, their carrying amount, and an explanation of why fair value cannot be measured reliably;</li>\r\n    <li>Information about the market for the instruments;</li>\r\n    <li>Information about whether and how the entity intends to dispose of the financial instruments; and</li>\r\n    <li>If financial instruments whose fair value previously could not be reliably measured are derecognised, that fact, their carrying amount at the time of derecognition, and the amount of gain or loss recognised?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.20', 'IFRS\r\n7.29\r\n\r\nIFRS 7.30\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2840, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Nature and Extent of Risks Arising from Financial Instruments</b> <br>Information (qualitative and quantitative) should be disclosed that enables users of the financial statements to evaluate the nature and extent of risks arising from financial instruments to which the entity is exposed at the end of the reporting period.  Risks typically include but are not limited to credit risk, liquidity risk and market risk.', '', 'IFRS\r\n7.31,32, 32A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2841, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Qualitative Disclosures</b> ~ <b><u>For each</u></b> type of risk arising from financial instruments, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The exposure to risk and how they arise;</li>\r\n    <li>The entity’s objectives, policies and processes for managing the risk and the methods used to measure the risk; and </li>\r\n    <li>Changes in the above from the previous period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.21', 'IFRS\r\n7.33', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2842, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Qualitative Disclosures</b> ~ <b><u>For each</u></b> type of risk arising from financial instruments, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>Summary quantitiative data about its exposure to that risk at the end of the reporting period.  This shall be based on the information presented internally to key management; and</li>\r\n    <li>The concentrations of risk, if not apparent from other disclosures made?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Concentrations of risk arise from financial instruments that have similar characteristics and are affected similarly by changes in economic or other conditions. The identification of concentrations of risk requires judgement taking into account the circumstances of the entity. Disclosure of concentrations of risk shall include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>description of how management determines concentrations;</li>\r\n    <li>a description of the shared characteristic that identifies each concentration (eg counterparty, geographical area, currency or market); and</li>\r\n    <li>the amount of the risk exposure associated with all financial instruments sharing that characteristic.</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.22', 'IFRS\r\n7.34', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2843, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If the quantitative disclosures as at the reporting date are unrepresentative of an entity’s exposure to risk during the period, has the entity provided further information that is representative?', '24.23', 'IFRS\r\n7.35', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2844, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'The disclosure requirements in IFRS 7 paragraphs 35F–35N shall be applied to financial instruments to which the impairment requirements in IFRS 9 are applied. \r\n<p>These disclosures shall enable users of financial statements to understand the effect of credit risk on the amount, timing and uncertainty of future cash flows. To achieve this objective, have the following disclosures been provided:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>information about an entity’s credit risk management practices and how they relate to the recognition and measurement of expected credit losses, including the methods, assumptions and information used to measure expected credit losses;</li>\r\n    <li>quantitative and qualitative information that allows users of financial statements to evaluate the amounts in the financial statements arising from expected credit losses, including changes in the amount of expected credit losses and the reasons for those changes; and</li>\r\n    <li>information about an entity’s credit risk exposure (ie the credit risk inherent in an entity’s financial assets and commitments to extend credit) including significant credit risk concentrations?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: the entity need not duplicate information already presented elsewhere, provided that appropriate cross references are given.</p>', '24.24', 'IFRS\r\n7.35A\r\n7.35B\r\n7.35C', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2845, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has an explantion been given of the entity’s credit risk management practices and how they relate to the recognition and measurement of expected credit losses? \r\n<p>To meet this objective an entity shall disclose information that enables users of financial statements to understand and evaluate:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>how an entity determined whether the credit risk of financial instruments has increased significantly since initial recognition, including, if and how:\r\n        <ol type=\"i\">\r\n            <li>financial instruments are considered to have low credit risk in accordance with paragraph 5.5.10 of IFRS 9, including the classes of financial instruments to which it applies; and</li>\r\n            <li>the presumption in paragraph 5.5.11 of IFRS 9, that there have been significant increases in credit risk since initial recognition when financial assets are more than 30 days past due, has been rebutted;</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>an entity’s definitions of default, including the reasons for selecting those definitions;</li>\r\n    <li>ow the instruments were grouped if expected credit losses were measured on a collective basis;</li>\r\n    <li>how an entity determined that financial assets are credit-impaired financial assets;</li>\r\n    <li>an entity’s write-off policy, including the indicators that there is no reasonable expectation of recovery and information about the policy for financial assets that are written-off but are still subject to enforcement activity; and</li>\r\n    <li>how the requirements in paragraph 5.5.12 of IFRS 9 for the modification of contractual cash flows of financial assets have been applied, including how an entity:\r\n        <ol type=\"i\">\r\n            <li>determines whether the credit risk on a financial asset that has been modified while the loss allowance was measured at an amount equal to lifetime expected credit losses, has improved to the extent that the loss allowance reverts to being measured at an amount equal to 12-month expected credit losses in accordance with paragraph 5.5.5 of IFRS 9; and</li>\r\n            <li>monitors the extent to which the loss allowance on financial assets meeting the criteria in (i) is subsequently remeasured at an amount equal to lifetime expected credit losses in accordance with paragraph 5.5.3 of IFRS 9?</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ol>', '24.25', 'IFRS 7.35F', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2846, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'To provide an explanation of the inputs, assumptions and estimation techniques used to apply the requirements in Section 5.5 of IFRS 9, are the following disclosed:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>the basis of inputs and assumptions and the estimation techniques used to:\r\n        <ol type=\"i\">\r\n            <li>measure the 12-month and lifetime expected credit losses;</li>\r\n            <li>determine whether the credit risk of financial instruments has increased significantly since initial recognition; and</li>\r\n            <li>determine whether a financial asset is a credit-impaired financial asset.</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>how forward-looking information has been incorporated into the determination of expected credit losses, including the use of macroeconomic information; and</li>\r\n    <li>changes in the estimation techniques or significant assumptions made during the reporting period and the reasons for those changes?</li>\r\n</ol>', '24.26', 'IFRS 7.35G', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2847, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Quantitative and qualitative information about amounts arising from expected credit losses</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2848, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'To explain the changes in the loss allowance and the reasons for those changes, has a reconciliation from the opening balance to the closing balance of the loss allowance been given <b><u>for each class of financial instrument</u></b>?\r\n<p>This reconciliation should be presented as a table, showing separately the changes during the period for:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>the loss allowance measured at an amount equal to 12-month expected credit losses;</li>\r\n    <li>the loss allowance measured at an amount equal to lifetime expected credit losses for:\r\n        <ol type=\"i\">\r\n            <li>financial instruments for which credit risk has increased significantly since initial recognition but that are not credit-impaired financial assets;</li>\r\n            <li>financial assets that are credit-impaired at the reporting date (but that are not purchased or originated credit-impaired); and</li>\r\n            <li>trade receivables, contract assets or lease receivables for which the loss allowances are measured in accordance with paragraph 5.5.15 of IFRS 9.</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>financial assets that are purchased or originated credit-impaired. In addition to the reconciliation, an entity shall disclose the total amount of undiscounted expected credit losses at initial recognition on financial assets initially recognised during the reporting period.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><i>For loan commitments and financial guarantee contracts the loss allowance is recognised as a provision. An entity should disclose information about the changes in the loss allowance for financial assets separately from those for loan commitments and financial guarantee contracts. However, if a financial instrument includes both a loan (ie financial asset) and an undrawn commitment (ie loan commitment) component and the entity cannot separately identify the expected credit losses on the loan commitment component from those on the financial asset component, the expected credit losses on the loan commitment should be recognised together with the loss allowance for the financial asset. To the extent that the combined expected credit losses exceed the gross carrying amount of the financial asset, the expected credit losses should be recognised as a provision.</i></p>', '24.27', 'IFRS 7.35H', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2849, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'To enable users of financial statements to understand the changes in the loss allowance disclosed in accordance with paragraph 35H, has an explanation been provided of how significant changes in the gross carrying amount of financial instruments during the period contributed to changes in the loss allowance?\r\n<p><i>The information shall be provided separately for financial instruments that represent the loss allowance as listed in paragraph 35H(a)–(c) and shall include relevant qualitative and quantitative information.</i></p>\r\n<p><i>Examples of changes in the gross carrying amount of financial instruments that contributed to the changes in the loss allowance may include:</i></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><i>changes because of financial instruments originated or acquired during the reporting period;</i></li>\r\n    <li><i>the modification of contractual cash flows on financial assets that do not result in a derecognition of those financial assets in accordance with IFRS 9;</i></li>\r\n    <li><i>changes because of financial instruments that were derecognised (including those that were written-off) during the reporting period; and</i></li>\r\n    <li><i>changes arising from whether the loss allowance is measured at an amount equal to 12-month or lifetime expected credit losses.</i></li>\r\n</ul>', '24.28', 'IFRS 7.35I', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2850, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'To enable users of financial statements to understand the nature and effect of modifications of contractual cash flows on financial assets that have not resulted in derecognition and the effect of such modifications on the measurement of expected credit losses, has the following been disclosed:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>the amortised cost before the modification and the net modification gain or loss recognised for financial assets for which the contractual cash flows have been modified during the reporting period while they had a loss allowance measured at an amount equal to lifetime expected credit losses; and</li>\r\n    <li>the gross carrying amount at the end of the reporting period of financial assets that have been modified since initial recognition at a time when the loss allowance was measured at an amount equal to lifetime expected credit losses and for which the loss allowance has changed during the reporting period to an amount equal to 12-month expected credit losses?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><i>Paragraph (a) above applies to those trade receivables, contract assets or lease receivables on which lifetime expected credit losses are recognised in accordance with paragraph 5.5.15 of IFRS 9, if those financial assets are modified while more than 30 days past due.</i></p>\r\n', '24.29', 'IFRS 7.35J\r\n\r\nIFRS 7. 35A(a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2851, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'To enable users of financial statements to understand the effect of collateral and other credit enhancements on the amounts arising from expected credit losses, by class of financial instrument, has the following been disclosed:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>the amount that best represents its maximum exposure to credit risk at the end of the reporting period without taking account of any collateral held or other credit enhancements (eg netting agreements that do not qualify for offset in accordance with IAS 32).</li>\r\n    <li>a narrative description of collateral held as security and other credit enhancements, including:\r\n        <ol type=\"i\">\r\n            <li>a description of the nature and quality of the collateral held;</li>\r\n            <li>an explanation of any significant changes in the quality of that collateral or credit enhancements as a result of deterioration or changes in the collateral policies of the entity during the reporting period; and</li>\r\n            <li>information about financial instruments for which an entity has not recognised a loss allowance because of the collateral.</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>quantitative information about the collateral held as security and other credit enhancements (for example, quantification of the extent to which collateral and other credit enhancements mitigate credit risk) for financial assets that are credit-impaired at the reporting date?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><i>Paragraph(b) above does not apply to lease receivables.</i></p>', '24.30', 'IFRS 7.35K\r\n\r\nIFRS 7. 35A(b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2852, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the contractual amount outstanding on financial assets that were written off during the reporting period and are still subject to enforcement activity been disclosed?', '24.31', 'IFRS 7.35L', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2853, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Credit risk exposure</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2854, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Have disclosures been given to enable users of financial statements to assess an entity’s credit risk exposure and understand its significant credit risk concentrations, by credit risk rating grades, the gross carrying amount of financial assets and the exposure to credit risk on loan commitments and financial guarantee contracts?\r\n<p>This information shall be provided separately for financial instruments:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>for which the loss allowance is measured at an amount equal to 12-month expected credit losses;</li>\r\n    <li>for which the loss allowance is measured at an amount equal to lifetime expected credit losses and that are:\r\n        <ol type=\"i\">\r\n            <li>financial instruments for which credit risk has increased significantly since initial recognition but that are not credit-impaired financial assets;</li>\r\n            <li>financial assets that are credit-impaired at the reporting date (but that are not purchased or originated credit-impaired); and</li>\r\n            <li>trade receivables, contract assets or lease receivables for which the loss allowances are measured in accordance with paragraph 5.5.15 of IFRS 9.</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>hat are purchased or originated credit-impaired financial assets.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><i>NB: For trade receivables, contract assets and lease receivables to which an entity applies paragraph 5.5.15 of IFRS 9, the information provided here may be based on a provision matrix (see paragraph B5.5.35 of IFRS 9).</i></p>', '24.32', 'IFRS 7.35M\r\n\r\nIFRS 7.35N', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2855, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Are the following disclosed by class of financial instrument:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The amount that best represents the entity’s maximum exposure to credit risk at the end of the reporting period, without taking account of any collateral held or other credit enhancements (e.g. netting agreements that do not qualify for offset in accordance with IAS 32) [NB: This disclosure is not required for financial instruments whose carrying amount best represents the maximum exposure to credit risk]; and</li>\r\n    <li>A description of collateral held as security and other credit enhancements, and their financial effect in respect of the amount that best represents the maximum exposure to credit risk?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.33', 'IFRS\r\n7.36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2856, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Collateral and Other Credit Enhancements Obtained</b>\r\n<p>Where, during the period, the entity obtains financial or non-financial assets by taking possession of collaterial it hold as security or calling on another credit enhancement (e.g. guarantees), and such assets meet the recognition criteria in other IFRS, have the following been disclosed for assets held at the reporting date:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature and carrying amount of the asset; and</li>\r\n    <li>When the assets are not readily convertible into cash, the entity’s policies for disposing of such assets or for using them in its operations?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.34', 'IFRS\r\n7.38', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2857, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Liquidity Risk \r\n<p>Have the following been disclosed:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>A maturity analysis for non-derivative financial liabilities (including issued financial guarantee contracts) that show the remaining contractual maturities;</li>\r\n    <li>A maturity analysis for derivative financial liabilities.  The maturity analysis shall include the remaining contractual maturities for those derivatives’ financial liabilities for which contractual maturities are essential for an understanding of the timing of the cash flows; and</li>\r\n    <li>A description of how the entity manages risk inherent in a and b?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><i>The entity should disclose a maturity analysis of financial assets it holds for managing liquidity risk (eg financial assets that are readily saleable or expected to generate cash inflows to meet cash outflows on financial liabilities), if that information is necessary to enable users of its financial statements to evaluate the nature and extent of liquidity risk.</i></p>\r\n<p><i><b>See also IFRS 7 B.11F</b></i></p>', '24.35', 'IFRS\r\n7.39 \r\n\r\nIFRS\r\n7.B11E\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2858, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Market Risk - Sensitivity Analysis\r\n<p>Unless the entity complies with IFRS 7, paragraph 41, are the following disclosures given:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A sensitivity analysis for each type of market risk to which the entity is exposed at the end of the reporting period, showing how profit or loss, and equity would have been affected by changes in the relevant risk variable that were reasonably possible at that date;</li>\r\n    <li>The method and assumptions used in preparing the sensitivity analysis, and </li>\r\n    <li>Changes from the previous period in the methods and assumptions used, and reasons for those changes?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.36', 'IFRS\r\n7.40\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2859, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where the entity prepares a sensitivity analysis, such as value-at-risk, that reflects interdependencies between risk variables (e.g. interest rates and exchange rates) and uses it to manage finanical risks, it may use that sensitivity analysis in place of the analysis specified in IFRS 7, paragraph 40, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>An explanation of the method used in preparing such a sensitivity analysis, and of the main parameters and assumptions underlying the data provided; and</li>\r\n    <li>An explanation of the objectives of the method used and of limitations that may result if the information does  not fully reflect the fair value of the assets and liabilities involved?</li>\r\n</ul> ', '24.37', 'IFRS\r\n7.41', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2860, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Other Market Risk Disclosures</b> <br>When the sensitivity analysis disclosure given in accordance with IFRS 7, paragraph 40 or 41 are unrepresentative of the risk inherent in a financial instrument (for example, because the year-end exposure does not reflect the exposure during the year), has the entity disclosed that fact and the reason it believes the sensitivity analyses are unrepresentative?', '24.38', 'IFRS\r\n7.42\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2861, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Transfers of Financial Assets</b>\r\n<p>The disclosure requirements of IFRS 7, paragraph 42B – 42H relate to all transferred financial assets that are not derecognised and for any continuing involvment in a transferred asset that existed as the reporting date.  For the purpose of applying the disclosure requirements in those paragraphs, an entity transfers all or a part of a financial asset (the transferred financial asset) if, and only if, it either:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Transfers the contractual rights to receive the cash flows of that financial asset; or </li>\r\n    <li>Retains the contractual rights to receive the cash flows of that asset, but assumes a contractual obligation to pay the cash flows to one or more recipients in an arrangement.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', 'IFRS\r\n7.42A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2862, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has information been disclosed that enables readers of the financial statements to:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>Understand the relationship between transferred financial assets that are not derecognised in their entirety and the associated liabilities; and</li>\r\n    <li>Evaluate the nature of, and risks associated with, the entity’s continuing involvement in derecognized financial assets?</li>\r\n</ol>', '24.39', 'IFRS \r\n7.42B', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2863, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'To meet the requirements of IFRS 7, paragraph 42B(a), have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature of the transferred asset;</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the risks and rewards of ownership to which the entity is exposed;</li>\r\n    <li>A description of the nature of the relationship between the transferred assets and the associated liabilities, including restrictions arising from the transfer on the reporting entity’s use of the transferred assets;</li>\r\n    <li>When the counterparty (counterparties) to the associated liabilities has (have) recourse only to the transferred assets, a schedule that sets out the fair value of the transferred assets, the fair value of the associated liabilities and the net position;</li>\r\n    <li>When the entity continues to recognise all of the transferred asset, the carrying amount of the transferred asset and the associated liability;</li>\r\n    <li>When the entity continues to recognise the assets to the extent of its continuing involvement (see IAS 39,  paragraph 20 (c) (ii) and 30), the total carrying amount of the original assets before the transfer, the carrying amount of the assets that the entity continues to recognise, and the carrying amount of the associated liabilities?</li>\r\n</ul>', '24.40', 'IFRS\r\n7.42D', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2864, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'To meet the requirements of IFRS 7, paragraph 42B (b) above, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>The carrying amount of the assets and liabilities that are recognized in the entity’s Statement of Financial Position and represents the entity’s continuing involvement in the derecognised financial assets, and the line items in which the carrying amount of those assets and liabilities are recognised;</li>\r\n    <li>The fair value of the assets and liabilities that represent the entity’s continuing involvement in the derecognised financial assets;</li>\r\n    <li>The amount that best represents the entity’s maximum exposure to loss from its continuing involvement in the derecognised financial asset, and information showing how the maximum exposure to loss is determined;</li>\r\n    <li>The undiscounted cash outflows that would or may be required to repurchase derecognised financial assets (e.g. the strike price in an option agreement) or other amounts payable to the transferee in respect of the transferred assets.  If the cash outflow is variable then the amount disclosed should be based on the conditions that exist at each reporting date;</li>\r\n    <li>A maturity analysis of the undiscounted cash outflows that would or maybe required to repurchase the derecognised financial assets or other amounts payable to the transferee in respect of the transferred assets, showing the remaining contractual maturities of the entity’s continuing involvement; and</li>\r\n    <li>Qualitative information that explains and supports the quantitative disclosures required by a to e above?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>The above information maybe aggregated in respect of particular assets if the entity has more than one type of continuing involvement in that derecognised financial asset, and reports it under one type of continuing involvement.</p>', '24.41', 'IFRS\r\n7.42E,F\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2865, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'In addition to the disclosures required by IFRS 7, paragraph 42F, have the following disclosures been given:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The gain or loss recognised at the date of transfer of the assets;</li>\r\n    <li>The income and expenses recognised, both in the reporting period and cumulatively, from the entity’s continuing involvement in the derecognised financial assets (e.g. fair value changes in derivative instruments);</li>\r\n    <li>If the total amount of proceeds from transfer activity (that qualifies for derecognition) in a reporting period, if not evenly distributed throughout the reporting period:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>When the greatest transfer activity took place within the reporting period;</li>\r\n            <li>The amount (e.g. related gains or losses) recognised from transfer activities in that part of the period; and </li>\r\n            <li>The total amount of proceeds from transfer activity in that part of the reporting period?</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '24.42', 'IFRS\r\n7.42G', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c3` (`acID`, `c3tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `drps`, `crps`, `drfp`, `crfp`, `issue`, `recommendation`, `result`, `yesno`, `comment`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(2866, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Hedge Accounting</b>\r\n<p>An entity shall apply the disclosure requirements in paragraphs 21B–24F of IFRS 7 for those risk exposures that an entity hedges and for which it elects to apply hedge accounting. Hedge accounting disclosures shall provide information about:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>an entity’s risk management strategy and how it is applied to manage risk;</li>\r\n    <li>how the entity’s hedging activities may affect the amount, timing and uncertainty of its future cash flows; and</li>\r\n    <li>the effect that hedge accounting has had on the entity’s statement of financial position, statement of comprehensive income and statement of changes in equity.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>An entity shall present the required disclosures in a single note or separate section in its financial statements. However, an entity need not duplicate information that is already presented elsewhere, provided that the information is incorporated by cross-reference from the financial statements to some other statement. </p>\r\n<p>When paragraphs 22A–24F require the entity to separate by risk category the information disclosed, the entity shall determine each risk category on the basis of the risk exposures an entity decides to hedge and for which hedge accounting is applied. An entity shall determine risk categories consistently for all hedge accounting disclosures</p>\r\n<p>To meet the objectives in paragraph 21A, an entity shall (except as otherwise specified below) determine how much detail to disclose, how much emphasis to place on different aspects of the disclosure requirements, the appropriate level of aggregation or disaggregation, and whether users of financial statements need additional explanations to evaluate the quantitative information disclosed. However, an entity shall use the same level of aggregation or disaggregation it uses for disclosure requirements of related information in this IFRS and IFRS 13 Fair Value Measurement.</p>\r\n', '<b>25</b>', 'IFRS 7.21A\r\n\r\nIFRS 7.21B\r\n\r\nIFRS 7.21C\r\n\r\nIFRS 7.21D', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2867, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Hedge accounting: The risk management strategy</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2868, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has an explanation been given of the risk management strategy for each risk category of risk exposures that it decides to hedge and for which hedge accounting is applied?\r\n<p>This explanation should enable users of financial statements to evaluate (for example):</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>how each risk arises.</li>\r\n    <li>how the entity manages each risk; this includes whether the entity hedges an item in its entirety for all risks or hedges a risk component (or components) of an item and why.</li>\r\n    <li>the extent of risk exposures that the entity manages.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>To meet these requirements, the information should include (but is not limited to) a description of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the hedging instruments  that are used (and how they are used) to hedge risk exposures;</li>\r\n    <li>how the entity determines the economic relationship between the hedged item and the hedging instrument for the purpose of assessing hedge effectiveness; and</li>\r\n    <li>how the entity establishes the hedge ratio and what the sources of hedge ineffectiveness are.</li>\r\n</ul>', '25.1', 'IFRS\r\n7.22A\r\n\r\nIFRS\r\n7.22B', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2869, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'When an entity designates a specific risk component as a hedged item (see paragraph 6.3.7 of IFRS 9), has it provided, in addition to the disclosures required by paragraphs 22A and 22B, qualitative or quantitative information about:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>how the entity determined the risk component that is designated as the hedged item (including a description of the nature of the relationship between the risk component and the item as a whole); and</li>\r\n    <li>how the risk component relates to the item in its entirety (for example, the designated risk component historically covered on average 80 per cent of the changes in fair value of the item as a whole)?</li>\r\n</ol>', '25.2', 'IFRS\r\n7.22C', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2870, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Unless exempted by paragraph 23C, has the entity disclosed, by risk category, quantitative information to allow users of its financial statements to evaluate the terms and conditions of hedging instruments and how they affect the amount, timing and uncertainty of future cash flows of the entity?\r\n<p>A breakdown that discloses the following must also be given:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>a profile of the timing of the nominal amount of the hedging instrument; and</li>\r\n    <li>if applicable, the average price or rate (for example strike or forward prices etc) of the hedging instrument.</li>\r\n</ol>', '25.3', 'IFRS 7.23A, B', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2871, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where an entity frequently resets (ie discontinues and restarts) hedging relationships because both the hedging instrument and the hedged item frequently change (see the example in paragraph B6.5.24(b) of IFRS 9) the entity is exempt from providing the disclosures required by paragraphs 23A and 23B.\r\n<p>Instead, have the following been disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>information about what the ultimate risk management strategy is in relation to those hedging relationships;</li>\r\n    <li>a description of how it reflects its risk management strategy by using hedge accounting and designating those particular hedging relationships; and</li>\r\n    <li>an indication of how frequently the hedging relationships are discontinued and restarted as part of the entity’s process in relation to those hedging relationships?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>When the volume of hedging relationships to which this exemption applies is unrepresentative of normal volumes during the period (ie the volume at the reporting date does not reflect the volumes during the period) an entity shall disclose that fact and the reason it believes the volumes are unrepresentative.</i></p>\r\n', '25.4', 'IFRS 7.23C\r\n\r\nIFRS 7.24D', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2872, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has a description, by risk category, of the sources of hedge ineffectiveness that are expected to affect the hedging relationship during its term been given?', '25.4', 'IFRS 7.23D', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2873, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If other sources of hedge ineffectiveness emerge in a hedging relationship, have those sources been disclosed by risk category and an explanation of the resulting hedge ineffectiveness been given?', '25.5', 'IFRS 7.23E', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2874, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the entity disclosed, in a tabular format, the following amounts related to items designated as hedging instruments separately by risk category for each type of hedge (fair value hedge, cash flow hedge or hedge of a net investment in a foreign operation):\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>the carrying amount of the hedging instruments (financial assets separately from financial liabilities);</li>\r\n    <li>the line item in the statement of financial position that includes the hedging instrument;</li>\r\n    <li>the change in fair value of the hedging instrument used as the basis for recognising hedge ineffectiveness for the period; and</li>\r\n    <li>the nominal amounts (including quantities such as tonnes or cubic metres) of the hedging instruments?</li>\r\n</ol>', '25.6', 'IFRS 7.24A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2875, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Fair Value hedges</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2876, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'In respect of fair value hedges, has the entity disclosed, in a tabular format, the following amounts separately by risk category:\r\n<ol type=\"i\">\r\n    <li>the carrying amount of the hedged item recognised in the statement of financial position (presenting assets separately from liabilities);</li>\r\n    <li>the accumulated amount of fair value hedge adjustments on the hedged item included in the carrying amount of the hedged item recognised in the statement of financial position (presenting assets separately from liabilities);</li>\r\n    <li>the line item in the statement of financial position that includes the hedged item;</li>\r\n    <li>the change in value of the hedged item used as the basis for recognising hedge ineffectiveness for the period; </li>\r\n    <li>the accumulated amount of fair value hedge adjustments remaining in the statement of financial position for any hedged items that have ceased to be adjusted for hedging gains and losses in accordance with paragraph 6.5.10 of IFRS 9;</li>\r\n    <li>hedge ineffectiveness (ie the difference between the hedging gains or losses of the hedging instrument and the hedged item) recognised in profit or loss (or other comprehensive income for hedges of an equity instrument for which an entity has elected to present changes in fair value in other comprehensive income in accordance with paragraph 5.7.5 of IFRS 9); and</li>\r\n    <li>the line item in the statement of comprehensive income that includes the recognised hedge ineffectiveness?</li>\r\n</ol>', '25.7', 'IFRS 7.24B(a)\r\n\r\nIFRS 7.24C(a)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2877, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Cash flow hedges and hedges of a net investment in a foreign operation</b>', '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2878, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'For cash flow hedges and hedges of a net investment in a foreign operation, has the entity disclosed, in a tabular format, the following amounts separately by risk category:\r\n<ol type=\"i\">\r\n    <li>the change in value of the hedged item used as the basis for recognising hedge ineffectiveness for the period (ie for cash flow hedges the change in value used to determine the recognised hedge ineffectiveness in accordance with paragraph 6.5.11(c) of IFRS 9);</li>\r\n    <li>the balances in the cash flow hedge reserve and the foreign currency translation reserve for continuing hedges that are accounted for in accordance with paragraphs 6.5.11 and 6.5.13(a) of IFRS 9;</li>\r\n    <li>the balances remaining in the cash flow hedge reserve and the foreign currency translation reserve from any hedging relationships for which hedge accounting is no longer applied;</li>\r\n    <li>hedging gains or losses of the reporting period that were recognised in other comprehensive income;</li>\r\n    <li>hedge ineffectiveness recognised in profit or loss;</li>\r\n    <li>the line item in the statement of comprehensive income that includes the recognised hedge ineffectiveness;</li>\r\n    <li>the amount reclassified from the cash flow hedge reserve or the foreign currency translation reserve into profit or loss as a reclassification adjustment (see IAS 1) (differentiating between amounts for which hedge accounting had previously been used, but for which the hedged future cash flows are no longer expected to occur, and amounts that have been transferred because the hedged item has affected profit or loss);</li>\r\n    <li>the line item in the statement of comprehensive income that includes the reclassification adjustment (see IAS 1); and</li>\r\n    <li>for hedges of net positions, the hedging gains or losses recognised in a separate line item in the statement of comprehensive income (see paragraph 6.6.4 of IFRS 9)?</li>\r\n</ol>', '25.8', 'IFRS 7.24B(b)\r\n\r\nIFRS 7.24C(b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2879, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'For cash flow hedges, has the entity given a description of any forecast transaction for which hedge accounting had been used in the previous period, but which is no longer expected to occur?', '25.9', 'IFRS 7.23F', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2880, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has a reconciliation been provided of each component of equity and an analysis of other comprehensive income in accordance with IAS 1 that, taken together:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>differentiates, at a minimum, between the amounts that relate to the disclosures in paragraph 24C(b)(i) and (b)(iv) as well as the amounts accounted for in accordance with paragraph 6.5.11(d)(i) and (d)(iii) of IFRS 9;</li>\r\n    <li>differentiates between the amounts associated with the time value of options that hedge transaction related hedged items and the amounts associated with the time value of options that hedge time-period related hedged items when an entity accounts for the time value of an option in accordance with paragraph 6.5.15 of IFRS 9; and</li>\r\n    <li>differentiates between the amounts associated with forward elements of forward contracts and the foreign currency basis spreads of financial instruments that hedge transaction related hedged items, and the amounts associated with forward elements of forward contracts and the foreign currency basis spreads of financial instruments that hedge time-period related hedged items when an entity accounts for those amounts in accordance with paragraph 6.5.16 of IFRS 9?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><i>This information should be disclosed separately by risk category. This disaggregation by risk may be provided in the notes to the financial statements.</i></p>', '25.10', 'IFRS 7.24E\r\n\r\nIFRS 7.24F', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2881, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If an entity designated a financial instrument, or a proportion of it, as measured at FVTPL because it uses a credit derivative to manage the credit risk of that financial instrument, has it disclosed:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>for credit derivatives that have been used to manage the credit risk of financial instruments designated as measured at FVTPL (see para 6.7.1 of IFRS 9), a reconciliation of each of the nominal amount and the fair value at the beginning and at the end of the period;</li>\r\n    <li>the gain or loss recognised in profit or loss on designation of a financial instrument, or a proportion of it, as measured at FVTPL; and</li>\r\n    <li>on discontinuation of measuring a financial instrument, or a proportion of it, at FVTPL, that financial instrument’s fair value that has become the new carrying amount in accordance with paragraph 6.7.4 of IFRS 9 and the related nominal or principal amount (except for providing comparative information in accordance with IAS 1, an entity does not need to continue this disclosure in subsequent periods).</li>\r\n</ol>', '25.11', 'IFRS 7.24G', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2882, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', '<b>Disclosure of Fair Value Measurement</b><p>Regarding IFRS 13 disclosures, an entity shall disclose the qualitative disclosures noted below in a tabular format unless another form is more appropriate [IFRS 13, paragraph 99].</p>', '<b>26</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2883, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has disclosure been given that helps the user of the financial statements assess both of the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>For assets and liabilities that are measured at fair value on a recurring or non-recurring basis in the Statement of Financial Position after initial recognition, the valuation techniques and inputs used to develop those measurements; and</li>\r\n    <li>For recurring fair value measurments using significant unobservable inputs (Level 3), the effect of the measurments on profit or loss or OCI for the period?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>To meet this requirement, the disclosures noted in IFRS 13, paragraph 93 must be given as a minimum.</p>', '26.1', 'IFRS \r\n13.91', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2884, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'For each class of asset and liablity (determined in accordance with IFRS 13, paragraph 94) measured at fair value in the Statement of Financial Position after initial recognition, are the following disclosed?\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>For recurring and non-recurring fair value measurements at the end of the reporting period, and non-recurring fair value measurements, the reason for the measurement;</li>\r\n    <li>For recurring and non-recurring fair value measurements; the level of the fair value hierarchy within which the fair value measurements are categorised in their entirety (e.g, Level 1,2,3);</li>\r\n    <li>For assets and liabilities held at the end of the reporting period that are measured at fair value on a recurring basis, the amount transferred between Level 1 and Level 2, the reason for those transfers and the policy for determining when transfers between levels occurred (transfers into a level should be discussed separately from transfer out of a level); a description of the valuation technique(s) and inputs used in the fair value measurement and if there has been a change in valuation technique, has this been disclosed along with the reason for the change;</li>\r\n    <li>For fair value measurements categorised within Level 3, have quantitative information about the significant unobservable inputs used in fair value measurements been discussed (this information does not need to be ‘artificially’ created when an entity uses prices from prior transactions or third-party pricing information without adjustment, however, quantitative unobservable inputs that are significant to the fair value measurement and are reasonably available cannot be ignored);</li>\r\n    <li>For fair value measurements categorised within Level 3, have quantitative information about the significant unobservable inputs used in fair value measurements been discussed (this information does not need to be ‘artificially’ created when an entity uses prices from prior transactions or third-party pricing information without adjustment, however, quantitative unobservable inputs that are significant to the fair value measurement and are reasonably available cannot be ignored);</li>\r\n    <li>For recurring fair value measurements categorised within Level 3, a reconciliation from the opening balances to the closing balances, disclosing separately:\r\n        <ol type=\"1\">\r\n            <li>) Total gains and losses for the period recognised in profit or loss, and the line item(s) in profit or loss in which those gains and losses are recognised;</li>\r\n            <li>) Total gains or losses for the period recognised in OCI, and the line item(s) in which those gains or losses are recognised;</li>\r\n            <li>) Purchase;</li>\r\n            <li>) Sales;</li>\r\n            <li>) Issues;</li>\r\n            <li>) Settlements;</li>\r\n            <li>) Transfers into Level 3; and</li>\r\n            <li>) Transfers out of Level 3.</li>\r\n        </ol>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>For recurring fair value measurements categorised within Level 3, the amount of the gain or loss for the period in (e)(1) included in profit or loss that is attributable to the change in unrealised gains or losses relating to those assets and liabilities held at the reporting period, and the line item(s) in profit or loss in which those unrealised gains or losses are recognised.</li>\r\n    <li>For non-recurring fair value measurements categorised within Level 3, a description of the valuation processes used by the entity;</li>\r\n    <li>For recurring and non-recurring fair value measurements categorised within Level 3, a description are the following disclosed:-\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>For all such measurements, a narrative description of the sensitivity of fair value measurements to changes in unobservable inputs, if a change in those inputs to a different amount might result in a significantly higher or lower fair value measurement.  If there are interrelationships between those inputs and other unobservable inputs in the fair value measurement, a description of those interrelationships and how they might magnify or mitigate the effect of changes in the unobservable inputs on the fair value measurement;</li>\r\n            <li>For financial assets and financial liabilities, if changing one or more of the unobservable inputs to reflect reasonably possible alternative assumptions would change fair value significantly, is this fact disclosed, the effect of those changes and how the effect of the changes was calculated</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>For recurring and non-recurring fair value measurements, if the highest and best use of a non-financial asset differs from its current use, has this been disclosed and why the non-financial asset is being used in a manner that differs from its highest and best use?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>NB: Any analysis given above should either agree or be reconcilied to a line item in the Statement of Financial Position.</p>', '26.2', 'IFRS 13\r\n93,94,95', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2885, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Has the policy of transfers between Levels 1,2,3, been disclosed?', '26.3', 'IFRS \r\n13.95\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2886, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'If an entity makes the decision to use the exception in IFRS 13, paragraph 48, has it disclosed that fact?\r\n<p>NB: Paragraph 48 allows, in certain circumstances, for groups of financial assets and financial liabilities to be measured on a group basis.</p>', '26.4', 'IFRS \r\n13.96\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2887, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'For each class of assets and liabilities not measured at fair value in the Statement of Financial Position, but for which fair value is disclosed, has the information required by IFRS 13.93(b), (d) and (i) been disclosed?', '26.5', 'IFRS 13.97', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2888, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section6', 'Where the client is the issuer of a liability measured at fair value and issued with an inseparable third-party credit enhancement, has the existence of that credit enhancement and whether it is reflected in the fair value measurement of the liability been disclosed?', '26.6', 'IFRS 13.98', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:26:38'),
(2889, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', '<b>General</b>', '<b>1</b>', '\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2890, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'Are cash flows split into operating, investing and financing activities?', '1.1', 'IAS 7\r\nIntroduction1, 10', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2891, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'Are cash flows from operating activities disclosed using either:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The direct method, disclosing major classes of gross cash receipts or payments; or</li>\r\n    <li>The indirect method, by adjusting profit or loss for the effects of:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>changes during the period in inventories and operating receivables and payable;</li>\r\n            <li>other non-cash items (depreciation, provisions, deferred taxation, unrealised foreign currency gains and losses, and in the consolidated cash flow statement undistributed profits from associates); and</li>\r\n            <li>all other items for which the cash effects are investing or financing.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB1: Entities are encouraged to report cash flows from operating activities using the direct method.</p>\r\n', '1.2', 'IAS 7.18 \r\n\r\nIAS 7.20\r\n\r\nIAS 7.19\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2892, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'For cash flows from investing and financing activities are the major classes of gross cash receipts and gross cash payments disclosed separately (unless the transactions are entered into as an agent or are cash receipts and payments for items in which the turnover is quick and maturities are short)?\r\n<p>NB1: Paragraphs 23, 23A and 24 give additional guidance.</p>', '1.3', 'IAS 7.21,22', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2893, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'Are investing and financing non-cash transactions disclosed separately in a note to the Statement of Cash Flows?\r\n<p>NB1: Paragraph 44 gives examples of such transactions.</p>\r\n', '1.4', 'IAS 7.43', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2894, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'In relation to changes in liabilities arising from financing activities, be those cash or non-cash changes, has disclosure been given of the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Changes from financing cash flows;</li>\r\n    <li>Changes arising from obtaining or losing control of subsidiaries or other businesses; </li>\r\n    <li>The effect of changes in foreign exchange rates;</li>\r\n    <li>Changes in fair values; and</li>\r\n    <li>Other changes?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>NB1: The disclosure of changes in liabilities arising from financing activities must be shown separately from changes in other assets and liabilities.</i></p>\r\n<p><i>NB2: On first time adoption of this requirement, comparatives are not required.</i></p>\r\n<p><i>See IAS 7.44D for a suggested method of fulfilling this disclosure requirement. </i></p>', '1.5', 'IAS 7.44A\r\nIAS 7.44B\r\n \r\nIAS 7.44E\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2895, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'The disclosure requirement above also applies to changes in financial assets (e.g. assets that hedge liabilities arising from financing activities) if cash flows from those financial assets were, or future cash flows will be, included in cash flows from operating activities.\r\n<p>Where relevant, has appropriate disclosure been given?</p>', '1.6', 'IAS 7.44C', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2896, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', '<b>Individual Items</b>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2897, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'In relation to cash flows arising from taxes on income, are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Taxes paid (shown in operating activities unless specifically identified as investing or financing activities); and</li>\r\n    <li>The total amount of taxes paid when tax cash flows are allocated over more than one class of activity?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.1', 'IAS 7.35\r\n\r\nIAS 7.36\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2898, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'For cash flows from interest and dividends, are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Interest received;</li>\r\n    <li>Interest paid;</li>\r\n    <li>Dividends received; and</li>\r\n    <li>Dividends paid?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB1: These items may be allocated to operating, investing or financing activities, see IAS 7, paragraphs 33 and 34.</p>\r\n<p>NB2: Interest paid should include all interest, including interest that has been capitalised.</p>', '2.2', 'IAS 7.31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2899, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'Are aggregate cash flows presented separately and classified as investing activities, when arising from obtaining or losing control of subsidiaries or other businesses during the period?', '2.3', 'IAS 7.39', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2900, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'Are aggregate cash flows in respect of both obtaining or losing control of subsidiaries or other business during the period disclosed for the following:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>the total consideration paid or received;</li>\r\n    <li>the portion of the consideration consisting of cash and cash equivalents;</li>\r\n    <li>the amount of cash and cash equivalents in the subsidiary or other businesses over which control was obtained or lost; and</li>\r\n    <li>the amount of the assets and liabilities other than cash or cash equivalents in the subsidiary or others businesses over which control was obtained or lost, summarised by each major category?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>NB1:  An investment entity, as defined by IFRS 10 need not disclose the information required by points c and d above regarding any investment in a subsidiary that is required to be measured at fair value through profit and loss.</p>', '2.4', 'IAS 7.40\r\n\r\nIAS 7.40A', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2901, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'For cash and cash equivalents, is the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Net increase / decrease in cash and cash equivalents during the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Cash and cash equivalents at the beginning of the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Other reconciling items (specifically, disclose the    effect of foreign exchange movement on cash and cash equivalents); and</li>\r\n    <li>Cash and cash equivalents at the end of the period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.5', 'IAS 7.45\r\nIAS 7.28\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2902, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'Are significant cash and cash equivalent balances held by the entity, but not available for use by the group disclosed together with a commentary by management?', '2.6', 'IAS 7.48', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2903, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'IAS 7 <b><u>encourages</u></b> the disclosure of additional information that is relevant to understand the financial position and liquidity of the entity.  Such disclosures include: \r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the amount of undrawn borrowing facilities that may be available for further operating activities and to settle capital commitments, indicating any restrictions on the use of these facilities; and</li>\r\n    <li>the aggregated amount of cash flows that represent increases in operating capacity, separately from those that are required to maintain operating capacity.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.7', 'IAS 7.50', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2904, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'Where a government grant has been received to assist in the purchase of an asset, is the grant receipt and purchase cost of the asset disclosed separately in the Statement of Cash Flows regardless of how they are presented in the Statement of Financial Position?', '2.8', 'IAS 20.28', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2905, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'In relation to discontinued operations, are the following net cash flows disclosed (either in notes to, or on the face of the Statement of Cash Flows):\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Operating activities;</li>\r\n    <li>Investing activities; and</li>\r\n    <li>Financing activities?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: These disclosures are not required for disposal groups that are newly acquired subsidiaries that meet the criteria to be classified as held for sale on acquisition.</p>', '2.9', 'IFRS 5.33 (c)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2906, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section7', 'In relation to leases, have:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>cash payments for the principal portion of the lease liability been shown within financing activities; and </li>\r\n    <li>cash payments for the interest portion of the lease liability, short-term lease payments, payments for leases of low-value assets and variable lease payments not included in the measurement of the lease liability been shown within operating activities?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.10', 'IFRS 16.50', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 15:39:30'),
(2926, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Basis of Preparation</b>', '<b>1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2927, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'Is there an explicit and unreserved statement that these financial statements have been prepared in accordance with International Financial Reporting Standards, or have the disclosures noted in point 2 below been given?', '1.1', 'IAS 1.16', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2928, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>True and Fair Override</b>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2929, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'When the entity departs from a requirement of an IAS / IFRS / SIC / IFRIC due to those charged with governance believing that it is necessary to show a true and fair view, have the following disclosures been made:\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>that management has concluded that the financial statements present fairly the entity’s financial position, financial performance and cash flows;</li>\r\n    <li>that the entity has complied with IFRS, except that it has departed from a particular requirement to achieve a fair presentation;</li>\r\n    <li>the title of the IAS / IFRS / SIC / IFRIC from which the entity has departed;</li>\r\n    <li>the nature of the departure, including:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>the treatment that would have been required; </li>\r\n            <li>the reason why that treatment would be misleading; </li>\r\n            <li>the treatment actually adopted; and</li>\r\n            <li>for each period presented, the financial effect of the departure on each item in the financial statements that would have been reported in complying with the requirement?</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ol>', '2.1', 'IAS 1.20\r\n(a) to (d)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2930, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'When the entity has departed from a requirement an IAS / IFRS / SIC / IFRIC in a prior period, and that departure affects the amounts recognised in the current period, have the disclosures set out in 2.1(c) and (d) above been given?', '2.2', 'IAS 1.21', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2931, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'In the extremely rare circumstance where management conclude that a departure from an IAS / IFRS / SIC / IFRIC is necessary to give a true and fair view, however, the relevant regulatory framework prohibits such as departure, have the following disclosures been given:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The title of the IAS / IFRS / SIC / IFRIC;</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the requirement;</li>\r\n    <li>The reason why management has concluded that complying with that requirement conflicts with the requirement to give a true and fair view; and </li>\r\n    <li>For each period presented, the adjustments to each item in the financial statements that management has concluded necessary to achieve a fair presentation?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.3', 'IAS 1.23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2932, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'Is the effect and reason for any departure from any of the following accounting concepts disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Going concern;</li>\r\n    <li>Consistency;</li>\r\n    <li>Prudence;</li>\r\n    <li>Accruals; and</li>\r\n    <li>Determination of aggregate amounts by separate determination of each individual asset and liability?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.4', 'Best Practice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2933, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Long and Short Accounting Periods</b>', '<b>3</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2934, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'Where the financial statements are for a period other than one year (i.e. there is a long or short accounting period) are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>That fact;</li>\r\n    <li>The reason for having a longer or shorter period; and</li>\r\n    <li>The fact that comparative amounts presented in the financial statements (including the related notes) are not entirely comparable?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.1', 'IAS 1.36', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2935, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Going Concern</b>', '<b>4</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2936, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'Whilst not a specific requirement of IFRS, it is desirable to disclose the period that those charged with governance have considered when assessing going concern, where necessary have appropriate disclosures been given?\r\n<p>ISA 570 requires this period to be disclosed in the auditors’ report if it is less than one year from the end of the reporting period, and this has not been noted in the financial statements.</p>', '4.1', 'ISA 570, 17-1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2937, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'When management are aware, in making their assessment of going concern, of material uncertainties related to events or conditions that cast significant doubt upon the entity’s ability to continue as a going concern, have those uncertainties been disclosed?', '4.2', 'IAS 1.25', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2938, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'When management do not prepare financial statements on a going concern basis (i.e. break up basis), are the following disclosures given:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>That fact;</li>\r\n    <li>The basis on which the financial statements are prepared; and </li>\r\n    <li>The reason why the entity is not considered to be going concern?</li>\r\n</ul>', '4.3', 'IAS 1.25', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2939, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Accounting Policies – General</b>', '<b>5</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2940, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'Is there a description of all significant accounting policies?', '5.1', 'IAS 1.117', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2941, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>First time adoption of IFRS 9 / 15 / 16</b>\r\n<p>Where applicable, have supplementary checklist Ab4g “ <b>Additional Disclosures on transition to IFRS 15 and IFRS 9</b>” and / or Ab4h, “ <b>Additional disclosures on transition to IFRS 16 </b>” been completed to ensure that the appropriate disclosures have been given? </p>', '5.2 ', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2942, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Change in Accounting Policies</b>', '<b>6</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2943, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'When initial application of an IFRS has an effect on the current period or any prior period, or might have an effect on future periods, has the entity disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The title of the IFRS;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, that the change in accounting policy is made in accordance with its transitional provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the change in accounting policy;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, a description of the transitional provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, the transitional provisions that might have an effects on future periods;</li>\r\n    <li>For the current and each prior period presented, to the extent practicable, the amount of the adjustment for each financial statement line item affected (including, lines in the statement of cash flows);</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of the adjustment relating to periods before those presented, to the extent practicable; and </li>\r\n    <li>If retrospective application is impracticable for a particular prior period, or for periods before those presented, the circumstances that led to the existence of that condition and a description of how and from when the change in accounting policy has been applied?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: This disclosure does not need to be repeated in subsequent periods.</p>', '6.1', 'IAS 8.28\r\n(a) to (h)\r\n\r\nIAS 7.47\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2944, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'Where a voluntary change in accounting policy has affected the current period or any prior period, has the entity disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature of the change in accounting policy;</li>\r\n    <li>The reasons why applying the new accounting policy provides reliable and more relevant information;</li>\r\n    <li>To the extent practicable, the amount of the adjustment for each financial statement line item affected (including lines in the Statement of Cash Flows); shown separately:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>For the current period;</li>\r\n            <li>For each prior period presented; and</li>\r\n            <li>In aggregate for the periods before those presented.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>If retrospective application is impracticable for a particular prior period, or for periods before those presented, the circumstances that led to the existence of that condition and a description of how and from when the change in accounting policy has been applied?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: This disclosure does not need to be repeated in subsequent periods.</p>', '6.2', 'IAS 8,29\r\n(a) to (e)\r\n\r\nIAS 7.49', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2945, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Impact of IFRS That Have Been Issued but Which are Not Yet Effective</b>', '<b>7</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2946, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'When an entity has not applied a new IFRS that has been issued but is not yet effective, have the following been disclosed:-\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>That fact; and</li>\r\n    <li>Known or reasonable estimable information relevant to assessing the possible impact that application of the new IFRS will have on the entity’s financial statements in the period of initial application.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>When giving the above disclosures an entity should consider, disclosing:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The title of the new IFRS;</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the impending change or changes in accounting policy;</li>\r\n    <li>The date by which application of the IFRS is required;</li>\r\n    <li>The date when the entity plans to apply the IFRS initially; and</li>\r\n    <li>Either:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>A discussion of the impact that initial application of the IFRS is expected to have on the entity’s financial statements; or</li>\r\n            <li>If that impact is not known or reasonably estimable, a statement to that effect.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '7.1', 'IAS 8.30\r\n\r\nIAS 8.30\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2947, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Change in Presentation and Classification.</b>', '<b>8</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2948, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'When the presentation or classification of items in the financial statements has changed, has the entity reclassified comparative amounts (including as at the beginning of the preceding period) unless the reclassification is impracticable?\r\n<p>When comparative amounts have been reclassified, has the entity disclosed the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature of the reclassification;</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of each item or class of items that is reclassified; and</li>\r\n    <li>The reason for the reclassification.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If it is impracticable to reclassify comparative amounts, has it been disclosed why reclassification was not practicable?</p>', '8.1', 'IAS 1.41\r\n\r\nIAS 1.42\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2949, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Change in Estimation Technique</b>', '<b>9</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2950, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'Where there has been a change in estimation technique, has the nature of the change and the effect on the current period and future periods (where it is practicable) been disclosed?\r\n<p>Regarding future periods, if the effect is impracticable to quantify has this been disclosed?</p>', '9.1', 'IAS 8.39\r\n\r\nIAS 8.40', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2951, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Correction of Material Prior Period Errors </b>', '<b>10</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2952, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', 'Where a material prior period error has occurred, have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature of the prior period error;</li>\r\n    <li>For each period presented, to the extent practicable, the amount of the correction for each financial statement line affected;</li>\r\n    <li>To the extent practicable, the amount of the correction at the beginning of the earliest period presented; and</li>\r\n    <li>An explanation where it is not practicable to give the above information, including the circumstances that led to the existence of that condition and a description of how and from when the error has been corrected?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: This disclosure does not need to be repeated in subsequent period.</p>', '10.1', 'IAS 8.49\r\n(a), (b)(i),\r\n(c), (d)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2953, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Specific Accounting Policies</b>', '<b>11</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2954, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Revenue Recognition </b> <br>Has an appropriate accounting policy for revenue recognition been disclosed? \r\n<p>For more detail, see question 3 “Revenue from Contracts with Customers” in Section 4: Statement of Comprehensive Income (SCI) and Related Notes.</p>', '<b>11.1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c3` (`acID`, `c3tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `drps`, `crps`, `drfp`, `crfp`, `issue`, `recommendation`, `result`, `yesno`, `comment`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(2955, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Exceptional Items</b> <br>Has an accounting policy for the accounting treatment of exceptional items been noted?', '<b>11.2</b>', 'Best Practice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2956, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Intangible Assets (including R&D)</b>\r\n<p>Are the following disclosed for each class of intangible asset:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Whether they have indefinite or finite lives;</li>\r\n    <li>Where lives are finite; either the useful lives or the amortisation rates use; and </li>\r\n    <li>The amortised method used for assets with finite lives?</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>11.3</b>', 'IAS 38.118 (a), (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2957, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Property, Plant and Equipment (PPE)</b>\r\n<p>Has an accounting policy been given for each class of PPE regarding:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The measurement bases used for determining the gross carrying amounts;</li>\r\n    <li>The depreciation method used; and</li>\r\n    <li>The useful lives or the depreciation rate used?</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>11.4</b>', 'IAS 16.73\r\n(a) to (c)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2958, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Investment Properties</b>\r\n<p>Has an accounting policy been given which notes:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Whether the cost or fair value model has been applied;</li>\r\n    <li>Where the fair value model has been applied, whether, and in what circumstances, property interests held under an operating lease are classified and accounted for an investment properties;</li>\r\n    <li>Where the classification is difficult, the criteria the entity uses to distinguish between:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>investment properties;</li>\r\n            <li>owner-occupied properties; and</li>\r\n            <li>properties held for sale in the ordinary course of the business; and</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>Where the cost model has been applied: the depreciation method used and the useful lives or the depreciation rate used?</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>11.5</b>', 'IAS 40.75 (a) to (c)\r\n\r\nIAS 40.79 (a) to (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2959, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Government Grants</b> <br>Is there and accounting policy, including the method of presentation adopted in the financial statement disclosed?', '<b>11.6</b>', 'IAS 20.39 (a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2960, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Inventory</b> <br>Has the accounting policy adopted in measuring inventories, including the cost formula used, been disclosed?', '<b>11.7</b>', 'IAS 2.36 (a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2961, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Foreign Currency Translation</b> <br>Has an accounting policy been given, which comprehensively covers foreign currency issues.  This should specifically cover the method of translation of sums originally denominated in foreign currencies.', '<b>11.8</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2962, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Investments in Subsidiaries, Associates and Joint Ventures</b>\r\n<p>Has the method of accounting for:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Subsidiaries;</li>\r\n    <li>Associates; and</li>\r\n    <li>Joint ventures;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>in the entity’s own balance sheet (as opposed to any consolidated balance sheet which has been presented) been disclosed?</p>', '<b>11.9</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2963, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Financial Instruments</b>\r\n<p>Has a summary been given of the significant accounting policies and the measurement bases used to value financial instruments?</p>\r\n<p>Such disclosure may include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>for financial liabilities designated as at FVTPL:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>the nature of the financial liabilities the entity has designated as at fair value through profit or loss;</li>\r\n            <li>the criteria for so designating such financial liabilities on initial recognition; and</li>\r\n            <li>how the entity has satisfied the conditions in paragraph 4.2.2 of IFRS 9 for such designation.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>for financial assets designated as measured at FVTPL:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>the nature of the financial assets the entity has designated as measured at fair value through profit or loss; and</li>\r\n            <li>how the entity has satisfied the criteria in paragraph 4.1.5 of IFRS 9 for such designation.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>whether regular way purchases and sales of financial assets are accounted for at trade date or at settlement date (see paragraph 3.1.2 of IFRS 9).</li>\r\n    <li>how net gains or net losses on each category of financial instrument are determined (see paragraph 20(a)), for example, whether the net gains or net losses on items at fair value through profit or loss include interest or dividend income.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>11.10</b>', 'IFRS 7.21\r\nIAS 1.117\r\n\r\nIFRS 7.B5\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2964, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Deferred Taxation</b> <br>Is there an appropriate accounting policy?', '<b>11.11</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2965, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Cash and Cash Equivalents</b> <br>Has the policy which is adopted in determining the composition of cash and cash equivalents been disclosed?', '<b>11.12</b>', 'IAS 7.46', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2966, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Entity is a Lessee</b> <br>Has an appropriate policy for accounting for leases for which the entity is a lessee been given, sufficient to enable users of the financial statements to understand the effect that leases have on the financial position, financial performance and cash flows of the entity? \r\n<p>For more detail, see question 13 “Entity is a Lessee” in Section 6 – Statement of Financial Position and Related Notes.</p>', '<b>11.13</b>', 'IFRS 16.51', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2967, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section8', '<b>Entity is a Lessor</b> <br>Has an appropriate policy for accounting for leases for which the entity is a lessor been given, sufficient to enable users of the financial statements to understand the effect that leases have on the financial position, financial performance and cash flows of the entity? \r\n<p>For more detail, see questions 14 “Entity is a Lessor: Finance Leases” and question 15 “Entity is a Lessor: Operating Leases” in Section 6 – Statement of Financial Position and Related Notes.</p>', '<b>11.14</b>', 'IFRS 16.89', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 17:45:26'),
(2968, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Disaggregation of Information </b>', '<b>1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2969, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'If the entity discloses information about its operating segments on a voluntary basis, has it been ensured that this information is not described as ‘Segmental Information’ unless the provisions of IFRS 8 have been fully complied with?', '1.1', 'IFRS 8.3 ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2970, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Government Grants and Assistance</b>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2971, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Where an IFRS requires the separate disclosure of an item of income or expense, if that item has been affected by a government grant, then has the effect on that line in the SCI been disclosed?', '2.1', 'IAS 20.31', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2972, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature and amounts of government grants recognised in the financial statements;</li>\r\n    <li>Unfulfilled conditions and other contingencies attaching to government grants that have been recognised in income;</li>\r\n    <li>An indication of other forms of government assistance from which the entity has directly benefited?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This disclosure does not apply to benefits that that arise in determining the amount of tax such as R&D tax credits etc.</p>\r\n<p>Examples would include free technical or marketing advice, the provision of guarantees and loans at nil or low interest rates.</p>', '2.2', 'IAS 20.39\r\n(b), (c)\r\nIAS 10.36\r\n\r\nIAS 20.35\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2973, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Information about Judgements</b>', '<b>3</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2974, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'If not already disclosed in the accounting policies, has management disclosed the key judgements made (apart from those involving estimations) in the process of applying the entity’s accounting policies and that have the most significant effect on the amounts recognised in the financial statements?', '3.1', 'IAS 1.122', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2975, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Information about Key Sources of Estimation Uncertainty</b>', '<b>4</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2976, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Where, in determining the carrying amount of assets and liabilities there are material uncertainties, are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature of the uncertainties;</li>\r\n    <li>The carrying amount as at the end of the reporting period?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Typical disclosures would include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature of the assumptions or other estimation uncertainty;</li>\r\n    <li>The sensitivity of carrying amounts to the methods, assumptions and estimates underlying their calculation, including the reasons for the sensitivity;</li>\r\n    <li>The expected resolution of an uncertainty and the range of possible outcomes within the next financial year in respect of the carrying amounts of the assets and liabilities; and</li>\r\n    <li>An explanation of changes made to past assumptions concerning those assets and liabilities, if the uncertainty remains unresolved.</li>\r\n</ul>', '4.1', 'IAS 1.125\r\n\r\nIAS 1.129\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2977, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Changes Since the Last Interim Financial Statements</b>', '<b>5</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2978, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Where interim financial statements have been prepared, and amounts estimated in those interim financial statements have changed significantly, have the nature and amount of that change been disclosed?', '5.1', 'IAS 34.26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2979, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Capitalisation of Borrowing Costs</b>', '<b>6</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2980, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Has the capitalisation rate used been disclosed?', '6.1', 'IAS 23.26 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2981, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Has the amount of borrowing costs capitalised in the period been disclosed?', '6.2', 'IAS 23.26 (a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2982, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Contingent Liabilities</b>', '<b>7</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2983, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Is the following information given in respect of each class of contingent liability (unless the possibility of any transfer in settlement is remote):\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A brief description of their nature; and where practical:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>an estimate of their financial effect;</li>\r\n            <li>an indication of the uncertainties relating to the amount or timing of any outflows; and</li>\r\n            <li>the possibility of any reimbursement?</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If it is impracticable to make one or more of these disclosures, that fact must be stated.</p>', '7.1', 'IAS 37.86\r\n\r\nIAS 37.91\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2984, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Where a provision and a contingent liability arise from the same set of circumstances, have they been disclosed in a way that shows the link between the two?', '7.2', 'IAS 37.88', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2985, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Contingent Assets </b>', '<b>8</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2986, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Is the following information given in respect of each class of contingent asset (where the likely inflow of economic benefit is probable (i.e. more likely than not)):\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the nature of the contingent asset; and where practical:</li>\r\n    <li>an estimate of their financial effect.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If it is impracticable to make this disclosure, that fact must be stated.</p>\r\n<p>It is vital that disclosure of contingent assets avoids giving a misleading indication of the likelihood of income arising.</p>', '8.1', 'IAS 37.89\r\n\r\nIAS 37.91\r\n\r\nIAS 37.90\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2987, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Non-Disclosure of Contingents Assets or Liabilities (Re: Seriously Prejudicial)</b>', '<b>9</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2988, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'The disclosures noted in 7.1 and 8.1 above do not have to be provided if deemed to be seriously prejudicial (unless required by statute).\r\n<p>If advantage is taken of this exemption, have the following been disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The general nature of the dispute; </li>\r\n    <li>The fact that full disclosure has not been given, and</li>\r\n    <li>The reason why the required information is not disclosed?</li>\r\n</ul>', '9.1', 'IAS 37.92', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2989, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Capital and Other Commitments</b>', '<b>10</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2990, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Has the amount of any contractual commitments for the acquisition of PPE been disclosed?', '10.1', 'IAS 16.74 (c) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2991, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Regarding Investment Properties, has the amount of any contractual commitments regarding the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Purchase;</li>\r\n    <li>Construction;</li>\r\n    <li>Development;</li>\r\n    <li>Repairs;</li>\r\n    <li>Maintenance; or</li>\r\n    <li>Enhancements?</li>\r\n</ul>', '10.2', 'IAS 40.75 (h)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2992, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Events after the End of the Reporting Period</b>', '<b>11</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2993, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Are the following disclosures made in respect of non-adjusting events:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature of the event; and</li>\r\n    <li>An estimate of the financial effect (or a statement that such an estimate cannot be made)?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: A non-adjusting event is an event after the reporting date, which concerns conditions that arose after the reporting date.  Examples, are given in IAS 10, paragraph 22.</p>', '11.1', 'IAS 10.32', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2994, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Where loans have been classified as current liabilities, however, during the period between the reporting date and the date of signing the financial statements, any of the following events occurred, are they disclosed as non-adjusting events:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Refinancing on a long-term basis;</li>\r\n    <li>Rectification of a breach of a long-term loan arrangement; and</li>\r\n    <li>The granting by the lender of a period of grace to rectify a breach of a long-term loan arrangement ending at least twelve months after the reporting period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '11.2', 'IAS 1.76', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2995, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Where a change in tax rates or law are enacted or announced after the reporting period, has the effect on current and deferred tax assets and liabilities been disclosed?', '11.3', 'IAS 12.88', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2996, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'If, after the end of a reporting period, but before the financial statements are authorised for issue, an entity declares a dividend in specie, it shall disclose:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the nature of the asset to be distributed;</li>\r\n    <li>the carrying amount of the asset to be distributed as of the end of the reporting period; and</li>\r\n    <li>the fair value of the asset to be distributed as of the end of the reporting period, if it is different from its carrying amount, and the information about the method(s) used to measure that fair value required by IFRS 13, paragraphs 93(b), (d), (g) and (i) and 99?</li>\r\n</ul>', '11.4', 'IFRIC 17.17', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2997, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Dividends</b>', '<b>12</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2998, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The amount of dividend recognised as a distribution to owners (i.e. equity dividends) and the related amount of dividend per share;</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of dividends proposed or declared before the financial statements were authorised for issue but not recognised as a distribution to owners during the period, and the related amount per share; and</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of any cumulative preference dividends not recognised?</li>\r\n</ul>', '12.1', 'IAS 1.107.\r\n\r\nIAS 1.137 (a)\r\nIAS 10.13\r\n\r\nIAS 1.137 (b)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(2999, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Ultimate Controlling Party and Parent Undertakings Disclosures </b>', '<b>13</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3000, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Do the notes disclose who:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The ultimate controlling party is;</li>\r\n    <li>The immediate parent undertaking is;</li>\r\n    <li>The ultimate parent undertaking is?</li>\r\n</ul>', '13.1', 'IAS 1.138 (c )\r\n\r\nIAS 24.13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3001, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'If neither the entity’s parent, nor the ultimate controlling party produces consolidated financial statements available for public use, has the name of the next most senior parent that does been disclosed?', '13.2', 'IAS 24.13', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3002, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Where the parent undertaking or ultimate controlling party has changed since the reporting date, has this been disclosed?', '13.3', 'Best Practice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3003, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Related Party Disclosures</b>', '<b>14</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3004, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Where related party transaction exist have the following been disclosed (as a <b>minimum</b>):\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The amount of the transactions;</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of outstanding balances (including commitments);</li>\r\n    <li>Regarding the outstanding balance (including commitments), have the terms and conditions been disclosed, including:</li>\r\n    <li>Whether the balances are secured;</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the consideration to be provided in settlement;</li>\r\n    <li>Details of whether any guarantees were given or received.</li>\r\n    <li>Provisions regarding outstanding debit balances; and</li>\r\n    <li>The bad debt expense recognised during the period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '14.1', 'IAS 24.18', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3005, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Have amounts incurred by the entity for the provision of key management services that are provided by a separate management entity been separately disclosed?\r\n<p>Unless separate disclosure is needed to understand the effects of related party transactions, transactions which are similar in nature can be aggregated where they relate to similar related parties.</p>\r\n<p>IAS 24 requires separate disclosure for each of the following categories of related party, has this disclosure been given:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The parent;</li>\r\n    <li>Entities with joint control or significant influence over the entity;</li>\r\n    <li>Subsidiaries;</li>\r\n    <li>Associates;</li>\r\n    <li>Joint ventures in which the entity is a joint venturer;</li>\r\n    <li>Key management personnel of the entity or its parent; and</li>\r\n    <li>Other related parties?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: Regarding similar transactions, IAS 24 gives the following examples where aggregation could occur:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Purchases or sales of goods (finished or unfinished); </li>\r\n    <li>Purchases or sales of property and other assets;</li>\r\n    <li>Rendering or receiving services;</li>\r\n    <li>Leases;</li>\r\n    <li>Transfers of R&D;</li>\r\n    <li>Transfers under licence agreements;</li>\r\n    <li>Transfers under finance agreements (including loans and equity contributions in the form of cash or in kind);</li>\r\n    <li>Provision of guarantees or collateral;</li>\r\n    <li>Commitments to do something if a particular event occurs or does not occur in the future, including executory contracts (recognised and unrecognised);</li>\r\n    <li>Settlement of liabilities on behalf of the entity or on behalf of another party; and</li>\r\n    <li>Participation by a parent or subsidiary in a defined benefit plan where risks are shared between group entities</li>\r\n</ul>', '14.2', 'IAS 24.18A\r\n\r\nIAS 24.24\r\n\r\nIAS 24.19\r\n\r\nIAS 24.20', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3006, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Government-Related Entities and Related Party Disclosures</b>\r\n<p>A reporting entity is exempt from disclosing related party transactions and balances (including commitments) with:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A government that has control or joint control of; or significant influence over the reporting entity; and</li>\r\n    <li>Another entity that is a related party because the same government has control or joint control of, or significant influence over, both the reporting entity and the other entity.</li>\r\n</ul>', '', 'IAS 24.25', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3007, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Where these exemptions are taken advantage of, are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The name of the government;</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the relationship; and</li>\r\n    <li>The following information in sufficient detail to enable users of the entity’s financial statement to understand the effect of related party transactions including:-\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The nature and amount of each individually significant transactions; and</li>\r\n            <li>For other transactions that are collectively, but not individually significant, a qualitative or quantitative indication of their extent?</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>IAS 24.27 gives additional guidance.</p>', '14.3', 'IAS 24.26', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3008, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', '<b>Capital Management</b>', '<b>15</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3009, 59, '3.15 Ab4', 'section9', 'Has adequate disclosure been given to allow an evaluation of the entity’s objectives, policies and processes for managing capital?\r\n<p>To comply with IAS 1, paragraph 134, the following disclosures should be given:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>A description of what the entity manages as capital;</li>\r\n    <li>When an entity is subject to externally imposed capital requirements, the nature of those requirements and how those requirements are incorporated into the management of capital;</li>\r\n    <li>How it is meeting its objectives for managing capital;</li>\r\n    <li>Summary quantitative data about what it manages as capital;</li>\r\n    <li>Any changes in (a) to (d) from the previous period;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether, during the period, externally imposed capital requirements were complied with and where not, the consequences of such non-compliance.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>NB: These disclosures should be based on the information provided internally to key management personnel</p>\r\n<p>NB: Where an entity has a number of different ways of measuring capital or is subject to a number of different external capital requirement, information may only be given on an aggregate basis if it would still be meaningful.</p>', '15.1', 'IAS 1.134\r\n\r\nIAS 1.135\r\n\r\nIAS 1.136', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 18:14:50'),
(3010, 60, '3.15.1 Ab4a', 'ab4a', '<p>Information must be disclosed that identifies and explains the amounts recognised in the financial statements arising from the exploration for and evaluation of mineral resources.</p>\r\n<p>To meet this requirement the following disclosures must be given.</p>', '1', 'IFRS 6.23', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 19:33:39'),
(3011, 60, '3.15.1 Ab4a', 'ab4a', '<p>Has an accounting policy been disclosed for, the exploration and evaluation expenditures, including: the recognition of exploration and evaluation assets?</p>', '2', 'IFRS 6.24 (a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 19:33:39'),
(3012, 60, '3.15.1 Ab4a', 'ab4a', 'Are the following disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Assets;</li>\r\n    <li>Liabilities;</li>\r\n    <li>Income;</li>\r\n    <li>Expense;</li>\r\n    <li>Operating cash flows; and</li>\r\n    <li>Investing cash flows which arise from exploration for and evaluation of mineral resources?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3', 'IFRS 6.24 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 19:33:39'),
(3013, 60, '3.15.1 Ab4a', 'ab4a', '<p>Have any exploration and evaluation assets been classified as a separate asset and have the disclosures required by either IAS 16 ‘Property, Plant and Equipment’ or IAS 38 ‘Intangible Assets’ been given?\r\n</p>', '4', 'IFRS 6.25', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 19:33:39'),
(3014, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', '<b>General</b>', '<b>1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3015, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Do the financial statements include a suitably worded accounting policy?', '1.1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3016, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', '<b>Defined Benefit Pension Plans being accounted for on a Defined Contribution Basis (Excluding those Plans that share risks between Entities under Common Control)</b>\r\n<p>NB: This section will only usually relate to industry-wide pension plans like the Merchant Navy Officers Fund.</p>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3017, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Where an entity has a defined benefit multi-employer pension plan which is being treated as a defined contribution pension plan due to there being a lack of available information, have the following disclosures been given:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>That the plan is defined benefit in nature;</li>\r\n    <li>The reason why sufficient information in not available to treat the plan as a defined benefit plan;</li>\r\n    <li>The expected contributions to the plan for the next annual reporting period;</li>\r\n    <li>Information about any deficit or surplus in the plan that may affect the amount of future contributions, including the basis used to determine that deficit or surplus and the implications, if any, for the entity; and</li>\r\n    <li>An indication of the level of participation of the entity in the plan compared with other entities.  If the information is available, examples of measures that might provide such an indication, include the entity’s proportion of:-\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The total contributions;</li>\r\n            <li>Active members;</li>\r\n            <li>Retired members;</li>\r\n            <li>Deferred members?</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '2.1', 'IAS\r\n19.148(d)\r\n(i) to (v)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3018, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Have the following been disclosed:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A description of the funding arrangements, including the method used to determine the entity’s rate of contributions and any minimum funding requirements;</li>\r\n    <li>A description of the extent to which the entity can be liable to the plan for other entities’ obligations under the terms and conditions of the multi-employer plan;</li>\r\n    <li>A description of any agreed allocation of a deficit or surplus on:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Wind-up of the plan, or</li>\r\n            <li>The entity’s withdrawal from the plan?</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '2.2', 'IAS\r\n19.147\r\n(a) - (c)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3019, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', '<b>Defined Benefit Pension Plans</b>\r\n<p>The Standard gives those charged with governance discretion to determine exactly how the disclosure objectives in IAS 19.135 are met.  Thus the level of detail, the emphasis placed on each disclosure noted below, whether additional disclosures are necessary, and where an entity operates multiple defined benefit plans whether to aggregate disclosures for different plans, and if so, to what extent.</p>\r\n', '<b>3</b>', 'IAS\r\n19.136-138\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3020, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Are the following disclosed:', '3.1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3021, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'The nature of the benefits provided by the plan (e.g. final salary defined benefit plan or contribution based plan with guarantee)?', 'a', 'IAS\r\n19.139\r\n(a) (i)\r\n\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3022, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'A description of the regulatory framework in which the plan operates, for example, the level of any minimum funding requirements, and any effects of the regulatory framework on the plan, such as the asset ceiling?', 'b', 'IAS\r\n19.139\r\n(a) (ii)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3023, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'A description of any other entities responsible for the governance of the plan, for example, the responsibilities of the trustees or of the board members of the plan?', 'c', 'IAS\r\n19.139\r\n(a) (iii)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3024, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'A description of the risks to which the plan exposes the entity, focused on any unusual, entity specific or plan-specific risks, and of any significant concentrations of risk.  E.g., if the plan assets are invested primarily in one class of investment, such as property, the plan may expose the entity to a concentration of property market risk?', 'd', 'IAS\r\n19.139 (b)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3025, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'A description of any plan amendments, curtailments and settlements?', 'e', 'IAS\r\n19.139 (c) \r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3026, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', '<p>A reconciliation of opening and closing balances for each of the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The net defined benefit liability (asset), showing separate reconciliations for:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>plan assets; </li>\r\n            <li>the present value of the defined benefit obligation; and</li>\r\n            <li>the effects of the asset ceiling;</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>Any reimbursement rights?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.2a', 'IAS\r\n19.140(a) ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3027, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'An entity shall also describe the relationship between any reimbursement right and the related obligation.', '3.2b', 'IAS\r\n19.140(b)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3028, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'For each of the reconciliations noted in 3.2a above, are the following shown as reconciling items (if applicable):\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>current service cost;</li>\r\n    <li>interest income or expense;</li>\r\n    <li>re-measurement of the defined benefit liability (asset), showing separately:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>the return on plan assets, less amounts included in (b) above;</li>\r\n            <li>actuarial gains and losses arising from changes in demographic assumptions; </li>\r\n            <li>actuarial gains and losses arising from changes in financial assumptions;</li>\r\n            <li>changes in the effects of limiting a net defined benefit plan asset to the asset ceiling, excluding amounts included in (b) above;</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>past service cost and gains and losses arising from settlements (see paragraph IAS 19.100 for additional guidance);</li>\r\n    <li>the effect of changes in foreign exchange rates;</li>\r\n    <li>contributions (splitting out employer and employee);</li>\r\n    <li>payments from the plan, showing separately the amounts paid in respect of any settlements;</li>\r\n    <li>the effect of business combinations and disposals?</li>\r\n</ol>', '3.3', 'IAS\r\n19.141\r\n(except c(iv))', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3029, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Where a plan is in surplus, has it been disclosed how the maximum economic benefit available to the entity has been determined, i.e. whether those benefits would be in the form of refunds, reduction in future contributions or a combination of both?', '3.4', 'IAS\r\n19.141\r\n(c(iv))\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3030, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', '<b>Plan Assets</b>\r\n<p>Plan assets need to be suitably analysed into classes that distinguish the nature and risk of those assets.  Has such an analysis been given?</p>\r\n<p>IAS 19 includes the following illustrative example:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Cash and cash equivalents;</li>\r\n    <li>Equity instruments (segregated by industry type, company size, geography etc.);</li>\r\n    <li>Debt instruments (segregated by type of issuer, credit quality, geography etc.);</li>\r\n    <li>Real estate (segregated by geography etc.);</li>\r\n    <li>Derivatives (segregated by type of underlying risk in the contract, for example, interest rate contracts, foreign exchange contracts; equity contracts, credit contracts, longevity swaps etc.);</li>\r\n    <li>Investment funds (segregated by type of fund);</li>\r\n    <li>Asset-backed securities; and </li>\r\n    <li>Structured debt.	</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>3.5a</b>', 'IAS\r\n19.142\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3031, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'The classifications above should be further split into those that have a quoted market price in an active market (as defined by IFRS 13 Fair Value Measurement) and those that do not.', '3.5b', 'IAS\r\n19.142\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3032, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Where the plan assets include:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The entity’s own transferable financial instruments; or</li>\r\n    <li>Any property occupied by the entity; or</li>\r\n    <li>Any other assets used by entity, has the fair value of each of these types of assets been disclosed?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.6', 'IAS\r\n19.143', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3033, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', '<b>Actuarial Valuations</b>\r\n<p>Whilst not specifically required by the IAS 19, to put the actuarial information in context, consideration should be given to disclosing:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The date of the last comprehensive actuarial valuation; and</li>\r\n    <li>If the last actuarial valuation was not co-terminus with the reporting date, a description of the adjustment made to ‘flex’ the last actuarial valuation to give the position at the reporting date.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>3.7</b>', 'Best\r\nPractice', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3034, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', '<b>Actuarial Assumptions</b>\r\n<p>Have the significant actuarial assumptions been disclosed?</p>\r\n<p>This disclosure must be in absolute terms (e.g., an absolute percentage, and not just as a margin between different percentages or other variables).</p>\r\n<p>Where an entity provides disclosures in total for grouping of plans, it shall provide such disclosures in the form of weighted averages or relatively narrow ranges.</p>', '<b>3.8</b>', 'IAS\r\n19.144\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3035, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', '<b>Actuarial Assumptions and Sensitivity Analysis</b>\r\n<p>Has a sensitivity analysis for each significant actuarial assumption (as disclosed under point 3.8) as of the end of the reporting period been disclosed; showing how the defined benefit obligation would have been affected by changes in the relevant actuarial assumptions that were reasonably possible at that date?</p>\r\n', '<b>3.9</b>', 'IAS\r\n19.145(a)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3036, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Have the methods and assumptions used in preparing the sensitivity analyses been disclosed, along with the limitations of those methods?', '3.10', 'IAS\r\n19.145 (b)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3037, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Have changes since the previous period in the methods and assumptions used in preparing the sensitivity analyses been disclosed, and the reasons for such changes noted?', '3.11', 'IAS\r\n19.145 (c )', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3038, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', '<b>Other Disclosures</b>\r\n<p>Is a description of any asset-liability matching strategies used by the plan or the entity, including the use of annuities and other techniques, such as longevity swaps, to manage risk been disclosed?</p>', '<b>3.12</b>', 'IAS\r\n19.146', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3039, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Has an indication been given of the effect of the defined benefit plan on the entity’s future cash flows, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A description of any funding arrangements and funding policy that affects future contributions;</li>\r\n    <li>The expected contributions to the plan for the next reporting period;</li>\r\n    <li>Information about the maturity profile of the defined benefit obligation.  This should include the weighted average duration of the defined benefit obligation and may include other information about the distribution of and timing of benefits payments, such as maturity analysis of the benefit payments.</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.13', 'IAS\r\n19.147', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3040, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', '<b>Defined Benefit Pension Plans that share risks between Entities under Common Control</b>\r\n<p><b>NB: The disclosures required by IAS 19.149 (c) - (d) do not need to be given if they are disclosed in another group entity’s financial statements and:</b></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b>The group entity’s financial statements separately identify and disclose the information required about the plan; and</b></li>\r\n    <li><b>The group entity’s financial statements are as available to the user of the financial statements on the same terms as the financial statements of the entity and at the same time as, or earlier than, the financial statements of the entity.</b></li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>4</b>', 'IAS\r\n19.150', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3041, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Have the disclosures required by 2.2 above been given?', '4.1', 'IAS\r\n19.148\r\n(a) - (c)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3042, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'If there is a contractual agreement or a stated policy for the charging of the cost of plan, has this been disclosed? Alternatively, if there is no such agreement, has this been disclosed?', '4.2', 'IAS\r\n19.149 (a)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3043, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'Has the policy for determining the contribution to be paid by the entity been disclosed?', '4.3', 'IAS\r\n19.149 (b)\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3044, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'If the plan is accounted for on a defined benefit basis, have the disclosures noted in 3.1 to 3.13 above been made?', '4.4', 'IAS\r\n19.149 (c)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3045, 61, '3.15.2 Ab4b', 'ab4b', 'If the plan is accounted for on a defined contribution basis, have the disclosures noted in 3.1, 3.5a - 3.8 and 3.13 (but only the first two bullet points) above been made?', '4.5', 'IAS\r\n19.149 (d)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:00:53'),
(3046, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<b>General</b>', '<b>1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3047, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>Do the financial statements include a suitably worded accounting policy?</p>\r\n', '1.1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3048, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>Has a description been given of each type of share-based payment arrangement that existed at any time during the period, including their general terms and conditions; e.g.:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The vesting requirements;</li>\r\n    <li>The maximum term of options granted;</li>\r\n    <li>The method of settlement i.e. whether cash-settled or equity-settled?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: Where arrangements are similar, this information may be aggregated.</p>', '1.2', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.45(a)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3049, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<b>Share Options</b>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3050, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>Has the number and weighted average exercise price for share options for each of the following been disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Outstanding at the beginning of the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Granted during the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Forfeited during the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Exercised during the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Expired during the period;</li>\r\n    <li>Outstanding at the period end; and </li>\r\n    <li>Exercisable at the period end?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.1', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.45(b)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3051, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>For share options exercised during the period, has the weighted average share price at the date of exercise been disclosed?  </p>\r\n<p>NB: If options were exercised on a regular basis throughout the period, the entity may instead disclose the weighted average share price during the period.</p>', '2.2', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.45(c)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3052, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>For share options outstanding at the end of the period, have the following been disclosed;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The range of exercise prices; and</li>\r\n    <li>Weighted average remaining contractual life?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: If the range of exercise prices is wide, the outstanding options shall be divided into ranges that are meaningful for assessing the number and timing of additional shares that may be issued and the cash that may be received upon exercise of those options.</p>\r\n', '2.3', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.45(d)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c3` (`acID`, `c3tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `drps`, `crps`, `drfp`, `crfp`, `issue`, `recommendation`, `result`, `yesno`, `comment`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(3053, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<b>Equity-Settled Share-Based Payment Arrangements ~ Valued by Reference to the Equity Instrument Granted</b>', '<b>3</b>', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.46</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3054, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>Are the following disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        For share options granted in the period, the weighted average fair value of those options at the measurement date and information on how the fair value was measured, including:\r\n        <p>The option pricing model used and the inputs to that model including:</p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>the weighted average share price;</li>\r\n            <li>exercise price;</li>\r\n            <li>expected volatility;</li>\r\n            <li>option life;</li>\r\n            <li>expected dividends;</li>\r\n            <li>the risk free interest rate; and</li>\r\n            <li>any other inputs to the model (including the method used and the assumptions made to incorporate the effects of expected early exercise)?</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n        <p>How expected volatility was determined (including how much was based on historical volatility); and</p>\r\n        <p>Whether and how any other features of the option grant were incorporated into fair value measurement, such as market conditions?</p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '3.1', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.47(a)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3055, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>For other equity instruments granted in the period (i.e. other than share options), have the number and weighted average fair value of those instruments at the measurement date, and information on how fair value was measured been disclosed, including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>If fair value was not measured on the basis of an observable market price, how it was determined;</li>\r\n    <li>Whether and how expected dividends were incorporated into the measurement of fair value; and</li>\r\n    <li>Whether and how any other features of the equity instruments granted were incorporated into the measurement of fair value?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.2', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.47(b)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3056, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>For share-based payments modified during the period, include the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>An explanation of the modifications;</li>\r\n    <li>The incremental fair value granted; and</li>\r\n    <li>Information on how the incremental fair value was measured?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.3', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.47(c)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3057, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<b>Equity-Settled Share-Based Payment Arrangements ~ Valued by Reference to the Goods or Services Received</b>', '<b>4</b>', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.46</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3058, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>Has it been disclosed how the fair value of goods and services was determined (e.g. whether fair value was measured at a market price for those goods and services)?</p>', '4.1', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.48</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3059, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>If the entity has rebutted the presumption that fair value of goods and services other than employee services can be estimated reliably (IFRS 2.13), is that fact disclosed, together with an explanation as to why?</p>', '4.2', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.49</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3060, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<b>Cash-Settled Share-Based Payment Arrangements</b>', '<b>5</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3061, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>Has it been disclosed how the liability has been measured?</p>\r\n<p>HAT believes that this disclosure should be given to comply with a number of the general disclosure provisions of IFRS 2, including IFRS 2.44.</p>', '5.1', '<p>Best Practice</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3062, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<b>Impact on Profit or Loss and Financial Position</b>', '<b>6</b>', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.50</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3063, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>Has the total expense arising from share-based payments recognised in profit or loss been disclosed split between:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Equity-settled share-based payment transactions; and</li>\r\n    <li>Cash-settled share-based payment transactions?</li>\r\n</ul>', '6.1', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.51(a)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3064, 62, '3.15.3 Ab4c', 'ab4c', '<p>For liabilities arising from share-based payments, have the following been disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The total carrying value at the end of the period; and</li>\r\n    <li>The total intrinsic value at the end of the period of liabilities for which the counterparty’s right to cash or other assets had vested by the end of the period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '6.2', '<p>IFRS </p>\r\n<p>2.51(b)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:14:10'),
(3065, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<b>Accounting Policy</b>', '<b>1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3066, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Has an accounting policy been noted for each class of biological asset and its related agricultural produce?</p>', '1.1', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3067, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<b>Performance</b>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3068, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Has the aggregate gain or loss arising during the current period on initial recognition of biological assets and agricultural produce and from change in fair value less costs to sell of biological assets been disclosed?</p>', '2.1', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.40</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3069, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<b>General</b>', '<b>3</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3070, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Has a description been given of each group of biological assets?</p>\r\n<p>NB: Additional guidance is given in paragraphs 42 to 45 of IAS 41 as to what this might consist of.</p>', '3.1', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.41</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3071, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Have the following been disclosed:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature of the activities, involving each group of biological assets; and </li>\r\n    <li>Output of agricultural produce during the period?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: If this disclosure has been given in another part of the Annual Report, such as the Directors’ Report, then it does not need to be duplicated.</p>', '3.2', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.46</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3072, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<b>Securitisation, Commitments and Risk</b>', '<b>4</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3073, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Has the existence and carrying amount of biological assets whose title is restricted been disclosed?</p>', '4.1', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.49(a)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3074, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Have the carrying amounts of biological assets pledged as security for liabilities been disclosed?</p>', '4.2', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.49(a)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3075, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Has the amount of any commitments for the development or acquisition of biological assets been disclosed?</p>', '4.3', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.49(b)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3076, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Have the financial risk management strategies related to agricultural activities been disclosed?</p>', '4.4', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.49(c)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3077, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<b>Reconciliation</b>', '<b>5</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3078, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Has a reconciliation of each class of biological asset been disclosed, including:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>brought forward carrying amount;</li>\r\n    <li>the gain or loss arising from changes in fair value less costs to sell;</li>\r\n    <li>increases resulting from purchases;</li>\r\n    <li>decreases resulting from sales and biological assets classified as held for sale (or included in a disposal group that is classified as held for sale) in accordance with IFRS 5;</li>\r\n    <li>decreases resulting from harvesting;</li>\r\n    <li>increases resulting from business combinations;</li>\r\n    <li>net exchange differences arising on the translation of financial statements into a different presentation currency, and on the translation of a foreign operation into the presentation currency of the reporting entity;</li>\r\n    <li>other changes; and</li>\r\n    <li>carried forward carrying amount?</li>\r\n</ul>', '5.1', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.50</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3079, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>The following disclosure is <b>encouraged</b> (particularly where the production cycle is in excess of one year):</p>\r\n<p>A change in fair value might be due to physical changes and also changes in price.  By group or otherwise, is the amount of change in fair value less costs to sell included in the profit or loss split between the amount due to physical changes and the amount due to price changes?</p>\r\n', '5.2', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.51</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3080, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Where an event such as virulent disease, a flood, a severe drought or frost or a plague of insects give rise to a material expense, has the nature and amount of this expense been disclosed in accordance with IAS 1?</p>', '5.3', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.53</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3081, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<b>Biological Assets Held at Cost Less Accumulated Depreciation / Impairment</b>', '<b>6</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3082, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Have the following disclosures been given:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A description of the biological assets;</li>\r\n    <li>An explanation as to why fair value cannot be measured reliably;</li>\r\n    <li>(If possible) the range of estimates within which fair value is highly likely to lie;</li>\r\n    <li>The depreciation method used;</li>\r\n    <li>The useful lives or the depreciation rates used; and</li>\r\n    <li>The gross carrying amount and the accumulated depreciation (aggregated with accumulated impairment losses) at the beginning and the end of the reporting period?</li>\r\n</ul>', '6.1', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.54</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3083, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>In the reconciliation required by 5.1 above, have the following been disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Impairment losses;</li>\r\n    <li>Reversal of impairment losses; and</li>\r\n    <li>Depreciation?</li>\r\n</ul>', '6.2', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.55</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3084, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>In the reconciliation required by 5.1 above, has the gain or loss on disposal been split between biological assets carried at fair value and those carried at cost?</p>', '6.3', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.55</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3085, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>If the fair value of biological assets previously measured at their cost less any accumulated depreciation and any accumulated impairment losses becomes reliably measurable during the current period, has the following been disclosed:-</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A description of the biological asset;</li>\r\n    <li>An explanation of why fair value has become reliably measurable; and </li>\r\n    <li>The effect of the change?</li>\r\n</ul>', '6.4', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.56</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3086, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<b>Government Grants</b>\r\n<p>NB: Government Grants which relate to biological assets held at fair value are scoped out of IAS 20, and into IAS 41.</p>', '<b>7</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3087, 63, '3.15.4 Ab4d', 'ab4d', '<p>Regarding government grants which are within the scope of IAS 41 have the following been disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The nature and extent of government grants recognised in the financial statements;</li>\r\n    <li>Unfulfilled conditions and other contingencies attaching to government grants; and</li>\r\n    <li>Significant decreases expected in the level of government grants?</li>\r\n</ul>', '7.1', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>41.57</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:18:50'),
(3110, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Comparative Information</b>', '<b>1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3111, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>On first time adoption, comparative figures must be presented in accordance with IFRS subject to specific exemptions and prohibitions contained within IFRS 1.  </p>\r\n<p><b><u>However, it is also necessary to present and disclose the Statement of Financial Position at the transition date.</u></b></p>\r\n<p>Have comparatives (including two years comparatives for the Statement of Financial Position) been disclosed in accordance with IFRS 1?</p>', '1.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.6, 21</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3112, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>Where historical summaries or comparative information using previous GAAP is shown (on a voluntary basis), is:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>This information prominently labelled as not being prepared under IFRS; and</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the main adjustments required to make it comply with IFRS?</li>\r\n</ul>', '1.2', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.22</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3113, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>If the entity did not present financial statements for the previous period, has this been disclosed?</p>', '1.3', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.28</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3114, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Explanation of Transition to IFRS</b>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3115, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>Is an explanation provided explaining how the transition from previous GAAP to IFRS affected the reported financial performance, position and cash flows?</p>', '2.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.23A</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3116, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>If the entity applied IFRS historically (however, it did not in the previous financial period, as it did not have an explicit and unreserved statement of compliance) has it disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The reason it stopped apply IFRS; and</li>\r\n    <li>The reason it is resuming the application of IFRS?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.2', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.23B, 4A</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3117, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>In the situation noted in 2.2, if the entity elects not to apply IFRS 1, has it explained the reasons for electing to apply IFRS as if it had never stopped applying them?</p>', '2.3', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.23B, 4A</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3118, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Reconciliations</b>', '<b>3</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3119, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>Are the following disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Reconciliations to the entity’s equity reported under previous GAAP to IFRS for the following dates:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>The date of transition to IFRS; and</li>\r\n            <li>The end of the latest period presented under previous GAAP;</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>A reconciliation of the last total comprehensive income reported under previous GAAP to the total comprehensive income shown for the same period under IFRS?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>These reconciliations must give sufficient detail to enable the user to understand the material adjustment(s) to the Statement of Financial Position and the Statement of Comprehensive Income.</p>\r\n<p>Errors made under previous GAAP and identified during the transitional process must be distinguished from transitional adjustments that relate to changes in accounting policies.</p>', '3.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.24(a)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.24(b)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.25</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.26</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3120, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>If the entity presented a Statement of Cash Flows under its previous GAAP, has it explained the material adjustments to the Statement of Cash Flows?</p>', '3.2', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.25</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3121, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>If the entity recognised or reversed any impairment losses for the first time in preparing its opening IFRS Statement of Financial Position, have the disclosures that would have been required if the entity had recognised these in the period beginning with the date of transition to IFRS been disclosed?</p>', '3.3', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.24(c)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IAS 36</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3122, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Where Interim Financial Statements have Already been Prepared under IFRS</b>', '<b>4</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3123, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>IIf, during the period covered by its first IFRS financial statements, an entity changes its accounting policies or its use of the exemptions contained within IFRS 1, has it explained the changes between its first IFRS interim financial report and its first IFRS financial statements, in accordance with paragraph 23, and has it updated the reconciliation required by paragraphs 24(a) and (b)?</p>', '4.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.27A</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3124, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Designation of Financial Assets or Financial Liabilities</b>', '<b>5</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3125, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<p>If the entity is permitted to designate previously recognised financial assets or liabilities at ‘fair value through profit or loss’ or as ‘available-for-sale’, are the following disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The fair value of any financial assets or liabilities designated into each category (at the date of designation); and</li>\r\n    <li>The classification and carrying amount in the previous financial statements?</li>\r\n</ul>', '5.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.29</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3126, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Use of Fair Value as Deemed Cost</b>', '<b>6</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3127, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Property, Plant or Equipment, Investment Properties or Intangibles</b>\r\n<p>If fair value is used as deemed cost in the transitional Statement of Financial Position, for any of the assets noted above, do the financial statements disclose:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The aggregate of those fair values; and</li>\r\n    <li>The aggregate adjustment to the carrying amounts reported under previous GAAP?</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>6.1</b>', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.30</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3128, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Investments in Subsidiaries, Joint Ventures or Associates</b>\r\n<p>If fair value is used as deemed cost in the transitional Statement of Financial Position (parent as opposed to consolidated), for any of the assets noted above, do the financial statements disclose:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The aggregate deemed cost of those investments for which deemed cost is their previous GAAP carrying amount;</li>\r\n    <li>The aggregate deemed cost of those investments for which deemed cost is fair value; and </li>\r\n    <li>The aggregate adjustment to the carrying amounts reported under previous GAAP?</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>6.2</b>', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.31</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3129, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Oil and Gas Assets</b>\r\n<p>If an entity uses the exemptions in paragraph D8A(b) of IFRS 1 for oil and gas assets, has it disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>That fact; and</li>\r\n    <li>The basis on which carrying amounts determined under previous GAAP were allocated?</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>6.3</b>', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.31A</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3130, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Operations Subject to Rate Regulations</b>\r\n<p>If an entity uses the exemptions in paragraph D8B of IFRS 1 for operations subject to rate regulations, has it disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>That fact; and</li>\r\n    <li>The basis on which carrying amounts determined under previous GAAP were allocated?</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>6.4</b>', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.31B</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3131, 64, '3.15.5 Ab4e', 'ab4e', '<b>Severe Hyperinflation</b>\r\n<p>If an entity elects to measure assets and liabilities at fair value and to use that fair value as deemed cost in its opening IFRS Statement of Financial Position because of severe hyperinflation, has it disclosed, how, and why the entity had, and then ceased to have, a functional currency that has both of the following characteristics:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A reliable general price index is not available to all entities with transactions and balances in the currency; and</li>\r\n    <li>Exchangeability between the currency and a relatively stable foreign currency does not exist?</li>\r\n</ul>', '<b>6.5</b>', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>1.31C</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:23:32'),
(3132, 65, '3.15.6 Ab4f', 'ab4f', '<b>Basis of Exemption </b>', '<b>1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:26:09'),
(3133, 65, '3.15.6 Ab4f', 'ab4f', '<p>Has it been noted that the exemption in IFRS 10 paragraph 4 (intermediate holding company exemption) or paragraph 31 (investment entities where no subsidiaries require consolidation) has been taken advantage of?</p>', '1.1', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>27.16 (a)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:26:09'),
(3134, 65, '3.15.6 Ab4f', 'ab4f', '<p>Where the exemptions in IFRS 10, paragraph 4 have been taken advantage of, have the following been given regarding the parent undertaking whose result include this intermediate parent company’s results:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Name;</li>\r\n    <li>Principal place of business (if unincorporated, or different from the place of incorporation);</li>\r\n    <li>The country of incorporation;</li>\r\n    <li>The address where consolidated IFRS financial statements can be obtained from.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>NB: It may be necessary to file a copy of the audited consolidated financial statements with the company’s financial statements (with a certified translation).</p>\r\n', '1.3', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>27.16 (a)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:26:09'),
(3135, 65, '3.15.6 Ab4f', 'ab4f', '<b>Significant Investments in Subsidiaries, Joint Ventures and Associates</b>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:26:09'),
(3136, 65, '3.15.6 Ab4f', 'ab4f', '<p>(Excluding investment entities) for each significant investment in a subsidiary, joint venture or associate are the following disclosed:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Name;</li>\r\n    <li>The principal place of business (and country of incorporation, if different);</li>\r\n    <li>The holding company’s proportion of the ownership interest (and its proportion of the voting rights, if different) held in those investments?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.1', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>27.16(b)</p>\r\n<p>27.17</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:26:09'),
(3137, 65, '3.15.6 Ab4f', 'ab4f', '<p>Is there an accounting policy as to how investments in subsidiaries, joint ventures and associates have been accounted for?</p>', '2.2', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>27.16 (c)</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:26:09'),
(3138, 65, '3.15.6 Ab4f', 'ab4f', '<b>Investment Entities </b>', '<b>3</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:26:09'),
(3139, 65, '3.15.6 Ab4f', 'ab4f', '<p>Where the client is an investment entity have the disclosure required by IFRS 12 been given?</p>', '3.1', '<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>27.16A</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:26:09'),
(3165, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', '<p>IFRS 16 is applied using one of the following two methods: </p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>The “retrospective” method: apply the Standard retrospectively to each prior reporting period presented in accordance with IAS 8 Accounting Policies, Changes in Accounting Estimates and Errors, subject to the expedients in paragraph IFRS 16.C3; or</li>\r\n    <li>The “cumulative effect” method: retrospectively with the cumulative effect of initially applying IFRS 16 recognised as an adjustment to the opening balance of retained earnings (or other component of equity, as appropriate) of the annual reporting period that includes the date of initial application. </li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><i>For the purposes of the transition requirements, the date of initial application is the start of the reporting period in which an entity first applies this Standard (i.e. 1 January 2019 for a 31 December 2019 year-end);</i></p>\r\n<p><b>Confirm here which transition method is being used: </b></p>\r\n<p><b>Retrospective method / Cumulative effect method </b></p>\r\n<p>Have the appropriate sections of the checklist below been completed? </p>', '1.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>16. C5</p>\r\n\r\n<p>16. C7</p>\r\n\r\n<p>16. C2</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3166, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', '<b>Transition to IFRS 16 using the “Retrospective” method</b>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3167, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', '<p>Has the entity disclosed the adjustments made to the opening balance of each affected component of equity for the earliest prior period presented and the other comparative amounts disclosed for each prior period presented as if IFRS 16 had always been applied?</p>', '2.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>16. C5</p>\r\n<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>8.22</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3168, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', 'When the initial application of IFRS 16 has an effect on the current period or any prior period, or might have an effect on future periods, has the entity disclosed:\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>The title of the IFRS;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, that the change in accounting policy is made in accordance with its transitional provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the change in accounting policy;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, a description of the transitional provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, the transitional provisions that might have an effect on future periods;</li>\r\n    <li>For the immediately prior period presented, the amount of the adjustment for each financial statement line item affected (including lines in the statement of cash flows); </li>\r\n    <li>The amount of the adjustment relating to periods before those presented, to the extent practicable; and </li>\r\n    <li>If retrospective application is impracticable for a particular prior period, or for periods before those presented, the circumstances that led to the existence of that condition and a description of how and from when the change in accounting policy has been applied?</li>\r\n</ol>', '2.2', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>16. C5</p><p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>8.28</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3169, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', '<p>When applying IFRS 16 using the Retrospective method, an entity can take advantage of the practical expedient set out in IFRS 16. C3.</p>\r\n<p>If this expedient has been taken advantage of, has this fact been disclosed? </p>', '2.3', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>16. C3</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3170, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', '<b>Transition to IFRS 16 using the “Cumulative effect” method</b>', '<b>3</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3171, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', '<p>For leases previously classified as operating leases under IAS 17, has the entity recognised the following at the date of initial application:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A lease liability; and</li>\r\n    <li>A right of use asset? </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>The date of initial application is 1 January 2019 for a 31 December 2019 year end. </i></p>', '3.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>15. C8</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3172, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', '<p>When applying IFRS 16 using the Cumulative effect method, an entity can take advantage of certain practical expedients, as set out in IFRS 16. C10.</p>\r\n<p>Where one or more of the practical expedients has been taken advantage of, has the entity disclosed that fact? </p>', '3.2', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>16. C10, C13</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3173, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', '<p>Is there disclosure of the following: </p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>The weighted average lessee’s incremental borrowing rate applied to lease liabilities recognised in the statement of financial position at the date of initial application; and</li>\r\n    <li>an explanation of any difference between:\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>operating lease commitments disclosed applying IAS 17 at the end of the annual reporting period immediately preceding the date of initial application, discounted using the incremental borrowing rate at the date of initial application as described in IFRS 16.C8(a); and</li>\r\n            <li>lease liabilities recognised in the statement of financial position at the date of initial application.</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ol>', '3.2', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>16. C12</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3174, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', '<b>Transition to IFRS 16 using the “Cumulative effect” method</b>', '<b>3</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3175, 67, '3.15.8 Ab4h', 'ab4h', '<p>When the initial application of IFRS 16 has an effect on the current period or any prior period, or might have an effect on future periods, has the entity disclosed:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>The title of the IFRS;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, that the change in accounting policy is made in accordance with its transitional provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the change in accounting policy;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, a description of the transitional provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, the transitional provisions that might have an effect on future periods;</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of the adjustment relating to periods before those presented, to the extent practicable; and </li>\r\n    <li>If retrospective application is impracticable for a particular prior period, or for periods before those presented, the circumstances that led to the existence of that condition and a description of how and from when the change in accounting policy has been applied.</li>\r\n</ol>', '3.3', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>16. C12</p><p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>8.28</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:42:43'),
(3176, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<b>IFRS 15 Revenue from Contracts with Customers</b>', '<b>1</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3177, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>IFRS 15 is applied using one of the following two methods: </p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>The “retrospective” method: apply the Standard retrospectively to each prior reporting period presented in accordance with IAS 8 Accounting Policies, Changes in Accounting Estimates and Errors, subject to the expedients in paragraph IFRS 15.C5; or</li>\r\n    <li>The “cumulative effect” method: retrospectively with the cumulative effect of initially applying IFRS 15 recognised as an adjustment to the opening balance of retained earnings (or other component of equity, as appropriate) of the annual reporting period that includes the date of initial application. The entity may elect to apply IFRS 15 retrospectively only to contracts that are not completed contracts at the date of initial application.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><i>For the purposes of the transition requirements: </i></p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li><i></i>the date of initial application is the start of the reporting period in which an entity first applies this Standard (i.e. 1 January 2018 for a 31 December 2018 year end);</li>\r\n    <li><i>a completed contract is a contract for which the entity has transferred all of the goods or services identified in accordance with IAS 11 Construction Contracts, IAS 18 Revenue and related Interpretations.</i></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<b>Confirm here which transition method is being used: </b><br>\r\n<b>Retrospective method / Cumulative effect method </b>\r\n<p>Have the appropriate sections of the checklist below been completed? </p>', '1.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>15. C3</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15. C3, C7</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15. C2</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3178, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<b>Transition to IFRS 15 using the “Retrospective” method</b>', '<b>2</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3179, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>Has the entity disclosed the adjustments made to the opening balance of each affected component of equity for the earliest prior period presented and the other comparative amounts disclosed for each prior period presented as if IFRS 15 had always been applied?</p>', '2.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>15. C3</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>IAS 8.22</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3180, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>When the initial application of IFRS 15 has an effect on the current period or any prior period, or might have an effect on future periods, has the entity disclosed:</p>\r\n<ol type=\"a\">\r\n    <li>The title of the IFRS;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, that the change in accounting policy is made in accordance with its transitional provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>The nature of the change in accounting policy;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, a description of the transitional provisions;</li>\r\n    <li>Where applicable, the transitional provisions that might have an effect on future periods;</li>\r\n    <li>For the immediately prior period presented, the amount of the adjustment for each financial statement line item affected (including lines in the statement of cash flows); NB 1</li>\r\n    <li>The amount of the adjustment relating to periods before those presented, to the extent practicable; and </li>\r\n    <li>If retrospective application is impracticable for a particular prior period, or for periods before those presented, the circumstances that led to the existence of that condition and a description of how and from when the change in accounting policy has been applied?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><i><b>NB 1</b>: Notwithstanding the requirements of paragraph 28 of IAS 8, when IFRS 15 is first applied (using the Retrospective method) an entity need only present the quantitative information required by paragraph 28(f) of IAS 8 for the annual period immediately preceding the first annual period for which this Standard is applied. An entity may also present this information for the current period or for earlier comparative periods, but is not required to do so.</i></p>', '2.2', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>15. C3</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IAS</p>\r\n<p>IAS 8.28</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3181, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>When applying IFRS 15 using the Retrospective method, an entity can take advantage of certain practical expedients, as set out in IFRS 15. C5.</p>\r\n<p>Has the entity disclosed the following in respect of any practical expedients used on transition:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The expedients that have been used; and</li>\r\n    <li>To the extent reasonably possible, a qualitative assessment of the estimated effect of applying each of those expedients?</li>\r\n</ul>', '2.3', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>15. C5, C6</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3182, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<b>Transition to IFRS 15 using the “Cumulative effect” method</b>', '<b>3</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3183, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>Has the entity disclosed the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the amount by which each financial statement line item is affected in the current reporting period by the application of this Standard as compared to IAS 11, IAS 18 and related Interpretations that were in effect before the change; and</li>\r\n    <li>an explanation of the reasons for significant changes identified above?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>This disclosure is only required to be given for the reporting period that includes the date of initial application (i.e. the 31 December 2018 reporting period where 1 January 2018 is the date of initial application). </i></p>', '3.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>15. C8</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3184, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>When applying IFRS 15 using the Cumulative effect method, an entity can take advantage of certain practical expedients, as set out in IFRS 15. C7A.</p>\r\n<p>Has the entity disclosed the following in respect of any practical expedients used on transition:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The expedients that have been used; and</li>\r\n    <li>To the extent reasonably possible, a qualitative assessment of the estimated effect of applying each of those expedients?</li>\r\n</ul>', '3.2', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>15. C7A, C6</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3185, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<b>IFRS 9 Financial Instruments</b>', '<b>4</b>', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3186, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>On transition, IFRS 9 is applied retrospectively in accordance with IAS 8 Accounting Policies, Changes in Accounting Estimates and Errors, expect as specified in IFRS 9.7.2.4 to 7.2.26 and 7.2.28. However, IFRS 9 is not applied to items that have already been derecognised at the date of initial application (i.e. 1 January 2018 for a 31 December 2018 year end). </p>', '', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>9. 7.2.1</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3187, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>Prior periods do not need to be restated; the entity can choose to restate prior periods if, and only if, it is possible without the use of hindsight.  However, the transition disclosures as set out in IFRS 7.42L to 42O will still be required. If prior periods are not restated, the difference between the previous carrying amount and the carrying amount at the date of initial application is recognised as an adjustment to the opening balance of retained earnings (or other component of equity, as appropriate) of the reporting period that includes the date of initial application.</p>', '', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>9. 7.2.15</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3188, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>Depending on the entity’s chosen approach to applying IFRS 9, the transition can involve one or more than one date of initial application for different requirements (e.g. if an entity has early adopted the requirement for the presentation of gains and losses on financial liabilities designated as at fair value through profit or loss).</p>\r\n<p>IFRS 9 itself does not contain any disclosure requirements; it is a Standard which changes the classification and measurement of financial instruments. IFRS 7 Financial Instruments: Disclosures deals with the disclosure requirements. </p>\r\n<p>Paragraphs 42I to 42S of IFRS 7 set out the disclosure requirements of initial application of IFRS 9. </p>\r\n<p>Key to abbreviations used in this checklist:</p>\r\n<p>FVTPL = Fair value through profit or loss</p>\r\n<p>FVOCI = Fair value through other comprehensive income</p>', '', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>9. 7.2.2</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3189, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>In the reporting period that includes the date of initial application of IFRS 9 (which will likely just be the current reporting period), has the entity disclosed the following information for each class of financial assets and financial liabilities as at the date of initial application:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the original measurement category and carrying amount determined in accordance with IAS 39 or in accordance with a previous version of IFRS 9 (if the entity’s chosen approach to applying IFRS 9 involves more than one date of initial application for different requirements);</li>\r\n    <li>the new measurement category and carrying amount determined in accordance with IFRS 9; and</li>\r\n    <li>the amount of any financial assets and financial liabilities in the statement of financial position that were previously designated as measured at fair value through profit or loss but are no longer so designated, distinguishing between those that IFRS 9 requires an entity to reclassify and those that an entity elects to reclassify at the date of initial application?</li>\r\n</ul>', '4.1', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42I</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3190, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>In the reporting period that includes the date of initial application of IFRS 9, has sufficient qualitative disclosure been given to enable users to understand:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>how it applied the classification requirements in IFRS 9 to those financial assets whose classification has changed as a result of applying IFRS 9; and</li>\r\n    <li>the reasons for any designation or de-designation of financial assets or financial liabilities as measured at fair value through profit or loss at the date of initial application?</li>\r\n</ul>', '4.2', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42J</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3191, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>Depending on the entity’s chosen approach to applying IFRS 9, the transition can involve more than one date of initial application (as per the introductory narrative).</p>\r\n<p>If the entity has more than one date of initial application, have the disclosures above in 4.1 and 4.2 been given for each date of initial application?</p>\r\n<i><p>NB: the entity shall present disclosures from 4.1 in a table unless another format is more appropriate.</p></i>', '4.3', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42J</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3192, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>Has disclosure been given of the changes in the classifications of financial assets and financial liabilities as at the date of initial application of IFRS 9, showing separately:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the changes in the carrying amounts on the basis of their measurement categories in accordance with IAS 39 (i.e. not resulting from a change in </li>\r\n    <li>measurement attribute on transition to IFRS 9); and the changes in the carrying amounts arising from a change in measurement attribute on transition to IFRS 9?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>NB: The disclosures in this paragraph need not be made after the annual reporting period in which the entity initially applies the classification and measurement requirements for financial assets in IFRS 9.</i></p>', '4.4', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42L</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02');
INSERT INTO `tbl_c3` (`acID`, `c3tID`, `code`, `type`, `question`, `extent`, `reference`, `initials`, `drps`, `crps`, `drfp`, `crfp`, `issue`, `recommendation`, `result`, `yesno`, `comment`, `other`, `totalcu`, `status`, `remarks`, `added_on`, `updated_on`) VALUES
(3193, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>Has the entity disclosed the following for financial assets and financial liabilities that have been reclassified so that they are measured at amortised cost and, in the case of financial assets, that have been reclassified out of FVTPL so that they are measured at FVOCI, as a result of the transition to IFRS 9:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the fair value of the financial assets or financial liabilities at the end of the reporting period; and</li>\r\n    <li>the fair value gain or loss that would have been recognised in profit or loss or other comprehensive income during the reporting period if the financial assets or financial liabilities had not been reclassified?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>NB: The disclosures in this paragraph need not be made after the annual reporting period in which the entity initially applies the classification and measurement requirements for financial assets in IFRS 9.</i></p>', '4.5', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42M</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3194, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>Has the following been disclosed for financial assets and financial liabilities that have been reclassified out of the FVTPL category as a result of the transition to IFRS 9:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the effective interest rate determined on the date of initial application; and</li>\r\n    <li>the interest revenue or expense recognised?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><i>NB: If an entity treats the fair value of a financial asset or a financial liability as the new gross carrying amount at the date of initial application (see paragraph 7.2.11 of IFRS 9), the disclosures in this paragraph shall be made for each reporting period until derecognition. Otherwise, the disclosures in this paragraph need not be made after the annual reporting period in which the entity initially applies the classification and measurement requirements for financial assets in IFRS 9.</i></p>\r\n', '4.6', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42N</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3195, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>Do the disclosures given in 4.5 and 4.6 above, as well as the disclosures required by paragraph 25 of this IFRS, permit a reconciliation between:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>the measurement categories presented in accordance with IAS 39 and IFRS 9; and</li>\r\n    <li>the class of financial instrument</li>\r\n</ul>', '4.7', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42O</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3196, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>As at the date of initial application of Section 5.5 of IFRS 9 (Impairment), has information been disclosed that permits the reconciliation of the ending impairment allowances in accordance with IAS 39 and the provisions in accordance with IAS 37 to the opening loss allowances determined in accordance with IFRS 9?</p>\r\n<p><i> For financial assets, this disclosure shall be provided by the related financial assets’ measurement categories in accordance with IAS 39 and IFRS 9, and shall show separately the effect of the changes in the measurement category on the loss allowance at that date.</i></p>\r\n', '4.8', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42P</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3197, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>Do the disclosures given in 4.5 and 4.6 above, as well as the disclosures required by paragraph 25 of this IFRS, permit a reconciliation between:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>	the measurement categories presented in accordance with IAS 39 and IFRS 9; and</li>\r\n    <li>	the class of financial instrument</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>as at the date of initial application?</p>', '4.7', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42R</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3198, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>As at the date of initial application of Section 5.5 of IFRS 9 (Impairment), has information been disclosed that permits the reconciliation of the ending impairment allowances in accordance with IAS 39 and the provisions in accordance with IAS 37 to the opening loss allowances determined in accordance with IFRS 9?</p>\r\n<p><i>For financial assets, this disclosure shall be provided by the related financial assets’ measurement categories in accordance with IAS 39 and IFRS 9, and shall show separately the effect of the changes in the measurement category on the loss allowance at that date.</i></p>\r\n', '4.8', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 7.42S</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3199, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>In accordance with paragraph 7.2.4 of IFRS 9, if it is impracticable at the date of initial application of IFRS 9 for an entity to assess a modified time value of money element based on the facts and circumstances that existed at the initial recognition of the financial asset, an entity shall assess the contractual cash flow characteristics of that financial asset based on the facts and circumstances that existed at the initial recognition of the financial asset without taking into account the requirements related to the modification of the time value of money element in paragraphs B4.1.9B–B4.1.9D of IFRS 9. </p>\r\n<p>In these circumstances, has disclosure been given of the carrying amount at the reporting date of those financial assets until those financial assets are derecognised?</p>\r\n', '4.9', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42R</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02'),
(3200, 66, '3.15.7 Ab4g', 'ab4g', '<p>In accordance with paragraph 7.2.4 of IFRS 9, if it is impracticable at the date of initial application of IFRS 9 for an entity to assess a modified time value of money element based on the facts and circumstances that existed at the initial recognition of the financial asset, an entity shall assess the contractual cash flow characteristics of that financial asset based on the facts and circumstances that existed at the initial recognition of the financial asset without taking into account the requirements related to the modification of the time value of money element in paragraphs B4.1.9B–B4.1.9D of IFRS 9. </p>\r\n<p>In these circumstances, has disclosure been given of the carrying amount at the reporting date of those financial assets until those financial assets are derecognised?</p>\r\n', '4.10', '<p>IFRS</p>\r\n<p>7. 42S</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Active', NULL, NULL, '2024-04-17 20:45:02');
